desc: <strong>Leading the future in luxury electric and mobility<br><br></strong>At Lucid, we set out to introduce the most captivating, luxury electric vehicles that elevate the human experience and transcend the perceived limitations of space, performance, and intelligence. Vehicles that are intuitive, liberating, and designed for the future of mobility.<br><br>We plan to lead in this new era of luxury electric by returning to the fundamentals of great design – where every decision we make is in service of the individual and environment. Because when you are no longer bound by convention, you are free to define your own experience.<br><br>Come work alongside some of the most accomplished minds in the industry. Beyond providing competitive salaries, we’re providing a community for innovators who want to make an immediate and significant impact. If you are driven to create a better, more sustainable future, then this is the right place for you.<br><br>Are you ready to embark on a journey where your analytical competency can shape the future of our organization? If you have a passion for turning complex data into actionable insights, we have an exciting opportunity for you. As a Jr Data Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in developing, implementing, and maintaining cutting-edge analytics systems that drive our business forward.<br><br>Your mission will be to extract meaningful information from complex datasets and provide invaluable insights that steer our organization toward growth and success. You will be at the forefront of identifying trends and opportunities, transforming intricate problems into straightforward frameworks, and creating best-practice reports through data mining, analysis, and visualization. Your role will also involve evaluating our internal systems for efficiency, pinpointing areas for improvement, and establishing protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data.<br><br><strong>Role Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li>Develop, implement, and maintain leading-edge analytics systems, taking complicated problems and building simple frameworks.</li><li>Identify trends and opportunities for growth through analysis of complex datasets.</li><li>Evaluate organizational methods and provide source-to-target mappings and information-model specification documents for datasets.</li><li>Create best-practice reports based on data mining, analysis, and visualization.</li><li>Evaluate internal systems for efficiency, problems, and inaccuracies, and develop and maintain protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data.</li><li>Work directly with managers and users to gather requirements, provide status updates, and build relationships.</li><li>Work with project managers to understand and maintain focus on their analytics needs, including critical metrics and KPIs, and deliver actionable insights to relevant decision-makers.</li><li>Proactively analyze data to answer key questions for stakeholders or yourself, with an eye on what drives business performance, and investigate and communicate which areas need improvement in efficiency and productivity.</li><li>Create and maintain rich interactive visualizations through data interpretation and analysis, with reporting components from multiple data sources.</li><li>Develop and maintain databases by acquiring data from primary and secondary sources.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Associate or Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent) in mathematics, computer science,</li><li>Proven analytics skills, including evaluation, and visualization.</li><li>Technical writing experience in relevant areas, including queries, reports, and presentations.</li><li>Strong SQL or Excel skills, with aptitude for learning another analytics tool.</li><li>Proven success in a collaborative, team-oriented environment<br><br></li></ul><strong>Salary Range: </strong>The compensation range for this position is specific to the locations listed below and is the range Lucid reasonably and in good faith expects to pay for the position taking into account the wide variety of factors that are considered in making compensation decisions, including job-related knowledge; skillset; experience, education and training; certifications; and other relevant business and organizational factors.<br><br><ul><li>California (Bay Area) - $92,000 - $115,000<br><br></li></ul><strong>Additional Compensation and Benefits: </strong>Lucid offers a wide range of competitive benefits, including medical, dental, vision, life insurance, disability insurance, vacation, and 401k. The successful candidate may also be eligible to participate in Lucid’s equity program and/or a discretionary annual incentive program, subject to the rules governing such programs. (Cash or equity incentive awards, if any, will depend on various factors, including, without limitation, individual and company performance.)<br><br>Lucid maintains your privacy according to its Candidate Privacy Notice . If you are a California resident, please refer to our California Candidate Privacy Notice .<br><br>At Lucid, we don’t just welcome diversity - we celebrate it! Lucid Motors is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, national or ethnic origin, age, religion, disability, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity and expression, marital status, and any other characteristic protected under applicable State or Federal laws and regulations.<br><br><strong>To all recruitment agencies</strong>: <em>Lucid Motors <strong>does not</strong> accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our careers alias or other Lucid Motors employees. Lucid Motors is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.</em>

<strong>About Stripe<br><br></strong>Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.<br><br><strong>About The Team<br><br></strong>Data Science at Stripe is a vibrant community where data analysts, data scientists and engineers learn and grow together. You will work with some of Stripe’s most fundamental and exciting data, and use that data to help drive company-wide initiatives. We have a variety of Data Analytics roles and teams across Stripe and will seek to align you to the most relevant team based on your background.<br><br>What you'll do<br><br>In this role, you will partner deeply with teams across Stripe to ensure that our users, our products, and our business have the models, data products, and insights needed to make decisions and grow responsibly. You will work closely with partners to extract insights from Stripe's rich and complex data. You will also work with leaders to translate business needs into data problems. You will build metrics, scalable data pipelines, dashboards, and reports to inform and run the business. You will deliver actionable business recommendations through analyses and data storytelling.<br><br>Who you are<br><br>We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.<br><br><strong>Minimum Requirements<br><br></strong><ul><li>2-8+ years experience in Business Intelligence Engineering, Data Engineering, Data Analysis or Data Science roles, building data pipelines and analyzing large datasets to solve problems</li><li>Proficiency in SQL and Python</li><li>Strong statistical knowledge</li><li>Expertise in visualization and using data insights to make recommendations and achieve goals</li><li>Proven ability to manage and deliver on multiple projects with great attention to detail</li><li>Ability to clearly communicate results and drive impact</li><li>Comfortable collaborating across functions to identify data analytics problems and execute solutions with technical rigor and data-driven insights.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Master’s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Engineering, or a related technical field.</li><li>Prior experience at a growth stage internet or software company.</li><li>Experience with distributed data frameworks like Hadoop and Spark to write and debug data pipelines.</li><li>Good understanding of development processes and best practices like engineering standards, code reviews, and testing.<br><br><br></li></ul>Pay and benefits<br><br>The annual US base salary range for this role is $163,852 - $251,077. For sales roles, the range provided is the role’s On Target Earnings ("OTE") range, meaning that the range includes both the sales commissions/sales bonuses target and annual base salary for the role. This salary range may be inclusive of several career levels at Stripe and will be narrowed during the interview process based on a number of factors, including the candidate’s experience, qualifications, and location. Applicants interested in this role and who are not located in the US may request the annual salary range for their location during the interview process.<br><br>Additional benefits for this role may include: equity, company bonus or sales commissions/bonuses; 401(k) plan; medical, dental, and vision benefits; and wellness stipends.

Parade is the leader in providing capacity management tools to freight brokers and 3PLs. Our technology platform revolutionizes the digital landscape for our customers with the vision of becoming the Bloomberg Terminal for Trucking, an $800B industry. Our platform has already been recognized by Inc. Magazine, Business Insider, and FreightTech 100... and we're just getting started!<br><br>Data Analyst<br><br>Parade is revolutionizing the logistics space by tackling its most pressing problems. We use advanced automation, AI, and machine learning to make freight more efficient and transparent. With a steady stream of new products, we're always at the cutting edge, addressing the future needs of freight. Since our breakthrough Series A funding in early 2022, we have rapidly scaled and recently secured an additional $17M in venture funding, fueling our growth and our commitment to driving the future of logistics. Join us in crafting groundbreaking solutions and influencing the future of logistics!<br><br><strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li>Design, develop, and execute SQL queries to retrieve, analyze, and report data for all departments within Parade. </li><li>Collaborate with various teams to identify data needs and translate business questions into actionable insights. </li><li>Support customer inquiries by writing complex SQL queries which allow for actionable insight to support better adoption of Parade's platform. </li><li>Generate comprehensive reports and dashboards that track key performance indicators, helping to drive strategic decisions across the organization. </li><li>Continuously monitor data quality and integrity, troubleshooting any discrepancies and ensuring data accuracy. </li><li>Analyze complex datasets to uncover trends, patterns, and actionable insights that will assist in optimizing business processes and strategies. <br><br></li></ul><strong>What Success Would Look Like in Your First Few Months <br><br></strong><ul><li>In your first 30 days, you'll integrate with the Product and CX departments to become their go-to resource for data retrieval and insights, leading to streamlined operations. </li><li>In the first 60 days, you'll identify and optimize two significant data-driven opportunities that accelerate business growth. </li><li>In your first 90 days, you'll increase data accessibility and transparency by developing repeatable SQL queries that allow teams to independently grab data for frequently requested information. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Basic Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field. </li><li>Minimum of 2 years of professional experience with SQL, including writing complex queries and working with large datasets. </li><li>Proficiency in data visualization tools such as Metabase, Tableau, or similar platforms. </li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy. </li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to present findings to both technical and non-technical audiences. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>High preference for prior experience in a freight tech or logistics environment. </li><li>Experience querying data using BigQuery. </li><li>Familiarity with statistical analysis tools such as Python or R. </li><li>Experience in working with cross-functional teams in a fast-paced startup environment. </li><li>Demonstrated ability to lead data-driven projects from inception to completion with minimal supervision. </li><li>A deep curiosity and passion for uncovering insights from data and a keen business acumen. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Perks<br><br></strong><ul><li>Competitive salary and compensation package with full Medical, Dental, and Vision benefits </li><li>401k plan to help you save for the future </li><li>UNLIMITED Paid Time Off - and we want you to use it! </li><li>100% Remote </li><li>Company Offsites to get to know your teammates <br><br></li></ul><strong>Compensation<br><br></strong>The expected on-target compensation for this role is between $90k-$120k for work performed in the United States. Starting pay for the successful applicant will depend on a variety of job-related factors, which may include experience level, transferrable skills, education, location, business needs, training, and market demands. This range may be modified in the future.<br><br>Parade is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive, positive, professional, and respectful environment for all our employees.

<p><span>Nevro is seeking a Data Analyst who will be responsible for turning data into information, to provide insight into data trends to assist in making business decisions. </span><span>This role will also support various ad-hoc projects. </span></p><p><span>Essential duties and responsibilities:</span></p><ul><li><span>Maintain existing data collection pipelines and develop new ones that optimize data processing efficiency and data quality</span></li><li><span>Collaborates cross functionally to acquire data from main database as well as additional data sources</span></li><li><span>Works closely with business key stakeholders to generate and provide reports based on already developed Python and SQL code</span></li><li><span>Automate new reports using Python and/or SQL</span></li><li><span>Create data visualizations (dashboards, charts, etc.)</span></li><li><span>Assist in correct CRM set up to ensure proper patients care</span></li><li><span>Identify, analyze and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets</span></li><li><span>Locate and define process improvements opportunities</span></li><li><span>Participates in new system end user testing and validation activities where applicable</span></li><li><span>Maintains professional and technical knowledge </span></li><li><span>Knowledge of Tableau or PowerBI</span></li><li><span>Other duties as assigned</span></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><span>Bachelor’s degree in related field or equivalent degree/major required. Years of experience may be substituted for the degree requirement.</span></li><li><span>1-2+ years’ experience</span></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><span>Proven experience as a data analyst</span></li><li><span>Proficient Excel knowledge</span></li><li><span>Python for data analysis and/or SQL knowledge</span></li><li><span>Nice to have Salesforce data model &amp; reports knowledge</span></li><li><span>Nice to have experience with Snowflake</span></li><li><span>Nice to have experience in post market surveillance and/or complaint trending</span></li></ul>

<strong>Title:Data Analyst I, Req# 16351287<br><br></strong><strong>Location: Cupertino , CA (Onsite in the Elk Grove, Cupertino, or Austin area)<br><br></strong><strong>Contract: 6 month<br><br></strong><strong>Job Description<br><br></strong>Key Qualifications<br><br>Strong working knowledge of the Export Administration Regulations, especially Categories 3.<br><br>Experience with Deemed Export review, and submission of IVLs.<br><br>Experience with both h/w and s/w product, part and component classifications.<br><br>Experience with End User Certifications and Nuclear Nonproliferation Statements.<br><br>Familiarity with international regulations is a plus.<br><br>Experience with investigating and researching companies and individuals for sanctions risks<br><br>Excellent oral and written communication skills.<br><br>Prefer 3+ years of general export compliance experience.<br><br>Mac and OS X proficiency is a must.<br><br><strong>Description<br><br></strong>The Global Export &amp; Sanctions Compliance (GESC) team at client aligns with worldwide laws governing the exports of technology and products. We architect creative and innovative solutions to solve compliance challenges at client. As an integral part of the GESC department you will be responsible for a wide array of compliance activities including aligning with the Export Administration Regulation (EAR), International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR), Office of Foreign Asset Control (OFAC), and foreign government agencies. You will research, and classify software, hardware, or 3rd party products, and submit classification requests to relevant government agencies, or applications for export licenses for controlled products or technologies and maintaining corporate records. You will also be responsible for deemed export compliance, reviewing foreign national candidates and submitting IVL export license applications to the BIS, and maintaining records for record retention. Furthermore, you will be developing and executing Export Compliance Awareness trainings, developing and implementing compliance processes and procedures. In addition, you will be expected to participate and contribute to the many other facets of responsibilities which the export compliance department manages across the company. Come join us for an opportunity to work with people that think different.<br><br>Education<br><br>Bachelors degree in international business, international relations, international trade, law degree or a related degree or equivalent work experience..<br><br>client is an Equal Opportunity Employer that is committed to inclusion and diversity. We also take affirmative action to offer employment and advancement opportunities to all applicants, including minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities. client will not discriminate or retaliate against applicants who inquire about, disclose, or discuss their compensation or that of other applicants

We’re constantly refining our approach to data analysis to help better understand hiring trends and their impact on Tesla’s work. We prioritize building tools using open source software that are custom designed to address internal customer needs provide us the agility to make real-1me adjustments. We prioritize building tools using open source software that are custom designed to address internal customer needs and provide us the agility to make real-1me adjustments.<br><br>The Recruiting Analyst will create reporting models that analyze key performance indicators, contribute to the growth of our in-house data tools, and work directly with engineering teams to make system improvements You will support projects/teams effectively to produce the desired results and communicate findings and issues to team standards. Additionally, you will assist in implementing standard policies and procedures for routine service and ensure ongoing adherence to corporate compliance.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li> Execute and monitor production data and data exchange-related processes</li><li> Support projects/teams to produce desired results</li><li> Communicate results and/or issues according to team standards</li><li> Assist in implementing standard policies and procedures for routine service</li><li> Ensure ongoing monitoring and communication of corporate compliance</li><li> Initiate troubleshooting and appropriate notification of issues</li><li> Monitor the status of production processes and progress of issue resolutions</li><li> Shift focus between clients and processes to meet production needs</li><li> Balance incoming requests with previously scheduled work</li><li> Provide assistance and supply information to internal and external personnel</li><li> Develop and maintain effective working relationships with customers<br><br></li></ul><strong>Requirements<br><br></strong><ul><li> Bachelor’s degree in Information Systems or a related field; a relevant combination of education and experience may be considered</li><li> Continuous learning mindset, in line with the Company’s philosophy</li><li> Certification or progress toward certification highly preferred</li><li> One year of experience in a related field, with knowledge in financial analysis, planning, healthcare economics, healthcare policy, statistical modeling, business decisions, analysis, or business management</li><li> Experience in healthcare preferred</li><li> Strong analytical, planning, problem-solving, verbal, and written communication skills</li><li> Intermediate SQL Server/Transact SQL skills</li><li> Ability to work independently, provide direction to others, and collaborate within a team environment</li><li> Proficiency in software packages such as PowerPoint, Excel, and Word</li><li> Effective communication skills with employees and clients at all levels.<br><br></li></ul>If you are seeking a challenging role as an Analyst and have the necessary qualifications and skills, we would love to hear from you. Apply now to be a part of our dynamic team.<br><br>Employment Type: Full-Time

<strong>Title:Data Analyst III, Req# 24099420</strong><p><br></p><strong>Location:Cupertino,CA(Hybrid)</strong><p><br></p><strong>Contract:12+ Month</strong><p><br></p><strong><u>Job Description</u></strong><p><br></p>Client Retail is looking for an experienced Data Analyst to support its Retail Engagement &amp; Marketing team. This position will be responsible for collecting information and turning it into insights.<p><br></p>The position will work closely with the marketing and programming teams to help make data driven decisions.<p><br></p>Key Responsibilities<p><br></p>Create analytics plan for projects in partnership with Marketing and Programming teams<p><br></p>Get a firm understanding of content strategy goals, and help define KPIs that align to those goals<p><br></p>Develop robust data visualizations that will help to quickly and thoroughly answer commonly asked questions about the performance of our content<p><br></p>Identify data anomalies, work to root cause and remediate issues in the data collection, storage, transforms, or reporting<p><br></p><strong><u>Key Qualifications</u></strong><p><br></p>5 7 Years of prior experience<p><br></p>Experience in python and SQL<p><br></p>Experience in Omniture, Tablaeu or similar data visualization tools<p><br></p>An understanding of how customers find and consume digital instructional content<p><br></p>Ability to create complex, cross-object, cross-platform reports<p><br></p>Ability to turn data into information and insights<p><br></p>High-level attention to detail, including the ability to maintain meticulous records of projects, and programs<p><br></p>Self-starter with the ability to work independently<p><br></p>Strong negotiation skills and ability to creatively solve problems<p><br></p>Excellent written and verbal communicator, with engaging interpersonal skills Must have flexibility to deal with rapidly changing, time-constrained launch schedules<p><br></p>A positive, enthusiastic attitude and a sincere willingness to learn from team members at all levels<p><br></p>Must exhibit high degree of ownership and accountability<p><br></p><strong><u>Hard Skills</u></strong><p><br></p>SQL<p><br></p>Python<p><br></p>Data Visualization (Tableau)<p><br></p>Test Processing<p><br></p>PayRate: $58-63/hr,W2

At Kargo, our mission is to build a connective tissue between the physical world of freight and the digital ecosystem used to manage it. We believe that advancements in smart infrastructure are critical to enabling a safer and more efficient future for logistics. Our loading dock sensor platform verifies all incoming and outgoing freight, aggregating data that enables shippers and carriers to efficiently manage dock operations, switch out suppliers and understand material flow in real time.<p><br></p>We care deeply about delivering the best solutions for our customers. As a member of the Kargo team, you will have the opportunity to develop and deploy tomorrow's hardware &amp; software solutions and help revolutionize logistics.<p><br></p><strong>Responsibilities</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Quantitative analysis – including clustering, regression, pattern recognition, or descriptive and inferential statistics. </li><li>Communicate the results of analysis to product, engineer, and leadership teams to influence strategy. </li><li>Partner with Product, Operations and Engineering teams to solve problems and identify trends, risks and opportunities. </li><li>Provide analytics on user behaviors and market research to support more informed product decisions. </li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Minimum Requirements</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>3+ years of work experience in a data analytics role. </li><li>Proficiency in querying and manipulating complex raw datasets for analysis using SQL, Python, and/or R. </li><li>Experience with big data analytics platforms and tools such as Bigquery, Airflow, etc. </li><li>Experience creating dashboards using Tableau (or similar) visualization tools. </li><li>Ability to drive strategic discussions and convert strategy to action. Experience explaining technical concepts and analysis implications clearly to varied audiences and can translate business objectives into actionable analysis. </li><li>Degree in Data Analytics, Economics, Computer Science, Operations Research, Math, or Statistics, with a quantitative focus. </li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Nice to Have</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Advanced degree with a quantitative focus (Data Analytics, Economics, Computer Science, Operations Research, Math, Statistics). </li><li>Knowledge of logistics, warehousing, and supply chain is a plus. </li><li>Knowledge of computer vision or machine learning. </li></ul><p><br></p><em>Kargo is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer committed to an inclusive and diverse workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regards to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status or any other basis prohibited by law. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories consistent with applicable federal, state and local law.</em>

<strong>Who We're Looking For<br><br></strong>We are looking for an experienced, results oriented Business Intelligence Analyst to join our high-performing team in the global Fieldwire headquarters in San Francisco, CA, reporting to the Director of Finance and Operations in a hybrid capacity being in the office 2-3 days a week. You will take a key role within our organization to build out our financial and business reporting landscape. This role will require you to possess strong quantitative analytical skills, statistical knowledge, data visualization skills, storytelling, and the ability to build strong partnerships across the organization. Stanford University’s Center on Food Security and the Environment (FSE) addresses critical global issues of hunger, poverty and environmental degradation. Our long-term goals focus on designing new approaches to solving food security’s global challenges by building an evolving research portfolio with a team of experts in relevant scientific, economic, and policy areas. FSE is a joint effort of the Freeman Spogli Institute for International Studies and the Stanford Woods Institute for the Environment.<br><br><strong>Our VPDoR Diversity Journey<br><br></strong><ul><li> We create a hub of innovation through the power of diversity of disciplines and people.</li><li>We provide equitable access and opportunity to all members of the community in order to do their best work, regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.</li><li>We listen to and value all colleagues who bring diverse perspectives to the advancement and development of a respectful community.</li><li>We promote a culture of belonging, equity, and safety.</li><li>We embed these values in excellence of education, research, and operation.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Position Summary<br><br></strong>The Center on Food Security and the Environment (FSE) is seeking a research data analyst (RDA) to contribute to several research projects that combine new data sources and computational tools to study climate and air pollution, global poverty, and food security working with Professor Marshall Burke. The RDA will help with identifying, assembling, and geo-coding datasets on household assets, food security, health, and environmental outcomes in the developing world, and will help with analyzing satellite imagery. They will also participate in lab meetings of the Stanford Sustain Lab (sustain.stanford.edu). The goal of this work is to predict, using imagery and other non-traditional data (e.g. social media data), various measures of economic well-being in the developing world. The position will require a very organized and creative person who is capable of writing efficient code and working with large datasets. Must have exceptional mathematical and statistical modeling and computer programming skills and willingness to use them in innovative manner. Must have the ability to work comfortably and effectively within an interdisciplinary research environment. Past data analysts working in this role have earned co-authorship on top scientific publications and are now enrolled in top PhD programs. This recruitment is for a one (1) year fixed-term, 100% FTE benefits-eligible position which begins on the start date and may be renewable in the future based on funding availability. For consideration, please submit resume and cover letter. All final candidates must successfully complete a background check.<br><br><strong>Core Duties<br><br></strong><ul><li> Collect, manage and clean datasets.</li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data.</li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions.</li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation.</li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Minimum Requirements<br><br></strong><strong>Education &amp; Experience:<br><br></strong>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.<br><br><strong>Knowledge, Skills And Abilities<br><br></strong><ul><li> Experience with R, Python, and/or Google Earth Engine </li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills.</li><li>Ability to prioritize workload.</li><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*:<br><br></strong><ul><li> Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.</li><li>Occasionally use a telephone.</li><li>Rarely writing by hand.</li><li> Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of the job.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Working Conditions<br><br></strong><ul><li> Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Work Standards<br><br></strong><ul><li> Interpersonal Skills: Demonstrates the ability to work well with Stanford colleagues and clients and with external organizations.</li><li>Promote Culture of Safety: Demonstrates commitment to personal responsibility and value for safety; communicates safety concerns; uses and promotes safe behaviors based on training and lessons learned.</li><li>Subject to and expected to comply with all applicable University policies and procedures, including but not limited to the personnel policies and other policies found in the University’s Administrative Guide, http://adminguide.stanford.edu.<br><br><br></li></ul>Hybrid or on-site.<br><br>The expected pay range for this position is $64,480 to $97,000 per annum.<br><br>Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. Stanford University is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to Manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, under the direction of project researchers, investigators, or managers.<br><br>You will be working with an unparalleled leading-edge community of faculty and staff that are fundamentally changing the world of health care. You will have the opportunity to influence and drive change with your innovative ideas, the ability to make a difference and participate in human advancements. Our culture is fast-paced, energetic, and growing all the time.<br><br>We offer a variety of benefits beyond traditional medical, dental, retirement, and savings options:<br><br><ul><li> Events and program for children, sports camps, tuition options </li><li>World-class intellectual stimulation through learning and development classes, workshops, and onsite conferences from leading-edge speakers and faculty </li><li>Work/life and family-friendly policies and reimbursement </li><li>Participation in Stanford’s social responsibility and sustainable programs for a better world </li><li>A vibrant university culture that values the uniqueness of each individual <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About The Department Of Pathology<br><br></strong>Comprised of extraordinary faculty and staff, our mission is to improve the ability to diagnose, treat and understand the origin and manifestation of human disease, and to care for those who have or are at risk to develop disease. We accomplish this through our clinical services (in all fields of anatomic and clinical pathology, including molecular and genomic pathology, histocompatibility testing and transfusion medicine) and be research (which includes basic, translational and clinical research into the origins and manifestations of disease, including efforts to improve disease prediction and prevention as part of the goal of achieving precision medicine and health), and also by educating future leaders in pathology and related fields. Everything we do is to achieve the goals of providing the highest quality of clinical services to the patients for whom we passionately care, to advance our ability to understand, diagnose, monitor and ultimately to cure disease or to prevent or delay its occurrence, and to provide outstanding education and career development opportunities to those who share these goals.<br><br>For more information about the department visit http://pathology.stanford.edu/<br><br><strong>About The Lab<br><br></strong>The goal of Dr. Brooke Howitt’s lab is to better understand molecular features of tumors that better inform:<br><br><ul><li>Diagnostic classification </li><li>Identification of diagnostic, prognostic, and predictive biomarkers </li><li>Our understanding of the complex biology underlying initiation and progression of diseases, leading to improved detection, prevention, and treatment approaches </li><li>Spatial and single cell studies compatible with archival FFPE tissues <br><br><br></li></ul>We have focused on gynecologic and sarcoma entities, with ongoing projects on:<br><br><ul><li>Uterine carcinosarcoma </li><li>Uterine sarcomas and mesenchymal tumors </li><li>Endometrial carcinomas including rare variants such as mesonephric-like carcinoma <br><br><br></li></ul>To learn more about our lab please visit https://med.stanford.edu/brookehowittlab.html<br><br><strong>About The Position<br><br></strong>We are seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Lab of Dr. Brooke Howitt in the Department of Pathology. This Data Analyst will aid in many of the lab’s research activities by collecting, managing, and cleaning datasets associated with patients’ tissues, for a variety of study cohorts ranging from &lt;10 patients to over 1,000 patients. You will extract data from clinical records and work with external collaborators to extract, clean, and provide de-identified data to create databases and reports. These databases need to be regularly updated, managed, and kept readily available for data exportation for analysis. As we study a variety of rare diseases and cancers, we often participate in multi-institutional projects where you will safely track and manage patient materials inventory in accordance with IRB protocols.<br><br>The Data Analyst will play a key role in designing, building, and maintaining the analytical pipelines used for routine analysis in the lab. We welcome candidates with a growth mindset, interest in a variety of cancer and autoimmune disease research questions, and a willingness to take on challenging learning opportunities. Candidates should be knowledgeable about best practices for handling large clinical datasets, using databases, and familiar with extracting data from medical records. This position will collaborate with a variety of trainees, research staff, and department staff, as well as institutional and industry collaborators.<br><br>In addition to comparable research compensation, candidates will have the opportunity to learn and develop their C.V. or resume through research publications and presentations.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br><br></strong><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets. </li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data. </li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements. </li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions. </li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation. </li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation. </li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods. </li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff. </li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> Other duties may also be assigned<br><br><br></li></ul><em>The job duties listed are typical examples of work performed by positions in this job classification and are not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, tasks, and responsibilities. Specific duties and responsibilities may vary depending on department or program needs without changing the general nature and scope of the job or level of responsibility. Employees may also perform other duties as assigned.<br><br></em><strong>Desired Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Biology, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or Biomedical related field. </li><li>Research experience in biology, pathology or oncology desired. Experience in designing data analysis pipelines is an advantage. </li><li>Experience (or willingness to learn) managing large patient cohorts and datasets in databases and digital repositories such as REDCap and Concentriq. </li><li>Intimate knowledge with at least one of the following programming languages: Python/R/Perl/Matlab/Java/C/C++ </li><li>The candidate should be able to work independently, be highly motivated, well organized with exceptional attention to detail, adaptable and work well within a highly interdisciplinary and international team. Good communication and interpersonal skills as well as fluent English are essential, as well as proficient computer skills (Mac and PC).<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Knowledge, Skills, And Abilities (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs. </li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills. </li><li>Ability to prioritize workload. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Physical Requirements*:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity. </li><li>Occasionally use a telephone. </li><li>Rarely writing by hand. <br><br><br></li></ul><em>* - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.<br><br></em><strong><em>This role is open to candidates anywhere in the United States. The Position<br><br><strong>Who We Are<br><br></strong>Genentech, a member of the Roche group and founder of the biotechnology industry, is dedicated to pursuing groundbreaking science to discover and develop medicines for people with serious and life-threatening diseases. To solve the world's most complex health challenges, we ask bigger questions that challenge our industry and the boundaries of science to transform society. Our transformational discoveries include the first targeted antibody for cancer and the first medicine for primary progressive multiple sclerosis.<br><br>The COVID-19 pandemic has forever altered the expectations for healthcare providers, patients, and their families on how data and technology can be used to enhance the customer experience in ways not previously possible. Genentech seeks to lead the industry in this new era of omnichannel pharma and integrated customer experience.<br><br>The Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization plays a key role in installing a digital culture and mindset across the Commercial and Medical Group (CMG) as well as providing every CMG customer - be it employee, manager, healthcare provider, and patient - with the information and skills that they need next, when they need it, where they need it. LSD is in the process of transforming CMG into a continuous then contribution learning culture by pioneering advances in skills management, digital learning, experiential learning, and workflow learning.<br><br>LSD includes a team of learning business partners who have deep business acumen and are well versed in the trends and data coming from sales, marketing, and medical. They work in close collaboration with a group of Learning Design Architects who are responsible for perennial focus areas such as medical, therapeutic area certification, leadership development as well as business transformation areas which currently include omnichannel, contracting, digital, and health equity across all CMG business units. Both teams are supported by a team of instructional designers and multimedia partners who build best-in-class learning products. LSD scales these learning products through facilitators who upskill business experts and leaders in executive presence, learning technologists who use cutting edge applications and systems to embed learning as close to the work as possible, and an analytics function that maps CMG's skill domains and employee skill gain to business impact metrics.<br><br><strong>Role Overview:<br><br></strong>The Data Analyst provides the Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization and our business partners with data analytics that enable insights and business decision-making. The role will develop, implement, and maintain leading-edge data analytics, to uncover key insights, assess operational health and lead to better informed decision making and business impact. The role will identify trends and opportunities for growth through analysis of complex datasets, create best-practice reports based on data mining, analysis, and visualization. The role will evaluate internal systems for efficiency, problems, and inaccuracies, and develop and maintain protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data and utilize their technical expertise to ensure data is accurate and high quality. The Data Analyst will work directly with key stakeholders to gather requirements, provide ongoing reports and dashboards, and build relationships<br><br><strong>Key Responsibilities:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Provide thought leadership the design of new experiments and metrics that can be used to test and validate experiments for new Learning &amp; Skill Development capabilities along with new operational metrics to monitor the health of Learning Operations </li><li>Partner with Learning Business Partners to co-deliver quarterly business reviews, monthly business reviews, or experiment findings and insights to senior business stakeholders </li><li>Work with key stakeholders to identify process improvement opportunities, propose system modifications, and devise data governance strategies </li><li>Use statistical tools to identify, analyze, and interpret patterns and trends in complex data sets to assess operational health, business impact of learning solutions, forecast future skill needs, and inform business decisions </li><li>Develop dashboards, automated data feeds, and ad-hoc reporting that tracks and evaluates the progress and effectiveness of LSD programs </li><li>Facilitate and support Learning Operations and Learning Business Partners through design, development, and management of key metrics, reports, and analyzes to help measure business performance and drive key business decisions across strategies and resourcing needs </li><li>Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and create and deliver ongoing dashboards and reports to key stakeholders across the business to enable important business decisions based on key insights and trends </li><li>Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality </li><li>Demonstrate attention to detail and ensure accuracy in data analysis and recognizing anomalies or errors in data. </li><li>Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems </li><li>Work with key stakeholders to prioritize business and information needs <br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications/Experience<br><br></strong><ul><li>Minimum of 5 years proven working experience as a Data Analyst or Business Data Analyst role</li><li>Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques</li><li>Strong knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc) Experience building and improving forecasting models</li><li>Minimum of 3 years experience with reporting packages (Business Objects etc), analytical tools/databases (Python, R, SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks) and proficiency in data visualization using Qlik/Tableau is preferred</li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings</li><li>Experience with statistical modeling, analysis, and presentation of results to a non-technical audience</li><li>Strong bias for action and ability to work with minimal supervision</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills, both written and verbal<br><br></li></ul><strong>Our Operating Principles<br><br></strong><ul><li>Put Patients First: I always act as if patients I know are in the room and do what's best for them.</li><li>Follow the science: I seek answers through experiments, data and debate, and act on facts.</li><li>Act as one team: I care, collaborate and commit without boundaries, and trust others to do their part.</li><li>Embrace differences: I seek diverse perspectives, invite opposing views, and challenge myself and others.</li><li>Accelerate learning: I push to learn new things even if difficult, and openly share my successes and failures.</li><li>Simplify radically: I eliminate complexity, reuse with pride, and accomplish more with less.</li><li>Make impact now: I take accountability to do what's right, deliver value fast, and don't wait for certainty.</li><li>Think long term: I choose actions today that benefit future generations<br><br></li></ul>The expected salary range for this position based on the primary location of South San Francisco, CA is $131,900.00 - $244,900. Actual pay will be determined based on experience, qualifications, geographic location, and other job-related factors permitted by law. A discretionary annual bonus may be available based on individual and Company performance. This position also qualifies for the benefits detailed at the link provided below.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong>Relocation benefits are not available for this job posting<br><br>Genentech is an equal opportunity employer, and we embrace the increasingly diverse world around us. <strong>This is a hybrid role with the onsite location from our headquarters in Campbell, CA - candidates must be local and willing to come into the office 4 days a week.<br><br></strong><strong>About Us<br><br></strong>Acceldata is the market leader in Enterprise Data Observability. Founded in 2018, Silicon Valley-based Acceldata has developed the world's first Enterprise Data Observability Platform to help build and operate great data products.<br><br>Enterprise Data Observability is at the intersection of today’s hottest and most crucial technologies such as AI, LLMs, Analytics, and DataOps. Acceldata provides mission-critical capabilities that deliver highly trusted and reliable data to power enterprise data products.<br><br>Delivered as a SaaS product, Acceldata's solutions have been embraced by global customers, such as HPE, HSBC, Visa, Freddie Mac, Manulife, Workday, Zoominfo, GSK, Oracle, PubMatic, PhonePe (Walmart), Hersheys, Dun &amp; Bradstreet, and many more. Acceldata is a Series-C funded company and its investors include Insight Partners, March Capital, Lightspeed, Sorenson Ventures, Industry Ventures, and Emergent Ventures.<br><br>Position Summary<br><br>As a Business Intelligence Analyst at Acceldata, you will be crucial in driving data-driven decision-making across various departments within the organization. You will leverage analytic and technical skills to innovate, build, and maintain well-managed data solutions and capabilities to tackle business problems. Comfortable working with various data sources, having the ability to identify inaccuracies and root cause of data issues</li><li>Experience in building data infrastructure and implementing reporting solutions<br><br></li></ul><strong>Bonus If You Have<br><br></strong><ul><li>Comfortable working with MS Excel and MS PowerPoint</li><li>Intellectually curious, eager to learn, self-motivated, detail oriented, and able to multitask</li><li>Ability to thrive in a dynamic startup environment; you’ll have guidance when you need it, but you’re also goal oriented and can execute without close supervision<br><br></li></ul>The SF base salary target range for this full-time position is $158,000 - $193,000 + equity + benefits. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location. Within the range, individual pay is determined by work location and additional factors, including job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for your work location during the hiring process.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong><ul><li>Competitive salary, equity, benefits, and perks for all full-time employees</li><li>Employer-paid medical, dental, and vision insurance (Country specific)</li><li>Retirement employer match</li><li>$2,000 Learning &amp; Development stipend to invest in your professional development</li><li>$1,000 USD Turo host matching and $1,500 USD vehicle reimbursement program</li><li>$100 USD Monthly Turo travel credit</li><li>Cell phone, internet and Fringe benefit stipend</li><li>Paid time off to relax and recharge</li><li>Paid holidays, volunteer time off, and parental leave</li><li>For those who are in the office full-time or hybrid we have weekly in-office lunch, office snacks, and fun activities</li><li>Annual Turbo Week (week-long, company-wide conference)<br><br></li></ul>We are committed to building a diverse team. If you are from a background that's underrepresented in tech, we'd love to meet you.<br><br>Aside from an award winning work environment and the opportunity to be part of the world’s largest car sharing marketplace, we are also growing the team quickly - join us! Even if you don't meet every qualification, we are looking for people with enthusiasm for what we do and we will consider you for this and other possibilities.<br><br>Turo is an Equal Opportunity Employer and a participant in the U.S. Federal E-Verify program. Women, minorities, individuals with disabilities and protected veterans are encouraged to apply. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities and perspectives.<br><br>Turo will consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, as applicable.<br><br>We welcome candidates with physical, mental, and/or neurological disabilities. If you require assistance applying for an open position, or need accommodation during the recruiting process due to a disability, please submit a request to People Operations by emailing PeopleOps@turo.com.<br><br><strong>About Turo<br><br></strong>Turo is the world’s largest car sharing marketplace where you can book any car you want, wherever you want it, from a vibrant community of trusted hosts across the US, Canada, France, UK and Australia. A pioneer of the sharing economy and the travel industry, Turo is a safe, supportive community where the car you book is part of a story, not a fleet.<br><br>Discover Turo at https://turo.com, the App Store, and Google Play, and check out our blog, Field Notes.<br><br>Read more about the Turo culture according to Turo CEO, Andre Haddad.<br><br>

desc: Amick Brown is seeking an experienced <strong>RA/QA Data Analyst</strong> for our direct client.<p><br></p><strong>Location:</strong> Sunnyvale, CA / Hybrid<p><br></p><strong>Duration: </strong>12 Months.<p><br></p><strong>Estimated pay range:</strong> <strong>$</strong> <strong>44</strong><strong> - 55</strong> hour per client contract and candidate skills, experience and work location.<p><br></p><strong><u>Job Description</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>The RA/QA Data Analyst will be a member of the RA/QA data analytics team and use technical expertise and a solid understanding of business processes and needs to turn data into useful information. </li><li>In this role, the analyst will work closely with various business teams to understand, collect, clarify, and translate business data requirements into reports and analytics as required. </li><li>The analyst will be heavily involved with the use, distribution, and successful delivery of reports on a periodic basis. </li><li>The ideal candidate would have medical device post market experience and have the ability to explore and integrate different data sources using tools such as SQL and Tableau. </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Responsibilities</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Partner with various Quality Management System (QMS) business teams to support data needs </li><li>Translate non-technical data requirements into metrics, reports, and visualization dashboards </li><li>Partner with business teams to define and document business requirements for new metrics and reports </li><li>Ability to execute deep dives into available data sets to provide insight on product quality performance </li><li>Develop user documentation and a variety of visual representation of data analysis and ensures consistency and accuracy of data and analysis provided </li><li>Support business system integrations for data needs and report outputs </li><li>Perform ongoing monitoring and refinement of reports and analytical solutions to ensure a good user experience in support reports and dashboards </li><li>Partner with architecture and solution delivery teams to enable reports that have long-term value </li><li>Perform functional, regression, usability test, etc. as applicable for both new and existing datasets, reports and dashboards. Document and summarize test results and findings as required </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Skill/Job Requirements</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Education: Bachelor's or higher degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer and Information Science or equivalent blend of work and certification experience required </li><li>Minimum 5 years of data analytics experience, with 3+ years hands on using Tableau required </li><li>Minimum 3+ years of experience with Microsoft SQL or equivalent required </li><li>Programming skills and experience, especially for data exploration and presentation to management and other users of data required </li><li>Highly organized, self-starter and highly motivated with strong prioritization skills managing multiple projects required </li><li>Creative problem solver that is able to look at an issue from a variety of angles required </li><li>Ability to work in fast-paced teams with a great work ethic and an enthusiasm for problem solving and data analysis required </li><li>Working experience in medical device, pharmaceutical, regulatory or other related industries highly preferred </li><li>Experience and capability using visualization software such as Tableau, Power BI, and familiarity with SAP, CRM or other ERP system preferred </li><li>Knowledge of the business of medical device development and manufacture preferred </li><li>Excellent writing skills and documentation skills that enable analyses to be reliably reproduced using the same data years later preferred </li></ul><p><br></p>Amick Brown is an Information Technology consulting company specializing in ERP, Data Analytics, Information Security, Application Development, Networking, and Cloud Computing. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in San Ramon, California.<p><br></p>Regular full-time employees are eligible for the following Amick Brown provided benefits:<p><br></p><ul><li>Health </li><li>Vision </li><li>Dental </li><li>401k with company match </li><li>Paid time off </li><li>Sick Leave </li><li>Short-Term Disability </li><li>Life Insurance </li><li>Wellness &amp; Discount Programs</li></ul>

IT EDW and BI/Reporting Sys<br><br>Full Time<br><br>75099BR<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>This key position will be integral in using data to support our Education mission. In addition to these duties, the position is required to perform any other tasks assigned to support the department’s function.<br><br>A data analyst is responsible for designing, developing, testing, documenting, and maintaining business intelligence/reporting to meet UCSF’s data and analytics needs.<br><br><ul><li>Collaborate with business and technology partners to gather business requirements and create BI solutions for the UCSF Education mission.</li><li>Use business domain knowledge to profile data and determine the best approaches to analyze source systems, determine how disparate systems relate to each other, and develop BI solutions from data warehouses.</li><li>Take guidance from senior data analysts and architects in developing BI solutions.</li><li>Demonstrate expertise in SQL programming.</li><li>Develop business intelligence products, such as reports and dashboards, using Tableau or other data visualization tools.</li><li>Document business rules and metadata in the data dictionary and keep the information updated.</li><li>Possess excellent communication skills and the ability to articulate system designs and patterns to colleagues and superiors within the team.</li><li>Participate in project planning, including scoping backlogs and determining estimates.</li><li>Assume on-call duties to support the operation of reporting and analytics systems.</li><li>Maintain appropriate business domain knowledge in healthcare, education, research, finance, and business administration.<br><br></li></ul><strong>To see the salary range for this position (we recommend that you make a note of the job code and use that to look up):</strong> TCS Non-Academic Titles Search (ucop.edu)<br><br>Please note: The compensation ranges listed online for roles not covered by a bargaining unit agreement are very wide, however a job offer will typically fall in the range of 80% - 120% of the established mid-point. An offer will take into consideration the experience of the final candidate AND the current salary level of individuals working at UCSF in a similar role.<br><br>For roles covered by a bargaining unit agreement, there will be specific rules about where a new hire would be placed on the range.<br><br>To learn more about the benefits of working at UCSF, including total compensation, please visit: https://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/compensation-and-benefits/index.html<br><br><strong>Department Description<br><br></strong><strong>UCSF:</strong> As a preeminent health sciences campus and health system, the University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) is at the forefront of creating new knowledge from the exploding volume of clinical, discovery, and education data that it creates and manages. These strategies include supporting better population health by improving the quality of care and population health of the University of California health system’s 14 million patients. As part of this exciting and important endeavor, UCSF is seeking a highly qualified Data Warehouse Supervisor.<br><br><strong>Information Technology Services:</strong> This position will reside within the Enterprise Information and Analytics team, and work in close alignment with IT Education to develop an overall education data strategy and data warehouse to support the education mission at UCSF.<br><br><strong>Enterprise Information and Analytics:</strong> EIA’s vision is advancing UCSF’s ability to care, heal, teach, and discover by providing ubiquitous access to relevant and high-quality information and analytics. Led by the Associate CIO for Education, this unit is charged with developing collaborative relationships, processes, and services that appropriately enable the education community to execute its mission, while keeping UCSF’s IT environment secure and sufficiently cost-effective. With a focus on diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility, this IT Education team is actively working to establish a computing architecture and services to support digital equity and digital transformation to support and advance the UCSF education mission.<br><br><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in a related area and/or equivalent experience/training.</li><li>Experienced in enterprise data warehousing development. Demonstrate ability to communicate technical information to technical and non-technical personnel at various levels in the organization.</li><li>Self-motivated and works independently and as part of a team. Able to learn effectively and meet deadlines.</li><li>Demonstrate complex problem-solving skills.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Understanding of advanced statistical analytics, machine learning, and data science principles.</li><li>Experience with cloud computing and technologies.</li><li>Experience in an Agile working environment is desired.</li><li>Experience in one programming language such as Python, R, Java, C++, C+, etc.</li><li>Experience with secure software development</li><li>Experienced with software specification, design, modification, implementation, and deployment of large-scale scope.</li><li>Able to resolve and improve performance issues. It is the only campus in the 10-campus UC system dedicated exclusively to the health sciences. We bring together the world’s leading experts in nearly every area of health. We are home to five Nobel laureates who have advanced the understanding of cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, aging and stem cells.<br><br><strong>Pride Values<br><br></strong>UCSF is a diverse community made of people with many skills and talents. We seek candidates whose work experience or community service has prepared them to contribute to our commitment to professionalism, respect, integrity, diversity and excellence – also known as our PRIDE values.<br><br>In addition to our PRIDE values, UCSF is committed to equity – both in how we deliver care as well as our workforce. Stanford University is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to Manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, under the direction of project researchers, investigators, or managers.<br><br>You will be working with an unparalleled leading-edge community of faculty and staff that are fundamentally changing the world of health care. You will have the opportunity to influence and drive change with your innovative ideas, the ability to make a difference and participate in human advancements. Our culture is fast-paced, energetic, and growing all the time.<br><br>We offer a variety of benefits beyond traditional medical, dental, retirement, and savings options:<br><br><ul><li>Events and program for children, sports camps, tuition options</li><li>World-class intellectual stimulation through learning and development classes, workshops, and onsite conferences from leading-edge speakers and faculty</li><li>Work/life and family-friendly policies and reimbursement</li><li>Participation in Stanford’s social responsibility and sustainable programs for a better world</li><li>A vibrant university culture that values the uniqueness of each individual<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About The Department Of Pathology<br><br></strong>Comprised of extraordinary faculty and staff, our mission is to improve the ability to diagnose, treat and understand the origin and manifestation of human disease, and to care for those who have or are at risk to develop disease. We accomplish this through our clinical services (in all fields of anatomic and clinical pathology, including molecular and genomic pathology, histocompatibility testing and transfusion medicine) and be research (which includes basic, translational and clinical research into the origins and manifestations of disease, including efforts to improve disease prediction and prevention as part of the goal of achieving precision medicine and health), and also by educating future leaders in pathology and related fields. Everything we do is to achieve the goals of providing the highest quality of clinical services to the patients for whom we passionately care, to advance our ability to understand, diagnose, monitor and ultimately to cure disease or to prevent or delay its occurrence, and to provide outstanding education and career development opportunities to those who share these goals.<br><br>For more information about the department visit http://pathology.stanford.edu/<br><br><strong>About The Lab<br><br></strong>The goal of Dr. Brooke Howitt’s lab is to better understand molecular features of tumors that better inform:<br><br><ul><li>Diagnostic classification</li><li>Identification of diagnostic, prognostic, and predictive biomarkers</li><li>Our understanding of the complex biology underlying initiation and progression of diseases, leading to improved detection, prevention, and treatment approaches</li><li>Spatial and single cell studies compatible with archival FFPE tissues<br><br><br></li></ul>We have focused on gynecologic and sarcoma entities, with ongoing projects on:<br><br><ul><li>Uterine carcinosarcoma</li><li>Uterine sarcomas and mesenchymal tumors</li><li>Endometrial carcinomas including rare variants such as mesonephric-like carcinoma<br><br><br></li></ul>To learn more about our lab please visit https://med.stanford.edu/brookehowittlab.html<br><br><strong>About The Position<br><br></strong>We are seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Lab of Dr. Brooke Howitt in the Department of Pathology. This Data Analyst will aid in many of the lab’s research activities by collecting, managing, and cleaning datasets associated with patients’ tissues, for a variety of study cohorts ranging from &lt;10 patients to over 1,000 patients. You will extract data from clinical records and work with external collaborators to extract, clean, and provide de-identified data to create databases and reports. These databases need to be regularly updated, managed, and kept readily available for data exportation for analysis. As we study a variety of rare diseases and cancers, we often participate in multi-institutional projects where you will safely track and manage patient materials inventory in accordance with IRB protocols.<br><br>The Data Analyst will play a key role in designing, building, and maintaining the analytical pipelines used for routine analysis in the lab. We welcome candidates with a growth mindset, interest in a variety of cancer and autoimmune disease research questions, and a willingness to take on challenging learning opportunities. Candidates should be knowledgeable about best practices for handling large clinical datasets, using databases, and familiar with extracting data from medical records. This position will collaborate with a variety of trainees, research staff, and department staff, as well as institutional and industry collaborators.<br><br>In addition to comparable research compensation, candidates will have the opportunity to learn and develop their C.V. or resume through research publications and presentations.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br><br></strong><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets.</li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data.</li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions.</li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation.</li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> Other duties may also be assigned<br><br><br></li></ul>The job duties listed are typical examples of work performed by positions in this job classification and are not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, tasks, and responsibilities. Specific duties and responsibilities may vary depending on department or program needs without changing the general nature and scope of the job or level of responsibility. Employees may also perform other duties as assigned.<br><br><strong>Desired Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Biology, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or Biomedical related field. </li><li>Research experience in biology, pathology or oncology desired. Experience in designing data analysis pipelines is an advantage.</li><li>Experience (or willingness to learn) managing large patient cohorts and datasets in databases and digital repositories such as REDCap and Concentriq.</li><li>Intimate knowledge with at least one of the following programming languages: Python/R/Perl/Matlab/Java/C/C++ </li><li>The candidate should be able to work independently, be highly motivated, well organized with exceptional attention to detail, adaptable and work well within a highly interdisciplinary and international team. Good communication and interpersonal skills as well as fluent English are essential, as well as proficient computer skills (Mac and PC).<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience.
