job_title: Data Analyst, Risk Data Mining - USDS
desc: <strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong> TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo. <br><br>Why Join Us<br>Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. <br>Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day. <br>To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always. <br>At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve. <br>Join us.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone department of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security & Privacy, Engineering, User & Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>The USDS-Platform and Community Integrity (PaCI) team is missioned to: - Protect U.S. TikTok users, including and beyond content consumers, creators, and advertisers; - Secure platform health and community experience authenticity; - Build infrastructures, platforms, and technologies, as well as to collaborate with many cross-functional teams and stakeholders. The PaCI team works to minimize the damage of inauthentic behaviors on TikTok platforms, covering multiple classical and novel community and business risk areas such as account integrity, engagement authenticity, anti-spam, API abuse, growth fraud, live streaming security and financial safety, etc. In this team, you'll have a unique opportunity to have first-hand exposure to the strategy of the company in key security initiatives, especially in building scalable and robust, intelligent and privacy-safe, secure, and product-friendly systems and solutions. Our challenges are not some regular day-to-day technical puzzles -- You'll be part of a team that's developing novel solutions to first-seen challenges of a non-stop evolution of a phenomenal product eco-system. The work needs to be fast, transferrable, while still down to the ground to make quick and solid differences.<br><br>In order to enhance collaboration and cross-functional partnerships, among other things, at this time, our organization follows a hybrid work schedule that requires employees to work in the office 3 days a week, or as directed by their manager/department. We regularly review our hybrid work model, and the specific requirements may change at any time.<br><br>Responsibilities <br>Build rules to recognize, mitigate or prevent risky inauthentic behaviors on TikTok and its extended platforms. Such risks include and are not limited to abusive accounts, fake engagements, spammy redirection, scraping, fraud, etc.<br>Analyze business, product and security data, uncover evolving attack motion, identify weaknesses and opportunities in risk defense solutions, explore new space from the discoveries.<br>Quantify risk control effects and trends, collaborate with engineering, modeling, operational and product colleagues, contribute to risk measurement, perception, mitigation and prevention with data stories. <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> Qualifications<br>Bachelor or degrees above in computer science, statistics, math, internet security or other relevant majors (e.g., finance if applying for financial fraud roles)<br>Solid analytical skills. Proficiency in statistical analytical tools, such as SQL and Python.<br>Familiarity with social/content online platform analytics. Bonus given to proficiency in data mining skills e.g. modern machine applications.<br>Ability to think critically, objectively, rationally. Reason and communicate in result-oriented, data-driven manner. High autonomy.<br><br>TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.<br><br>TikTok is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation, please reach out to us at usds.accommodations@tiktokusds.com. <br><br><strong>Job Information:<br><br></strong>【For Pay Transparency】Compensation Description (annually) <p>The base salary range for this position in the selected city is $86555 - $177777 annually.<span></span></p><p>Compensation may vary outside of this range depending on a number of factors, including a candidate’s qualifications, skills, competencies and experience, and location. Base pay is one part of the Total Package that is provided to compensate and recognize employees for their work, and this role may be eligible for additional discretionary bonuses/incentives, and restricted stock units.<span></span></p><p>Our company benefits are designed to convey company culture and values, to create an efficient and inspiring work environment, and to support our employees to give their best in both work and life. We offer the following benefits to eligible employees: <span></span></p><p>We cover 100% premium coverage for employee medical insurance, approximately 75% premium coverage for dependents and offer a Health Savings Account(HSA) with a company match. As well as Dental, Vision, Short/Long term Disability, Basic Life, Voluntary Life and AD&amp;D insurance plans. In addition to Flexible Spending Account(FSA) Options like Health Care, Limited Purpose and Dependent Care. <span></span></p><p>Our time off and leave plans are: 10 paid holidays per year plus 17 days of Paid Personal Time Off (PPTO) (prorated upon hire and increased by tenure) and 10 paid sick days per year as well as 12 weeks of paid Parental leave and 8 weeks of paid Supplemental Disability. <span></span></p><p>We also provide generous benefits like mental and emotional health benefits through our EAP and Lyra. A 401K company match, gym and cellphone service reimbursements. The Company reserves the right to modify or change these benefits programs at any time, with or without notice.<span></span></p>

Stanford University’s Center on Food Security and the Environment (FSE) addresses critical global issues of hunger, poverty and environmental degradation. Our long-term goals focus on designing new approaches to solving food security’s global challenges by building an evolving research portfolio with a team of experts in relevant scientific, economic, and policy areas. FSE is a joint effort of the Freeman Spogli Institute for International Studies and the Stanford Woods Institute for the Environment.<br><br><strong>Our VPDoR Diversity Journey<br><br></strong><ul><li> We create a hub of innovation through the power of diversity of disciplines and people.</li><li>We provide equitable access and opportunity to all members of the community in order to do their best work, regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.</li><li>We listen to and value all colleagues who bring diverse perspectives to the advancement and development of a respectful community.</li><li>We promote a culture of belonging, equity, and safety.</li><li>We embed these values in excellence of education, research, and operation.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Position Summary<br><br></strong>The Center on Food Security and the Environment (FSE) is seeking a research data analyst (RDA) to contribute to several research projects that combine new data sources and computational tools to study climate and air pollution, global poverty, and food security working with Professor Marshall Burke. The RDA will help with identifying, assembling, and geo-coding datasets on household assets, food security, health, and environmental outcomes in the developing world, and will help with analyzing satellite imagery. They will also participate in lab meetings of the Stanford Sustain Lab (sustain.stanford.edu). The goal of this work is to predict, using imagery and other non-traditional data (e.g. social media data), various measures of economic well-being in the developing world. The position will require a very organized and creative person who is capable of writing efficient code and working with large datasets. Must have exceptional mathematical and statistical modeling and computer programming skills and willingness to use them in innovative manner. Must have the ability to work comfortably and effectively within an interdisciplinary research environment. Past data analysts working in this role have earned co-authorship on top scientific publications and are now enrolled in top PhD programs. This recruitment is for a one (1) year fixed-term, 100% FTE benefits-eligible position which begins on the start date and may be renewable in the future based on funding availability. For consideration, please submit resume and cover letter. All final candidates must successfully complete a background check.<br><br><strong>Core Duties<br><br></strong><ul><li> Collect, manage and clean datasets.</li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data.</li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions.</li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation.</li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Minimum Requirements<br><br></strong><strong>Education &amp; Experience:<br><br></strong>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.<br><br><strong>Knowledge, Skills And Abilities<br><br></strong><ul><li> Experience with R, Python, and/or Google Earth Engine </li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills.</li><li>Ability to prioritize workload.</li><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*:<br><br></strong><ul><li> Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.</li><li>Occasionally use a telephone.</li><li>Rarely writing by hand.</li><li> Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of the job.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Working Conditions<br><br></strong><ul><li> Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Work Standards<br><br></strong><ul><li> Interpersonal Skills: Demonstrates the ability to work well with Stanford colleagues and clients and with external organizations.</li><li>Promote Culture of Safety: Demonstrates commitment to personal responsibility and value for safety; communicates safety concerns; uses and promotes safe behaviors based on training and lessons learned.</li><li>Subject to and expected to comply with all applicable University policies and procedures, including but not limited to the personnel policies and other policies found in the University’s Administrative Guide, http://adminguide.stanford.edu.<br><br><br></li></ul>Hybrid or on-site.<br><br>The expected pay range for this position is $64,480 to $97,000 per annum.<br><br>Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. The pay offered to a selected candidate will be determined based on factors such as (but not limited to) the scope and responsibilities of the position, the qualifications of the selected candidate, departmental budget availability, internal equity, geographic location and external market pay for comparable jobs.<br><br>At Stanford University, base pay represents only one aspect of the comprehensive rewards package. The Cardinal at Work website (https://cardinalatwork.stanford.edu/benefits-rewards) provides detailed information on Stanford’s extensive range of benefits and rewards offered to employees. Specifics about the rewards package for this position may be discussed during the hiring process.<br><br><strong>Why Stanford is for You <br><br></strong>Imagine a World Without Search Engines Or Social Platforms. Consider Lives Saved Through First-ever Organ Transplants And Research To Cure Illnesses. Stanford University Has Revolutionized The Way We Live And Enrich The World. Supporting This Mission Is Our Diverse And Dedicated 17,000 Staff. We Seek Talent Driven To Impact The Future Of Our Legacy. Our Culture And Unique Perks Empower You With<br><br><ul><li> Freedom to grow. We offer career development programs, tuition reimbursement, or audit a course. Join a TedTalk, film screening, or listen to a renowned author or global leader speak.</li><li>A caring culture. We provide superb retirement plans, generous time-off, and family care resources.</li><li>A healthier you. Climb our rock wall, or choose from hundreds of health or fitness classes at our world-class exercise facilities. We also provide excellent health care benefits.</li><li>Discovery and fun. Stroll through historic sculptures, trails, and museums.</li><li>Enviable resources. Enjoy free commuter programs, ridesharing incentives, discounts and more!<br><br><br></li></ul>The job duties listed are typical examples of work performed by positions in this job classification and are not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, tasks, and responsibilities. <strong>About The Role<br><br></strong>At Uber, People Data and Analytics (PDnA) exists to empower leaders and HR partners to make higher quality decisions, in less time, using the best available data. We deliver actionable insights across all aspects of the talent lifecycle - recruiting, selection, onboarding, development, engagement, and retention - to build positive people and business outcomes.<br><br>This role will be responsible for developing and optimizing employee data processes as well as working closely with key partners to support data management, analysis and reporting. The team will be looking to you as a consultant on all things employee data with an ownership mentality, creative mind and constantly looking for internal and external solutions to improve our program.<br><br>This person will report into our Director of People Data Management in our office based in San Francisco, CA.<br><br><strong>What You'll Do<br><br></strong><ul><li> Own the data management workstream with a focus on data integrity, analysis and reporting. </li><li> Establish data change management and audit processes and policies to ensure the integrity of people data as well as the security of sensitive people data. </li><li> Diagnose operational breakdowns at the root cause and work with key stakeholders to find efficient and holistic solutions. </li><li> Proactively identify and troubleshoot data issues </li><li> Produce Ad-hoc reporting </li><li> Understanding and ensuring high quality of the source data used in core metrics <br><br></li></ul><strong> <strong>Basic Qualifications</strong> <br><br></strong><ul><li> Bachelor degree required </li><li> 3+ years of demonstrated experience </li><li> Advanced skills in data querying, data analysis and data visualization <br><br></li></ul><strong> <strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong> <br><br></strong><ul><li> Fluent in SQL, Tableau experience is a plus </li><li> Experience in solving problems by deep diving into technical landscape, both structured and ambiguous, with strong attention to detail </li><li> Analytical Skills - translate data and insights into a meaningful story to drive strategy, action, and decision-making. </li><li> Communication - excellent at communicating information to audiences of all levels in a clear and concise manner </li><li> Organization &amp; Execution - able to balance multiple work streams concurrently for yourself and others; able to scope and execute a project from start to finish </li><li> Teamwork - Collaborates and makes compromises when necessary in order to help broader org achieve goals</li></ul>

The Summer Internship<br><br>At Discord, we offer a personalized experience for interns, and our aim is to offer an experience that mimics what it is like to actually work here. Conditions permitting, our 2024 summer internships will be remote, with an opportunity to spend a week in the office at some point during the program.<br><br><strong>The Team:<br><br></strong>The Data Engineering team at Discord collaborates with data science and engineering teams to design, build, and scale high-leverage datasets that enable analytics, modeling, and experimentation. detection as necessary</li><li>Support critical data processes running in production<br><br></li></ul><strong>You'll Succeed In This Role If...<br><br></strong><ul><li>In the process of obtaining a database systems and data modeling</li><li>Knowledge of modern data storage and processing technologies (i.e. GCP BigQuery, Airflow, and DBT or similar)</li><li>Strong communication skills to collaborate with individuals and teams<br><br></li></ul><strong>Salary of $63/hour (Undergrad), 69/hour (Master's) and $78/hour (PhD)*<br><br></strong><strong>Note: Disclosure as required by NYC Pay Transparency Law and CO Disclosure as required by sb19-085(8-5-20)<br><br></strong><strong>Benefits listed below may differ from those available depending on terms of employment*<br><br></strong>Benefits and Perks<br><br><ul><li>Comprehensive medical insurance including Health, Dental and Vision (plus up to $20,000 for gender affirmation procedures)</li><li>Mental health resources and quarterly wellness stipends</li><li>14+ paid holidays, 4 weeks of PTO + use-what-you-need sick days </li><li>Paid parental leave (plus fertility, adoption and other family planning benefits)</li><li>Flexible long-term work options (remote and hybrid)</li><li>Volunteer time off</li><li>A diverse slate of Employee Resource Groups </li><li>Plus commuter contributions and other perks for office-based employees<br><br></li></ul><strong>About Us<br><br></strong>Discord is a voice, video and text app that helps friends and communities come together to hang out and explore their interests — from artists and activists, to study groups, sneakerheads, plant parents, and more. Discord was built without selling ads or user data and instead, offers a premium subscription called Nitro that gives users special perks like higher quality streams and fun customizations.<br><br>We’re working toward an inclusive world where no one feels like an outsider, where genuine human connection is a click, text chat, or voice call away. A place where everyone can find belonging. Challenging? Heck yes. Rewarding? Double heck yes. It’s a mission that gives us the chance to positively impact millions of people all over the world. <strong>So if this strikes a chord with you, come build belonging with us!<br><br></strong>

Stanford University is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to Manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, under the direction of project researchers, investigators, or managers.<br><br>You will be working with an unparalleled leading-edge community of faculty and staff that are fundamentally changing the world of health care. You will have the opportunity to influence and drive change with your innovative ideas, the ability to make a difference and participate in human advancements. Our culture is fast-paced, energetic, and growing all the time.<br><br>We offer a variety of benefits beyond traditional medical, dental, retirement, and savings options:<br><br><ul><li> Events and program for children, sports camps, tuition options </li><li>World-class intellectual stimulation through learning and development classes, workshops, and onsite conferences from leading-edge speakers and faculty </li><li>Work/life and family-friendly policies and reimbursement </li><li>Participation in Stanford’s social responsibility and sustainable programs for a better world </li><li>A vibrant university culture that values the uniqueness of each individual <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About The Department Of Pathology<br><br></strong>Comprised of extraordinary faculty and staff, our mission is to improve the ability to diagnose, treat and understand the origin and manifestation of human disease, and to care for those who have or are at risk to develop disease. We accomplish this through our clinical services (in all fields of anatomic and clinical pathology, including molecular and genomic pathology, histocompatibility testing and transfusion medicine) and be research (which includes basic, translational and clinical research into the origins and manifestations of disease, including efforts to improve disease prediction and prevention as part of the goal of achieving precision medicine and health), and also by educating future leaders in pathology and related fields. Everything we do is to achieve the goals of providing the highest quality of clinical services to the patients for whom we passionately care, to advance our ability to understand, diagnose, monitor and ultimately to cure disease or to prevent or delay its occurrence, and to provide outstanding education and career development opportunities to those who share these goals.<br><br>For more information about the department visit http://pathology.stanford.edu/<br><br><strong>About The Lab<br><br></strong>The goal of Dr. Brooke Howitt’s lab is to better understand molecular features of tumors that better inform:<br><br><ul><li>Diagnostic classification </li><li>Identification of diagnostic, prognostic, and predictive biomarkers </li><li>Our understanding of the complex biology underlying initiation and progression of diseases, leading to improved detection, prevention, and treatment approaches </li><li>Spatial and single cell studies compatible with archival FFPE tissues <br><br><br></li></ul>We have focused on gynecologic and sarcoma entities, with ongoing projects on:<br><br><ul><li>Uterine carcinosarcoma </li><li>Uterine sarcomas and mesenchymal tumors </li><li>Endometrial carcinomas including rare variants such as mesonephric-like carcinoma <br><br><br></li></ul>To learn more about our lab please visit https://med.stanford.edu/brookehowittlab.html<br><br><strong>About The Position<br><br></strong>We are seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Lab of Dr. Brooke Howitt in the Department of Pathology. This Data Analyst will aid in many of the lab’s research activities by collecting, managing, and cleaning datasets associated with patients’ tissues, for a variety of study cohorts ranging from &lt;10 patients to over 1,000 patients. You will extract data from clinical records and work with external collaborators to extract, clean, and provide de-identified data to create databases and reports. These databases need to be regularly updated, managed, and kept readily available for data exportation for analysis. As we study a variety of rare diseases and cancers, we often participate in multi-institutional projects where you will safely track and manage patient materials inventory in accordance with IRB protocols.<br><br>The Data Analyst will play a key role in designing, building, and maintaining the analytical pipelines used for routine analysis in the lab. We welcome candidates with a growth mindset, interest in a variety of cancer and autoimmune disease research questions, and a willingness to take on challenging learning opportunities. Candidates should be knowledgeable about best practices for handling large clinical datasets, using databases, and familiar with extracting data from medical records. This position will collaborate with a variety of trainees, research staff, and department staff, as well as institutional and industry collaborators.<br><br>In addition to comparable research compensation, candidates will have the opportunity to learn and develop their C.V. or resume through research publications and presentations.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br><br></strong><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets. </li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data. </li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements. </li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions. </li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation. </li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation. </li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods. </li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff. </li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> Other duties may also be assigned<br><br><br></li></ul><em>The job duties listed are typical examples of work performed by positions in this job classification and are not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, tasks, and responsibilities. Specific duties and responsibilities may vary depending on department or program needs without changing the general nature and scope of the job or level of responsibility. Employees may also perform other duties as assigned.<br><br></em><strong>Desired Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Biology, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or Biomedical related field. </li><li>Research experience in biology, pathology or oncology desired. Experience in designing data analysis pipelines is an advantage. </li><li>Experience (or willingness to learn) managing large patient cohorts and datasets in databases and digital repositories such as REDCap and Concentriq. </li><li>Intimate knowledge with at least one of the following programming languages: Python/R/Perl/Matlab/Java/C/C++ </li><li>The candidate should be able to work independently, be highly motivated, well organized with exceptional attention to detail, adaptable and work well within a highly interdisciplinary and international team. Good communication and interpersonal skills as well as fluent English are essential, as well as proficient computer skills (Mac and PC).<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Knowledge, Skills, And Abilities (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs. </li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills. </li><li>Ability to prioritize workload. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Physical Requirements*:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity. </li><li>Occasionally use a telephone. </li><li>Rarely writing by hand. <br><br><br></li></ul><em>* - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.<br><br></em><strong><em>This role is open to candidates anywhere in the United States. Stanford University has </em></strong><strong><em>five Regional Pay Structures</em></strong><strong><em>. The compensation for this position will be based on the location of the successful candidate. The expected pay range for this position is $64,480 to $97,000 per annum/hour. <br><br></em></strong><strong><em>Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. The pay offered to a selected candidate will be determined based on factors such as (but not limited to) the scope and responsibilities of the position, the qualifications of the selected candidate, departmental budget availability, internal equity, geographic location, and external market pay for comparable jobs. <br><br></em></strong><strong><em>At Stanford University, base pay represents only one aspect of the comprehensive rewards package. The Cardinal at Work website (</em></strong><strong><em>https://cardinalatwork.stanford.edu/benefits-rewards</em></strong><strong><em>) provides detailed information on Stanford’s extensive range of benefits and rewards offered to employees. Specifics about the rewards package for this position may be discussed during the hiring process.<br><br></em></strong><em>Stanford is an equal employment opportunity and affirmative action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.</em>

<p>Our client, a fortune 500 software company that creates financial services platforms for businesses and consumers is hiring a Businesss Intelligence Analyst to join their payment solutions team located in Mountain View, CA.</p><p><br></p><p>This team is building predictive data models that help assess risk that will be used to help better manage the internal workforce. As a Business Intelligence Analyst you will constantly explore ways to improve and automate manual processes using data, machine learning, and analytics. </p><p><br></p><p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Lead automation of job scheduling and migrate legacy dashboards onto advanced analytical tools or better-automated approaches to reduce manual work. </li><li>Develop anomaly detection alerts for risk operations related metrics. </li><li>Optimize the performance of scripts, reports, and models. </li><li>Work with engineers to develop, test, debug and maintain accurate tracking, capturing, and reporting of risk operations metrics via server-side data collection and other database sources.</li><li>Document approaches, automation and debug steps, and scripts used in all the work</li><li>Communicate and present models, findings, and automation projects with both technical and non-technical audiences, use data and simple language to tell a good story.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Bachelors Degree in related field</li><li>3+ years of Advanced SQL &amp; Python</li><li>Strong ETL and data extraction experience </li><li>Comfortable writing complex SQL queries that combine data from various tables</li><li>Experience using Python for data cleaning, analytics, and predictive modeling</li><li>Highly proficient in building effective data visualizations using Tableau and Databricks</li></ul>

The Position<br><br><strong>Who We Are<br><br></strong>Genentech, a member of the Roche group and founder of the biotechnology industry, is dedicated to pursuing groundbreaking science to discover and develop medicines for people with serious and life-threatening diseases. To solve the world's most complex health challenges, we ask bigger questions that challenge our industry and the boundaries of science to transform society. Our transformational discoveries include the first targeted antibody for cancer and the first medicine for primary progressive multiple sclerosis.<br><br>The COVID-19 pandemic has forever altered the expectations for healthcare providers, patients, and their families on how data and technology can be used to enhance the customer experience in ways not previously possible. Genentech seeks to lead the industry in this new era of omnichannel pharma and integrated customer experience.<br><br>The Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization plays a key role in installing a digital culture and mindset across the Commercial and Medical Group (CMG) as well as providing every CMG customer - be it employee, manager, healthcare provider, and patient - with the information and skills that they need next, when they need it, where they need it. LSD is in the process of transforming CMG into a continuous then contribution learning culture by pioneering advances in skills management, digital learning, experiential learning, and workflow learning.<br><br>LSD includes a team of learning business partners who have deep business acumen and are well versed in the trends and data coming from sales, marketing, and medical. They work in close collaboration with a group of Learning Design Architects who are responsible for perennial focus areas such as medical, therapeutic area certification, leadership development as well as business transformation areas which currently include omnichannel, contracting, digital, and health equity across all CMG business units. Both teams are supported by a team of instructional designers and multimedia partners who build best-in-class learning products. LSD scales these learning products through facilitators who upskill business experts and leaders in executive presence, learning technologists who use cutting edge applications and systems to embed learning as close to the work as possible, and an analytics function that maps CMG's skill domains and employee skill gain to business impact metrics.<br><br><strong>Role Overview:<br><br></strong>The Data Analyst provides the Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization and our business partners with data analytics that enable insights and business decision-making. The role will develop, implement, and maintain leading-edge data analytics, to uncover key insights, assess operational health and lead to better informed decision making and business impact. The role will identify trends and opportunities for growth through analysis of complex datasets, create best-practice reports based on data mining, analysis, and visualization. The role will evaluate internal systems for efficiency, problems, and inaccuracies, and develop and maintain protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data and utilize their technical expertise to ensure data is accurate and high quality. The Data Analyst will work directly with key stakeholders to gather requirements, provide ongoing reports and dashboards, and build relationships<br><br><strong>Key Responsibilities:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Provide thought leadership the design of new experiments and metrics that can be used to test and validate experiments for new Learning &amp; Skill Development capabilities along with new operational metrics to monitor the health of Learning Operations </li><li>Partner with Learning Business Partners to co-deliver quarterly business reviews, monthly business reviews, or experiment findings and insights to senior business stakeholders </li><li>Work with key stakeholders to identify process improvement opportunities, propose system modifications, and devise data governance strategies </li><li>Use statistical tools to identify, analyze, and interpret patterns and trends in complex data sets to assess operational health, business impact of learning solutions, forecast future skill needs, and inform business decisions </li><li>Develop dashboards, automated data feeds, and ad-hoc reporting that tracks and evaluates the progress and effectiveness of LSD programs </li><li>Facilitate and support Learning Operations and Learning Business Partners through design, development, and management of key metrics, reports, and analyzes to help measure business performance and drive key business decisions across strategies and resourcing needs </li><li>Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and create and deliver ongoing dashboards and reports to key stakeholders across the business to enable important business decisions based on key insights and trends </li><li>Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality </li><li>Demonstrate attention to detail and ensure accuracy in data analysis and recognizing <strong>About Watershed<br><br></strong>Watershed is a software platform for running a world-class climate program. We measure our success in the carbon reduction achievements of our customers. We are looking for team members who love product-building, want to work hard at a mission-oriented startup, and will collaborate with us in shaping the culture of a growing team.<br><br>We have offices in San Francisco, New York and London and remote team members across the US and Europe. We hope that you'll be interested in joining us!<br><br>The role<br><br>Accurately measuring carbon emissions is the first step to decarbonize the economy. Watershed is compiling an exhaustive carbon emissions dataset, powered by the latest climate science, and engineering a best-in-class calculation software to empower our customers to reduce emissions. And, we are building a team of Carbon Data Analysts to implement the end-to-end measurement experience for our customers. Measurement is both the first step in a customer’s climate journey and their first experience with Watershed, making this the foundation of not only a company’s climate program, but also their relationship with Watershed.<br><br>We’re looking for individuals to own measurements for some of the world’s leading corporate climate programs. You'll work directly with our customers to develop measurement strategies with industry leading companies, collect and transform their raw business activity data into final carbon numbers, and ensure they understand the methodology and processes that got them there.<br><br>As part of this work, you will:<br><br><ul><li>Work directly with customers to help them build a measurement strategy and identify the correct raw data (on everything from electricity consumption to cheese purchases to Bitcoin transactions) to measure their footprint. </li><li>Help customers ingest and transform unstructured data sets so that they're ready for processing in our automated carbon data pipelines. </li><li>Use our tooling to calculate, test, and publish finalized carbon footprint assessments. </li><li>Explain the technical details of carbon accounting, emissions measurement methodology and how it applies to an individual customer’s business operations. <br><br></li></ul>You might be a fit if you:<br><br><ul><li>Have 2+ years experience in a consulting, solutions-engineering, and/or customer-facing role. You are excited to work directly with customers to help them take the first step in setting up world-class climate programs</li><li>Are an excellent verbal and written communicator. You can communicate complex topics to technical and non-technical audiences. </li><li>Are organized, systematic, and efficient. You thrive in a high-volume environment. </li><li>Are meticulous and detail-obsessed. You won't rest until you get the numbers right. </li><li>Are willing to roll up your sleeves to work with unstructured and inconsistent data. You have good intuition for how numbers in a table map to the real world. </li><li>Are passionate about solving climate change and excited to contribute to doing so at a fast paced startup. You learn quickly and operate well in ambiguity. <br><br></li></ul>FAQ<br><br><strong>Where does Watershed work?<br><br></strong>We have hub offices in San Francisco, New York and London, and some remote team members in the US and EU. Most of our jobs need to be in San Francisco / New York / London, but certain jobs are open to being remote and will be specifically noted on the jobs page and in the job description.<br><br><strong>What’s the interview process like?<br><br></strong>It starts the same for every candidate: getting to know the team members through 1 to 2 conversations about Watershed, your experience, and your interests. Next steps can vary by role, but usual next steps are a skill or experience screen (e.g. a coding interview for an engineer, a portfolio review for a designer, deeper experience call for other roles) which leads to a virtual or in person interview panel after that if the screens go well. We prioritize transparency and lack of surprise throughout the process.

The ideal person for this role possesses strong financial and analytics experience, is a demonstrated self-starter that is comfortable with ambiguity and operates with an ownership mindset, possess excellent communication skills, and has the ability to get up to speed quickly on different topics and areas.<br><br><strong>What You’ll Do<br><br></strong><ul><li>Develop a keen understanding of our business and build expertises within the risk domain</li><li>Identify areas of opportunity for the business through rigorous data analysis, develop implementation plans with stakeholders, and help to quantify ROI of initiatives </li><li>Design and build dashboards to monitor performance metrics; helps to maintain analytics pipelines to ensure highest levels of accuracy in reporting</li><li>Communicate metrics/KPIs to to business leaders, explaining the business reasons for changes in business trends</li><li>Partner with finance, accounting, product, and operations teams to design, lead, and optimize data &amp; reporting processes</li><li>Work with accounting to assist with monthly close and audit procedures</li><li>Build scalable solutions that facilitate data consumption by different stakeholders</li><li>Take full ownership of internal financial reporting processes<br><br></li></ul><strong>Your Profile<br><br></strong><ul><li>3-5 years of using analytics to drive strategic business decisions; examples include FP&amp;A/product analytics, business intelligence, or strategy consulting; experience in consumer tech, marketplaces or e-commerce a strong plus</li><li>Top notch quantitative skills; strong proficiency in conducting detailed data analysis and using metrics to drive business results</li><li>Extensive experience with SQL required; additional experience with BI &amp; visualization tools is a strong plus (i.e. DOMO, Looker, Tableau)</li><li>Experience transforming data into presentations that “tell the story” behind the data</li><li>Very strong attention to detail. Comfortable working with various data sources, having the ability to identify inaccuracies and root cause of data issues</li><li>Experience in building data infrastructure and implementing reporting solutions<br><br></li></ul><strong>Bonus If You Have<br><br></strong><ul><li>Comfortable working with MS Excel and MS PowerPoint</li><li>Intellectually curious, eager to learn, self-motivated, detail oriented, and able to multitask</li><li>Ability to thrive in a dynamic startup environment; you’ll have guidance when you need it, but you’re also goal oriented and can execute without close supervision<br><br></li></ul>The SF base salary target range for this full-time position is $158,000 - $193,000 + equity + benefits. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location. The range displayed on each job posting reflects the minimum and maximum target for new hire salaries for the position in San Francisco, CA. Within the range, individual pay is determined by work location and additional factors, including job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for your work location during the hiring process.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong><ul><li>Competitive salary, equity, benefits, and perks for all full-time employees</li><li>Employer-paid medical, dental, and vision insurance (Country specific)</li><li>Retirement employer match</li><li>$2,000 Learning &amp; Development stipend to invest in your professional development</li><li>$1,000 USD Turo host matching and $1,500 USD vehicle reimbursement program</li><li>$100 USD Monthly Turo travel credit</li><li>Cell phone, internet and Fringe benefit stipend</li><li>Paid time off to relax and recharge</li><li>Paid holidays, volunteer time off, and parental leave</li><li>For those who are in the office full-time or hybrid we have weekly in-office lunch, office snacks, and fun activities</li><li>Annual Turbo Week (week-long, company-wide conference)<br><br></li></ul>We are committed to building a diverse team. If you are from a background that's underrepresented in tech, we'd love to meet you.<br><br>Aside from an award winning work environment and the opportunity to be part of the world’s largest car sharing marketplace, we are also growing the team quickly - join us! Even if you don't meet every qualification, we are looking for people with enthusiasm for what we do and we will consider you for this and other possibilities.<br><br>Turo is an Equal Opportunity Employer and a participant in the U.S. Federal E-Verify program. Women, minorities, individuals with disabilities and protected veterans are encouraged to apply. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities and perspectives.<br><br>Turo will consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, as applicable.<br><br>We welcome candidates with physical, mental, and/or neurological disabilities. If you require assistance applying for an open position, or need accommodation during the recruiting process due to a disability, please submit a request to People Operations by emailing PeopleOps@turo.com.<br><br><strong>About Turo<br><br></strong>Turo is the world’s largest car sharing marketplace where you can book any car you want, wherever you want it, from a vibrant community of trusted hosts across the US, Canada, France, UK and Australia. Guests choose from a totally unique selection of nearby cars, while hosts earn extra money to offset the costs of car ownership. A pioneer of the sharing economy and the travel industry, Turo is a safe, supportive community where the car you book is part of a story, not a fleet.<br><br>Discover Turo at https://turo.com, the App Store, and Google Play, and check out our blog, Field Notes.<br><br>Read more about the Turo culture according to Turo CEO, Andre Haddad.<br><br>

desc: Amick Brown is seeking an experienced <strong>RA/QA Data Analyst</strong> for our direct client.<p><br></p><strong>Location:</strong> Sunnyvale, CA / Hybrid<p><br></p><strong>Duration: </strong>12 Months.<p><br></p><strong>Estimated pay range:</strong> <strong>$</strong> <strong>44</strong><strong> - 55</strong> hour per client contract and candidate skills, experience and work location.<p><br></p><strong><u>Job Description</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>The RA/QA Data Analyst will be a member of the RA/QA data analytics team and use technical expertise and a solid understanding of business processes and needs to turn data into useful information. </li><li>In this role, the analyst will work closely with various business teams to understand, collect, clarify, and translate business data requirements into reports and analytics as required. </li><li>The analyst will be heavily involved with the use, distribution, and successful delivery of reports on a periodic basis. </li><li>The ideal candidate would have medical device post market experience and have the ability to explore and integrate different data sources using tools such as SQL and Tableau. </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Responsibilities</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Partner with various Quality Management System (QMS) business teams to support data needs </li><li>Translate non-technical data requirements into metrics, reports, and visualization dashboards </li><li>Partner with business teams to define and document business requirements for new metrics and reports </li><li>Ability to execute deep dives into available data sets to provide insight on product quality performance </li><li>Develop user documentation and a variety of visual representation of data analysis and ensures consistency and accuracy of data and analysis provided </li><li>Support business system integrations for data needs and report outputs </li><li>Perform ongoing monitoring and refinement of reports and analytical solutions to ensure a good user experience in support reports and dashboards </li><li>Partner with architecture and solution delivery teams to enable reports that have long-term value </li><li>Perform functional, regression, usability test, etc. as applicable for both new and existing datasets, reports and dashboards. Document and summarize test results and findings as required </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Skill/Job Requirements</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Education: Bachelor's or higher degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer and Information Science or equivalent blend of work and certification experience required </li><li>Minimum 5 years of data analytics experience, with 3+ years hands on using Tableau required </li><li>Minimum 3+ years of experience with Microsoft SQL or equivalent required </li><li>Programming skills and experience, especially for data exploration and presentation to management and other users of data required </li><li>Highly organized, self-starter and highly motivated with strong prioritization skills managing multiple projects required </li><li>Creative problem solver that is able to look at an issue from a variety of angles required </li><li>Ability to work in fast-paced teams with a great work ethic and an enthusiasm for problem solving and data analysis required </li><li>Working experience in medical device, pharmaceutical, regulatory or other related industries highly preferred </li><li>Experience and capability using visualization software such as Tableau, Power BI, and familiarity with SAP, CRM or other ERP system preferred </li><li>Knowledge of the business of medical device development and manufacture preferred </li><li>Excellent writing skills and documentation skills that enable analyses to be reliably reproduced using the same data years later preferred </li></ul><p><br></p>Amick Brown is an Information Technology consulting company specializing in ERP, Data Analytics, Information Security, Application Development, Networking, and Cloud Computing. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in San Ramon, California.<p><br></p>Regular full-time employees are eligible for the following Amick Brown provided benefits:<p><br></p><ul><li>Health </li><li>Vision </li><li>Dental </li><li>401k with company match </li><li>Paid time off </li><li>Sick Leave </li><li>Short-Term Disability </li><li>Life Insurance </li><li>Wellness &amp; Discount Programs</li></ul>

<strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong> About TikTok<br>TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.<br><br>Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day. To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always. At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve. Join us.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone department of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security &amp; Privacy, Engineering, User &amp; Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>About Trust and Safety<br>Trust and Safety Operations a pivotal team within U.S. Data Security. We strive to enable TikTok to become the most trusted and secure platform in the US through operational excellence in content moderation via innovations in technology, optimization in processes and investment in people. We ensure that we enforce our policies based on our community guidelines and we take appropriate actions in a timely manner to minimize risks on our platform to our users and advertisers.<br><br>In order to enhance collaboration and cross-functional partnerships, among other things, at this time, our organization follows a hybrid work schedule that requires employees to work in the office 3 days a week, or as directed by their manager/department. We regularly review our hybrid work model, and the specific requirements may change at any time.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>- Lead the weekly business review (WBR) process for the Safety Operations team, including executive level presentations and performance meetings<br>- Develop and maintain scalable, automated dashboards and reports that benchmark and track progress against key operational performance goals and initiatives.<br>- Work with management and/or internal stakeholders to define business requirements and analytical needs and execute against them.<br>- Support demand forecasting and modeling capabilities related to how fast we should be growing our expenses and our investment in our moderation workforce.<br>- Conduct data mining, regression analysis and other quantitative analysis using industry standard statistical and business analytics techniques.<br>- Creating and maintaining data documentation both for an internal, technical audience and for partner user teams <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> Qualifications<br>- A Bachelor's degree or higher in Management Information Systems, Business Analytics, or related subjects is preferred.<br>- 5+ years of experience in management, business process improvement, or analytical roles in content moderation or similar fields. Such as call centers and adverts moderation in tech companies.<br>- Proficiency in Excel &amp; Google sheet and hands-on experience in SQL. <br>- Experience working with Business Insights tools, e.g., Tableau, Power BI, etc.<br>- Experience in data science programming languages (e.g., Python, R)<br>- Comfortable with ambiguity; able to thrive with minimal oversight and process, while keeping leadership informed on progress against deadlines<br>- Strong communication, presentation &amp; documentation skills.<br><br>D&amp;I Statement<br>TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.<br><br>Accommodation Statement<br>TikTok is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation, please reach out to us at usds.accommodations@tiktokusds.com <br><br><strong>Job Information:<br><br></strong>【For Pay Transparency】Compensation Description (annually) <p>The base salary range for this position in the selected city is $106400 - $177777 annually.<span></span></p><p>Compensation may vary outside of this range depending on a number of factors, including a candidate’s qualifications, skills, competencies and experience, and location. Base pay is one part of the Total Package that is provided to compensate and recognize employees for their work, and this role may be eligible for additional discretionary bonuses/incentives, and restricted stock units.<span></span></p><p>Our company benefits are designed to convey company culture and values, to create an efficient and inspiring work environment, and to support our employees to give their best in both work and life. We offer the following benefits to eligible employees: <span></span></p><p>We cover 100% premium coverage for employee medical insurance, approximately 75% premium coverage for dependents and offer a Health Savings Account(HSA) with a company match. As well as Dental, Vision, Short/Long term Disability, Basic Life, Voluntary Life and AD&amp;D insurance plans. In addition to Flexible Spending Account(FSA) Options like Health Care, Limited Purpose and Dependent Care. <span></span></p><p>Our time off and leave plans are: 10 paid holidays per year plus 17 days of Paid Personal Time Off (PPTO) (prorated upon hire and increased by tenure) and 10 paid sick days per year as well as 12 weeks of paid Parental leave and 8 weeks of paid Supplemental Disability. <span></span></p><p>We also provide generous benefits like mental and emotional health benefits through our EAP and Lyra. A 401K company match, gym and cellphone service reimbursements. The Company reserves the right to modify or change these benefits programs at any time, with or without notice.<span></span></p>

IT EDW and BI/Reporting Sys<br><br>Full Time<br><br>75099BR<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>This key position will be integral in using data to support our Education mission. This position is responsible for the design, specifications, coding, testing, implementation, maintenance, documentation, debugging, and troubleshooting of data warehouse solutions. Its work includes analyzing source system data and creating data visualization products such as reports and dashboards. The position plays a critical role in requirement gathering, project plan planning, technical architecture design, go-live implementation, and ongoing system support. Stanford University is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to Manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, under the direction of project researchers, investigators, or managers.<br><br>You will be working with an unparalleled leading-edge community of faculty and staff that are fundamentally changing the world of health care. You will have the opportunity to influence and drive change with your innovative ideas, the ability to make a difference and participate in human advancements. Our culture is fast-paced, energetic, and growing all the time.<br><br>We offer a variety of benefits beyond traditional medical, dental, retirement, and savings options:<br><br><ul><li>Events and program for children, sports camps, tuition options</li><li>World-class intellectual stimulation through learning and development classes, workshops, and onsite conferences from leading-edge speakers and faculty</li><li>Work/life and family-friendly policies and reimbursement</li><li>Participation in Stanford’s social responsibility and sustainable programs for a better world</li><li>A vibrant university culture that values the uniqueness of each individual<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About The Department Of Pathology<br><br></strong>Comprised of extraordinary faculty and staff, our mission is to improve the ability to diagnose, treat and understand the origin and manifestation of human disease, and to care for those who have or are at risk to develop disease. We accomplish this through our clinical services (in all fields of anatomic and clinical pathology, including molecular and genomic pathology, histocompatibility testing and transfusion medicine) and be research (which includes basic, translational and clinical research into the origins and manifestations of disease, including efforts to improve disease prediction and prevention as part of the goal of achieving precision medicine and health), and also by educating future leaders in pathology and related fields. Everything we do is to achieve the goals of providing the highest quality of clinical services to the patients for whom we passionately care, to advance our ability to understand, diagnose, monitor and ultimately to cure disease or to prevent or delay its occurrence, and to provide outstanding education and career development opportunities to those who share these goals.<br><br>For more information about the department visit http://pathology.stanford.edu/<br><br><strong>About The Lab<br><br></strong>The goal of Dr. Brooke Howitt’s lab is to better understand molecular features of tumors that better inform:<br><br><ul><li>Diagnostic classification</li><li>Identification of diagnostic, prognostic, and predictive biomarkers</li><li>Our understanding of the complex biology underlying initiation and progression of diseases, leading to improved detection, prevention, and treatment approaches</li><li>Spatial and single cell studies compatible with archival FFPE tissues<br><br><br></li></ul>We have focused on gynecologic and sarcoma entities, with ongoing projects on:<br><br><ul><li>Uterine carcinosarcoma</li><li>Uterine sarcomas and mesenchymal tumors</li><li>Endometrial carcinomas including rare variants such as mesonephric-like carcinoma<br><br><br></li></ul>To learn more about our lab please visit https://med.stanford.edu/brookehowittlab.html<br><br><strong>About The Position<br><br></strong>We are seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Lab of Dr. Brooke Howitt in the Department of Pathology. This Data Analyst will aid in many of the lab’s research activities by collecting, managing, and cleaning datasets associated with patients’ tissues, for a variety of study cohorts ranging from &lt;10 patients to over 1,000 patients. These databases need to be regularly updated, managed, and kept readily available for data exportation for analysis. As we study a variety of rare diseases and cancers, we often participate in multi-institutional projects where you will safely track and manage patient materials inventory in accordance with IRB protocols.<br><br>The Data Analyst will play a key role in designing, building, and maintaining the analytical pipelines used for routine analysis in the lab. job_title: Senior Data Analyst, Reimbursement (Hybrid, Remote, or Onsite Options)
desc: <strong>Company Description<br><br></strong>Guardant Health is a leading precision oncology company focused on helping conquer cancer globally through use of its proprietary tests, vast data sets and advanced analytics. The Guardant Health oncology platform leverages capabilities to drive commercial adoption, improve patient clinical outcomes and lower healthcare costs across all stages of the cancer care continuum. Guardant Health has commercially launched Guardant360®, Guardant360 CDx, Guardant360 TissueNext™, Guardant360 Response™, and GuardantOMNI® tests for advanced stage cancer patients, and Guardant Reveal™ for early-stage cancer patients. The Guardant Health screening portfolio, including the Shield™ test, aims to address the needs of individuals eligible for cancer screening.<br><br><strong>Job Description<br><br></strong>Are you a data wizard with a passion for healthcare? Do you have experience using data and dashboards to add value? If so, we want you to join our team as a Senior Data Analyst!<br><br>In this strategic role, you will be responsible for using your data analysis skills to solve complex data challenges, optimize processes to increase reimbursement, and ensure the integrity of our systems. You will also be responsible for developing and maintaining dashboards that track our performance and provide insights into areas for improvement.<br><br>This is a unique opportunity to make a real difference at a company that is revolutionizing cancer care. By using your data analysis skills to improve revenue, you will be contributing to the company’s mission of fighting cancer with data.<br><br><strong>Essential Duties And Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li>Collaborate with reimbursement specialists to identify payor trends and opportunities</li><li>Develop and manage Tableau dashboards for the team to track performance</li><li>Validate that Guardant products are properly billed according to Medicare criteria</li><li>Assist Reimbursement management with data requests and operational reporting</li><li>Lead projects with other teams/departments for Salesforce, Tableau, lab information, and billing systems enhancements and applications</li><li>Manage existing Excel spreadsheets for ad hoc analysis and compliance reporting</li><li>Be the go-to expert on the team for analysis, providing support and training to front line team members who need help<br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>A minimum of 5 years of experience in data analysis, preferably in healthcare revenue cycle</li><li>Strong analytical capability to be able to use diverse datasets to identify trends</li><li>Problem-solving skills to be able to make recommendations and influence change</li><li>Excellent communication and presentation skills – able to present ideas clearly to senior management level and front line team members</li><li>Experience and proficiency with Excel and Tableau a requirement</li><li>Experience and proficiency with SQL, Salesforce, and automation tools a plus<br><br></li></ul>If you are a data wizard with a passion for healthcare, then we encourage you to apply for this exciting role!<br><br><strong>Additional Information<br><br></strong><strong>Hybrid Work Model</strong><strong>: At Guardant Health, we have defined days for in-person/onsite collaboration and work-from-home days for individual-focused time. We have found aligning our scheduled in-office days allows our teams to do the best work and creates the focused thinking time our innovative work requires. At Guardant, our work model has created flexibility for better work-life balance while keeping teams connected to advance our science for our patients.<br><br></strong>The US base salary range for this full-time position is $88,052 to $126,795 USD. The range does not include benefits, and if applicable, bonus, commission, or equity. <em>The range displayed reflects the minimum and maximum target for new hire salaries across all US locations for the posted role with the exception of any locations specifically referenced below (if any).<br><br></em>For positions based in Palo Alto, CA or Redwood City, CA, the base salary range for this full-time position is $117,403 to $158,494 USD. The range does not include benefits, and if applicable, bonus, commission, or equity.<br><br><em>Within the range, individual pay is determined by work location and additional factors, including, but not limited to, job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. First Round is a seed-stage venture capital firm on a mission to build and serve the world's strongest community of entrepreneurs. Uber, Roblox, Square and Notion are some of the companies we’ve been fortunate to partner with — and we’re just getting started.<br><br>We’ve built an Insights function at First Round that helps drive our end-to-end investment process. We’re hiring an analyst to join this team in San Francisco and help us continue to develop our decision-making system.<br><br>Your core role will include:<br><br><ul><li>Leading and operationalizing data projects to help improve how we make investment decisions</li><li>Designing and running internal dashboards that drive our end-to-end investing process</li><li>Driving analysis to help us uncover new pockets of talent to back</li><li>Supporting our Annual Meeting and other shareholder touch points</li><li>Collaborating closely with the Investment and Finance teams on a piece of analysis, from design to delivery<br><br><br></li></ul>Interested? Here’s what we’re looking for:<br><br><ul><li>This is a unique opportunity in which individuals from many backgrounds could excel. Here are just a few examples of profiles we think could be great:</li><li>A former consultant / business operations professional who biases towards action</li><li>A data analyst / data scientist at a startup who enjoys doing exploratory analysis and testing hypotheses and can always tie it back to business impact (i.e. the “so what”)</li><li>A solutions architect at a young SaaS company who enjoys the balance between client-service, data analysis and designing systems</li><li>An analytical RevOps/SalesOps/CS Ops professional at a startup looking to broaden their professional horizons<br><br><br></li></ul>You could be a great Investment Insights Analyst at First Round if:<br><br><ul><li>You love playing with numbers. You get excited about diving into data to learn how to improve a product or business. You take just as much pride in doing the work that sits upstream of data analysis: data gathering, preparation, cleaning and deduping</li><li>You thrive in autonomous environments. You like to understand the goal, but then can figure out the path to make it happen. </li><li>You’re fascinated by technology and how today’s entrepreneurs are shaping the future. You don’t necessarily need deep knowledge of the venture capital industry, but you should be excited about the field and eager to learn the business quickly. </li><li>You have excellent communication skills. You pride yourself on your thoughtful communication. This includes all forms of business communication: oral, slide preparation and presentation, spreadsheet analysis creation, long-form prose in proposals. You know the right questions to ask, as well as when to listen and learn</li><li>You have a get-things-done mindset. You are laser focused on execution with the drive to get things done. You’re organized, detail oriented and reliable above all else</li><li>You are a creative problem solver. You are resourceful and clever about tackling the challenges of doing analysis at the seed stage i.e. lack of data and very long feedback loops. You know when to 80/20 something and when we need a true deep dive to find the answer we’re looking for</li><li>We hope to meet with candidates with at least 3-6 years of working experience. Please note, this is not an investing role, rather it’s a role to support how we invest and operate<br><br><br></li></ul>Our Values:<br><br><ul><li>Try harder for founders. They’re our customers — LPs are our shareholders. Going above and beyond for our founders is what we do. We strive to be a founder's most valuable investor. That’s why we don't pull term sheets, and we're always in for their second round. We respond to their emails in hours, not days. We build candidate pipelines, unprompted. We arrange meal deliveries when they become a new parent. Simply put, we go above and beyond to earn that right to be their first call every time there’s a bump in the road</li><li>Give your unvarnished opinions and unwavering support. We strive to be kind, not nice. One of the most (counterintuitively) compassionate things you can do is to offer your unvarnished opinion — along with your unwavering support. That willingness to risk a fleeting moment of discomfort in exchange for someone else’s growth is long-term kindness</li><li>Treat the little things like big things. Everything can always be made better. We’re all about the carefully crafted, the nitty-gritty, and the bespoke. Whether it’s hand cutting each nameplate, or debating the optimal shape of the dinner table, no detail is too small to sweat</li><li>Make speed a habit. Whatever you’re building, remember that now is better than two weeks from now. We’re fans of starting small and iterating quickly. No matter what we’re launching, you’ll likely hear this question in a meeting: “How soon can we get something out there?”Invent and wander. Never stop experimenting. The best ideas are born out of experimentation. Our flagship programs have always come from our penchant for going out on a limb and approaching problems with a different perspective</li><li>Build wider doorways and longer tables. We're in the business of backing people and betting on their ideas — no matter where they come from. While talent is evenly distributed, opportunity is not. We need to break down barriers in our investment process, and make sure our work doesn’t stop after writing a check. Everything from the composition of our team to the inclusiveness of our community impacts how we can support founders. First Round is dedicated to building a diverse and inclusive workspace. We encourage people from underrepresented groups to apply because we believe that our diverse team helps us build and serve the strongest community of entrepreneurs<br><br><br></li></ul>The pay range for this role is $100,000-$150,000 (not including our profit sharing program), and will be determined by a candidate's experience level. Our talent team is happy to share more details about our total compensation and benefits package.

<strong>10 Months<br><br></strong><strong>Foster City CA<br><br></strong><strong>Description<br><br></strong><ul><li>3-5 Years of Experience, ideally working with data for most of that time</li><li>We are looking for someone to assist with dashboard creation, to help ensure synchronization of critical sales pipeline data across two systems, and support tech tools implementation.</li><li>The primary responsibility of the Associate will be understanding the key data elements being tracked across both systems, and with guidance from the manager, develop and implement a standardized process to download data from one system and manually upload into a second system.</li><li>Once the process is determined to be stable, the Associate will be on point to regularly implement the data sync across the two systems.</li><li>In addition, the person will need to flag records where a straightforward update is not possible due to discrepancies in record identifiers, and work with the manager to follow-up with data owners to correct data as needed before uploading.</li><li>An ideal candidate would go beyond the core requirements and be able to not only execute on process efficiently and with great attention to detail and follow-through, but also be able to proactively identify opportunities for improvement.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Education/Experience<br><br></strong><ul><li>High School Diploma or GED required, associate or bachelor’s Degree preferred.</li><li>3-7 years related experience required.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Skills &amp;
