Stanford University is seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to Manage and analyze large amounts of information, typically technical or scientific in nature, under the direction of project researchers, investigators, or managers.<br><br>You will be working with an unparalleled leading-edge community of faculty and staff that are fundamentally changing the world of health care. You will have the opportunity to influence and drive change with your innovative ideas, the ability to make a difference and participate in human advancements. Our culture is fast-paced, energetic, and growing all the time.<br><br>We offer a variety of benefits beyond traditional medical, dental, retirement, and savings options:<br><br><ul><li> Events and program for children, sports camps, tuition options </li><li>World-class intellectual stimulation through learning and development classes, workshops, and onsite conferences from leading-edge speakers and faculty </li><li>Work/life and family-friendly policies and reimbursement </li><li>Participation in Stanford’s social responsibility and sustainable programs for a better world </li><li>A vibrant university culture that values the uniqueness of each individual <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>About The Department Of Pathology<br><br></strong>Comprised of extraordinary faculty and staff, our mission is to improve the ability to diagnose, treat and understand the origin and manifestation of human disease, and to care for those who have or are at risk to develop disease. We accomplish this through our clinical services (in all fields of anatomic and clinical pathology, including molecular and genomic pathology, histocompatibility testing and transfusion medicine) and be research (which includes basic, translational and clinical research into the origins and manifestations of disease, including efforts to improve disease prediction and prevention as part of the goal of achieving precision medicine and health), and also by educating future leaders in pathology and related fields. Everything we do is to achieve the goals of providing the highest quality of clinical services to the patients for whom we passionately care, to advance our ability to understand, diagnose, monitor and ultimately to cure disease or to prevent or delay its occurrence, and to provide outstanding education and career development opportunities to those who share these goals.<br><br>For more information about the department visit http://pathology.stanford.edu/<br><br><strong>About The Lab<br><br></strong>The goal of Dr. Brooke Howitt’s lab is to better understand molecular features of tumors that better inform:<br><br><ul><li>Diagnostic classification </li><li>Identification of diagnostic, prognostic, and predictive biomarkers </li><li>Our understanding of the complex biology underlying initiation and progression of diseases, leading to improved detection, prevention, and treatment approaches </li><li>Spatial and single cell studies compatible with archival FFPE tissues <br><br><br></li></ul>We have focused on gynecologic and sarcoma entities, with ongoing projects on:<br><br><ul><li>Uterine carcinosarcoma </li><li>Uterine sarcomas and mesenchymal tumors </li><li>Endometrial carcinomas including rare variants such as mesonephric-like carcinoma <br><br><br></li></ul>To learn more about our lab please visit https://med.stanford.edu/brookehowittlab.html<br><br><strong>About The Position<br><br></strong>We are seeking a Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Lab of Dr. Brooke Howitt in the Department of Pathology. This Data Analyst will aid in many of the lab’s research activities by collecting, managing, and cleaning datasets associated with patients’ tissues, for a variety of study cohorts ranging from &lt;10 patients to over 1,000 patients. You will extract data from clinical records and work with external collaborators to extract, clean, and provide de-identified data to create databases and reports. These databases need to be regularly updated, managed, and kept readily available for data exportation for analysis. As we study a variety of rare diseases and cancers, we often participate in multi-institutional projects where you will safely track and manage patient materials inventory in accordance with IRB protocols.<br><br>The Data Analyst will play a key role in designing, building, and maintaining the analytical pipelines used for routine analysis in the lab. We welcome candidates with a growth mindset, interest in a variety of cancer and autoimmune disease research questions, and a willingness to take on challenging learning opportunities. Candidates should be knowledgeable about best practices for handling large clinical datasets, using databases, and familiar with extracting data from medical records. This position will collaborate with a variety of trainees, research staff, and department staff, as well as institutional and industry collaborators.<br><br>In addition to comparable research compensation, candidates will have the opportunity to learn and develop their C.V. or resume through research publications and presentations.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br><br></strong><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets. </li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data. </li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements. </li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions. </li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation. </li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation. </li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods. </li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff. </li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> Other duties may also be assigned<br><br><br></li></ul><em>The job duties listed are typical examples of work performed by positions in this job classification and are not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, tasks, and responsibilities. Specific duties and responsibilities may vary depending on department or program needs without changing the general nature and scope of the job or level of responsibility. Employees may also perform other duties as assigned.<br><br></em><strong>Desired Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Biology, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or Biomedical related field. </li><li>Research experience in biology, pathology or oncology desired. Experience in designing data analysis pipelines is an advantage. </li><li>Experience (or willingness to learn) managing large patient cohorts and datasets in databases and digital repositories such as REDCap and Concentriq. </li><li>Intimate knowledge with at least one of the following programming languages: Python/R/Perl/Matlab/Java/C/C++ </li><li>The candidate should be able to work independently, be highly motivated, well organized with exceptional attention to detail, adaptable and work well within a highly interdisciplinary and international team. Good communication and interpersonal skills as well as fluent English are essential, as well as proficient computer skills (Mac and PC).<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Knowledge, Skills, And Abilities (Required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs. </li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills. </li><li>Ability to prioritize workload. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Physical Requirements*:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity. </li><li>Occasionally use a telephone. </li><li>Rarely writing by hand. <br><br><br></li></ul><em>* - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.<br><br></em><strong><em>This role is open to candidates anywhere in the United States. The expected pay range for this position is $64,480 to $97,000 per annum/hour. <br><br></em></strong><strong><em>Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. The Position<br><br><strong>Who We Are<br><br></strong>Genentech, a member of the Roche group and founder of the biotechnology industry, is dedicated to pursuing groundbreaking science to discover and develop medicines for people with serious and life-threatening diseases. To solve the world's most complex health challenges, we ask bigger questions that challenge our industry and the boundaries of science to transform society. Our transformational discoveries include the first targeted antibody for cancer and the first medicine for primary progressive multiple sclerosis.<br><br>The COVID-19 pandemic has forever altered the expectations for healthcare providers, patients, and their families on how data and technology can be used to enhance the customer experience in ways not previously possible. Genentech seeks to lead the industry in this new era of omnichannel pharma and integrated customer experience.<br><br>The Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization plays a key role in installing a digital culture and mindset across the Commercial and Medical Group (CMG) as well as providing every CMG customer - be it employee, manager, healthcare provider, and patient - with the information and skills that they need next, when they need it, where they need it. LSD is in the process of transforming CMG into a continuous then contribution learning culture by pioneering advances in skills management, digital learning, experiential learning, and workflow learning.<br><br>LSD includes a team of learning business partners who have deep business acumen and are well versed in the trends and data coming from sales, marketing, and medical. They work in close collaboration with a group of Learning Design Architects who are responsible for perennial focus areas such as medical, therapeutic area certification, leadership development as well as business transformation areas which currently include omnichannel, contracting, digital, and health equity across all CMG business units. Both teams are supported by a team of instructional designers and multimedia partners who build best-in-class learning products. LSD scales these learning products through facilitators who upskill business experts and leaders in executive presence, learning technologists who use cutting edge applications and systems to embed learning as close to the work as possible, and an analytics function that maps CMG's skill domains and employee skill gain to business impact metrics.<br><br><strong>Role Overview:<br><br></strong>The Data Analyst provides the Learning &amp; Skill Development (LSD) organization and our business partners with data analytics that enable insights and business decision-making. The role will develop, implement, and maintain leading-edge data analytics, to uncover key insights, assess operational health and lead to better informed decision making and business impact. The role will identify trends and opportunities for growth through analysis of complex datasets, create best-practice reports based on data mining, analysis, and visualization. The role will evaluate internal systems for efficiency, problems, and inaccuracies, and develop and maintain protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data and utilize their technical expertise to ensure data is accurate and high quality. The Data Analyst will work directly with key stakeholders to gather requirements, provide ongoing reports and dashboards, and build relationships<br><br><strong>Key Responsibilities:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Provide thought leadership the design of new experiments and metrics that can be used to test and validate experiments for new Learning &amp; Skill Development capabilities along with new operational metrics to monitor the health of Learning Operations </li><li>Partner with Learning Business Partners to co-deliver quarterly business reviews, monthly business reviews, or experiment findings and insights to senior business stakeholders </li><li>Work with key stakeholders to identify process improvement opportunities, propose system modifications, and devise data governance strategies </li><li>Use statistical tools to identify, analyze, and interpret patterns and trends in complex data sets to assess operational health, business impact of learning solutions, forecast future skill needs, and inform business decisions </li><li>Develop dashboards, automated data feeds, and ad-hoc reporting that tracks and evaluates the progress and effectiveness of LSD programs </li><li>Facilitate and support Learning Operations and Learning Business Partners through design, development, and management of key metrics, reports, and analyzes to help measure business performance and drive key business decisions across strategies and resourcing needs </li><li>Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and create and deliver ongoing dashboards and reports to key stakeholders across the business to enable important business decisions based on key insights and trends </li><li>Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and quality </li><li>Demonstrate attention to detail and ensure accuracy in data analysis and recognizing anomalies or errors in data. </li><li>Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems </li><li>Work with key stakeholders to prioritize business and information needs <br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications/Experience<br><br></strong><ul><li>Minimum of 5 years proven working experience as a Data Analyst or Business Data Analyst role</li><li>Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques</li><li>Strong knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc) Experience building and improving forecasting models</li><li>Minimum of 3 years experience with reporting packages (Business Objects etc), analytical tools/databases (Python, R, SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks) and proficiency in data visualization using Qlik/Tableau is preferred</li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings</li><li>Experience with statistical modeling, analysis, and presentation of results to a non-technical audience</li><li>Strong bias for action and ability to work with minimal supervision</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills, both written and verbal<br><br></li></ul><strong>Our Operating Principles<br><br></strong><ul><li>Put Patients First: I always act as if patients I know are in the room and do what's best for them.</li><li>Follow the science: I seek answers through experiments, data and debate, and act on facts.</li><li>Act as one team: I care, collaborate and commit without boundaries, and trust others to do their part.</li><li>Embrace differences: I seek diverse perspectives, invite opposing views, and challenge myself and others.</li><li>Accelerate learning: I push to learn new things even if difficult, and openly share my successes and failures.</li><li>Simplify radically: I eliminate complexity, reuse with pride, and accomplish more with less.</li><li>Make impact now: I take accountability to do what's right, deliver value fast, and don't wait for certainty.</li><li>Think long term: I choose actions today that benefit future generations<br><br></li></ul>The expected salary range for this position based on the primary location of South San Francisco, CA is $131,900.00 - $244,900. Actual pay will be determined based on experience, qualifications, geographic location, and other job-related factors permitted by law. A discretionary annual bonus may be available based on individual and Company performance. This position also qualifies for the benefits detailed at the link provided below.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong>Relocation benefits are not available for this job posting<br><br>Genentech is an equal opportunity employer, and we embrace the increasingly diverse world around us. <strong>Overview<br><br></strong>Our Customer Experience (CX) Analytics team within TurboTax is customer obsessed and fearless in our pursuit of data backed insights and tech led continuous improvements. Inspiring action and informing decisions across the business, driving toward our growth and retention goals.<br><br><strong>What You'll Bring<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree, or equivalent work experience, in Quantitative field or commensurate experience (Statistics, Applied Math, Econometrics, Operations Research). Master’s degree preferred.</li><li>10+ years’ professional experience with data and statistical analysis, with a deep understanding of explanatory power and hypothesis-driven analyses.</li><li>Data mining algorithms and statistical modeling techniques such as clustering, classification, regression, decision trees, neural nets, support vector machines, genetic algorithms, anomaly detection, recommender systems, sequential pattern discovery, and text mining.</li><li>Experience with tools to analyze, manipulate and visualize datasets (e.g. SQL, Excel/Sheets, Python, Splunk, Tableau, Qlik).</li><li>Proven track record of data visualization and story-telling, to develop actionable insights and business impact.</li><li>Experience working with operational KPI metrics &amp; reporting systems<br><br></li></ul><strong>How You Will Lead<br><br></strong><ul><li>Investigator: Translate business questions into verifiable hypotheses, create experiments and/or analysis to test them, and generate recommendations based on the findings. You collect requirements and execute queries to answer the team’s most important data questions</li><li>Dot-Connector: Your business and operational acumen help you recognize patterns, connections and relationships across variables. You make the connections across data sets to help others understand the broader system.</li><li>Artist: your visualization, simplicity and clarity of analysis brings data to life and inspires action and understanding.</li><li>Craftsman: You build models and reports that allow others to interact, utilize and better understand the underlying data, relationships and insights.</li></ul>

<strong>Overview<br><br></strong>Do you have a passion for making huge business impacts by leveraging data-driven insights? Do you love working collaboratively in an innovative environment? Would you love to make an impact on our customers’ lives? Come join Intuit where you’ll be empowered to do the best work of your life!<br><br>We are looking for a world-class analyst to help transform the decision-making process with data. We have an exciting opportunity to help shape how we use data and technology to drive decisions and deliver the best customer experience across multiple strategic touchpoints. If you are an individual with excellent analytical skills and a passion for delivering data-driven insights, come join Intuit’s Turbo Tax Analytics team.<br><br><strong>What You'll Bring<br><br></strong><ul><li>3+ years of experience working with marketing analytics, web analytics, product analytics, customer care analytics, or other customer experience analytics</li><li>Advanced proficiency in SQL, A/B Testing, and Data Visualization</li><li>Experience in defining metrics and instrumenting data tracking</li><li>Experience working with teams with a heavy focus on developing strategies that look to add substantial value with data inputs</li><li>Experience in programming languages and stats packages preferred (e.g. Python, R)</li><li>Ability to simplify stories with data, and be concise in the insights and how they drive outcomes with leadership and stakeholders</li><li>Excellent problem-solving skills and end-to-end quantitative thinking</li><li>Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously to meet objectives and key deadlines</li><li>Outstanding communication skills with both technical and non-technical colleagues</li><li>Proactive and inquisitive learner... seeks out and capitalizes on opportunities for change that enhance the business, rather than reacting to circumstances</li><li>Strong organization, time management and task prioritization skills</li><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, Data Analytics, Finance, Advanced Analytics, or related field or equivalent work experience. Master’s Degree preferred<br><br></li></ul><strong>How You Will Lead<br><br></strong><ul><li>Driving business strategy: You will collaborate with the Customer and Business Strategy team to determine TurboTax’s FY24 and FY25+ product lineups and in-season decisions to ensure we are meeting our revenue growth goals. In addition, provide ongoing recommendations to leadership utilizing complex data, business knowledge, and strategic assumptions when data doesn’t exist.</li><li>Identifying opportunities and influencing partners to act: You will partner with a cross-functional team to develop hypotheses, decision frameworks, and experiments to leverage data and technology to deliver better outcomes for customers through personalized shopping experiences. You will lead discussions on testing best practices to guarantee an effective upsell/add-on strategy using various testing methodologies.</li><li>Driving self-serve and data literacy: You will create learning and measurement plans for experiments, and define requirements for instrumentation and data collection. You will build reports to drive discussions, facilitate decision-making, and actionable insights by partnering with the strategy team to identify the drivers that have downstream business impact revenue metrics.</li></ul>

The Summer Internship<br><br>At Discord, we offer a personalized experience for interns. Our aim is to offer an experience that mimics what it is like to actually work here.<br><br>Internships are paid and run for (at minimum) 12 weeks, targeting a start date in June 2024 to accommodate varying school calendars. Conditions permitting, our 2024 summer internships will be remote, with an opportunity to spend a week in the office at some point during the program.<br><br><strong>The Team:<br><br></strong>Join our team and help us make Discord better for its current &amp; future users! As a member of our team, you will have the opportunity to leverage our vast amounts of data to inspire new and exciting Discord features. You'll also use your analytics skills to identify ways to improve our user growth funnels and drive real business results.<br><br>What You'll Do:<br><br><ul><li>Analyze data to understand user behavior and user preferences, with the goal of identifying opportunities to build new features and improve the user experience. </li><li>Design and run experiments in partnership with Product and Engineering. </li><li>Communicate insights and recommendations to business leads and influence strategic decision-making. <br><br></li></ul>Role Requirements:<br><br><ul><li>Currently enrolled in a graduate program for a technical discipline</li><li>Analytical mindset, with an ability to solve complex problems</li><li>Excellent communication skills, with an ability to convey technical concepts to non-technical partners</li><li>Strong technical skills in SQL, Python, or R</li><li>Strong understanding of experimentation in the form of A/B testing<br><br></li></ul><strong>Salary of $69/hour (Master's) and $78/hour (PhD)<br><br></strong><strong>Note: Disclosure as required by NYC Pay Transparency Law and CO Disclosure as required by sb19-085(8-5-20)<br><br></strong><strong>Benefits listed below may differ from those available depending on terms of employment*<br><br></strong>Benefits and Perks<br><br><ul><li>Comprehensive medical insurance including Health, Dental and Vision (plus up to $20,000 for gender affirmation procedures)</li><li>Mental health resources and quarterly wellness stipends</li><li>14+ paid holidays, 4 weeks of PTO + use-what-you-need sick days </li><li>Paid parental leave (plus fertility, adoption and other family planning benefits)</li><li>Flexible long-term work options (remote and hybrid)</li><li>Volunteer time off</li><li>A diverse slate of Employee Resource Groups </li><li>Plus commuter contributions and other perks for office-based employees<br><br></li></ul><strong>About Us<br><br></strong>Discord is a voice, video and text app that helps friends and communities come together to hang out and explore their interests — from artists and activists, to study groups, sneakerheads, plant parents, and more. With 150 million monthly users across 19 million active communities, called servers, Discord has grown to become one of the most popular communications services in the world. Discord was built without selling ads or user data and instead, offers a premium subscription called Nitro that gives users special perks like higher quality streams and fun customizations.<br><br>We’re working toward an inclusive world where no one feels like an outsider, where genuine human connection is a click, text chat, or voice call away. A place where everyone can find belonging. Challenging? Heck yes. Rewarding? Double heck yes. It’s a mission that gives us the chance to positively impact millions of people all over the world. <strong>So if this strikes a chord with you, come build belonging with us!<br><br></strong>

<strong>About Watershed<br><br></strong>Watershed is a software platform for running a world-class climate program. We measure our success in the carbon reduction achievements of our customers. We are looking for team members who love product-building, want to work hard at a mission-oriented startup, and will collaborate with us in shaping the culture of a growing team.<br><br>We have offices in San Francisco, New York and London and remote team members across the US and Europe. We hope that you'll be interested in joining us!<br><br>The role<br><br>Accurately measuring carbon emissions is the first step to decarbonize the economy. Watershed is compiling an exhaustive carbon emissions dataset, powered by the latest climate science, and engineering a best-in-class calculation software to empower our customers to reduce emissions. And, we are building a team of Carbon Data Analysts to implement the end-to-end measurement experience for our customers. Measurement is both the first step in a customer’s climate journey and their first experience with Watershed, making this the foundation of not only a company’s climate program, but also their relationship with Watershed.<br><br>We’re looking for individuals to own measurements for some of the world’s leading corporate climate programs. You'll work directly with our customers to develop measurement strategies with industry leading companies, collect and transform their raw business activity data into final carbon numbers, and ensure they understand the methodology and processes that got them there.<br><br>As part of this work, you will:<br><br><ul><li>Work directly with customers to help them build a measurement strategy and identify the correct raw data (on everything from electricity consumption to cheese purchases to Bitcoin transactions) to measure their footprint. </li><li>Help customers ingest and transform unstructured data sets so that they're ready for processing in our automated carbon data pipelines. </li><li>Use our tooling to calculate, test, and publish finalized carbon footprint assessments. </li><li>Explain the technical details of carbon accounting, emissions measurement methodology and how it applies to an individual customer’s business operations. <br><br></li></ul>You might be a fit if you:<br><br><ul><li>Have 2+ years experience in a consulting, solutions-engineering, and/or customer-facing role. You are excited to work directly with customers to help them take the first step in setting up world-class climate programs</li><li>Are an excellent verbal and written communicator. You can communicate complex topics to technical and non-technical audiences. </li><li>Are organized, systematic, and efficient. You thrive in a high-volume environment. </li><li>Are meticulous and detail-obsessed. You won't rest until you get the numbers right. </li><li>Are willing to roll up your sleeves to work with unstructured and inconsistent data. You have good intuition for how numbers in a table map to the real world. </li><li>Are passionate about solving climate change and excited to contribute to doing so at a fast paced startup. You learn quickly and operate well in ambiguity. <br><br></li></ul>FAQ<br><br><strong>Where does Watershed work?<br><br></strong>We have hub offices in San Francisco, New York and London, and some remote team members in the US and EU. Most of our jobs need to be in San Francisco / New York / London, but certain jobs are open to being remote and will be specifically noted on the jobs page and in the job description.<br><br><strong>What’s the interview process like?<br><br></strong>It starts the same for every candidate: getting to know the team members through 1 to 2 conversations about Watershed, your experience, and your interests. Next steps can vary by role, but usual next steps are a skill or experience screen (e.g. a coding interview for an engineer, a portfolio review for a designer, deeper experience call for other roles) which leads to a virtual or in person interview panel after that if the screens go well. We prioritize transparency and lack of surprise throughout the process.

<strong>This is a hybrid role with the onsite location from our headquarters in Campbell, CA - candidates must be local and willing to come into the office 4 days a week.<br><br></strong><strong>About Us<br><br></strong>Acceldata is the market leader in Enterprise Data Observability. Founded in 2018, Silicon Valley-based Acceldata has developed the world's first Enterprise Data Observability Platform to help build and operate great data products.<br><br>Enterprise Data Observability is at the intersection of today’s hottest and most crucial technologies such as AI, LLMs, Analytics, and DataOps. Acceldata provides mission-critical capabilities that deliver highly trusted and reliable data to power enterprise data products.<br><br>Delivered as a SaaS product, Acceldata's solutions have been embraced by global customers, such as HPE, HSBC, Visa, Freddie Mac, Manulife, Workday, Zoominfo, GSK, Oracle, PubMatic, PhonePe (Walmart), Hersheys, Dun &amp; Bradstreet, and many more. Acceldata is a Series-C funded company and its investors include Insight Partners, March Capital, Lightspeed, Sorenson Ventures, Industry Ventures, and Emergent Ventures.<br><br>Position Summary<br><br>As a Business Intelligence Analyst at Acceldata, you will be crucial in driving data-driven decision-making across various departments within the organization. You will leverage analytic and technical skills to innovate, build, and maintain well-managed data solutions and capabilities to tackle business problems. You will be responsible for utilizing your quantitative skills, scripting, and storytelling through numbers to drive Acceldata on three types of work – Analytics Innovation, Business Intelligence, and Data Management. You will be expected to excel in communication, system fluency, and project management.<br><ul><li>Business Intelligence: Collaborate with departmental heads and their teams to offer consultancy and transform business requirements into reports, metrics, dashboards, tools, and methodologies that will enable fact-based decision-making processes.</li><li>BI infrastructure: Build well-managed BI solutions, tools, and capabilities to enable self-service frameworks for data consumers.<br><br></li></ul>We’re looking for someone who can:<br><ul><li>Develop and maintain scripts using SQL, R and Python to extract, clean, and transform data.</li><li>Demonstrate a strong desire and experience with data in various forms (data warehouses/SQL, unstructured data).</li><li>Demonstrate ability to explore and quickly grasp new technologies to progress varied initiatives.</li><li>Perform data analysis to identify trends, patterns, and anomalies within datasets.</li><li>Utilize different BI tools to create interactive and informative data visualizations and dashboards.</li><li>Collaborate with various customer facing functions (Sales, Marketing, Sales Engineering, CS) and Finance to translate their data needs and objectives into reports and dashboards for meaningful insights and recommendations.</li><li>Perform ongoing and ad-hoc analyses for data-driven decision-making across various functions, oversee critical project initiatives, including issue identification, hypothesis formulation, end-to-end analytics project management, data-driven storytelling, and root cause analysis.</li><li>Design, implement, and analyze AB tests to optimize marketing and sales strategies. Report on test results and recommend adjustments based on findings. Effectively communicate complex findings and insights to non-technical stakeholders with strong recommendations to improve processes and outcomes.</li><li>Build and maintain interactive and automated dashboards using tools like Google Sheets or Excel to monitor key performance metrics and ensure data accuracy and real-time updates.<br><br></li></ul>What makes you the right fit for this position?<br><ul><li>Master’s degree in Mathematics or Statistics</li><li>4 - 7 years of experience as a BI Analyst in a B2B or B2C startup</li><li>Must have startup experience</li><li>At least 4 years of scripting experience in coding (Python, R, Spark, or SQL)</li><li>Strong analytical mindset with the ability to think critically and solve complex problems</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to tell a compelling data story</li><li>Project management skills and the ability to work independently and in a team</li><li>Proficiency in data integration</li><li>Familiarity with AB testing methodologies and statistical analysis</li><li>Experience in creating and maintaining dashboards in Google Sheets or Excel</li><li>Goes beyond immediate requests to recognize patterns<br><br></li></ul>Hiring Range<br><br>The hiring pay range provides a guide for what we would reasonably pay for the position. Pay is determined by various factors including market demand, applicable skills, work experience and education, location, company budget, and in-demand skill sets.<br><br>$140,000 - $160,000 USD<br><br>Acceldata is an equal-opportunity employer<br><br>At Acceldata, we are committed to providing equal employment opportunities regardless of job history, disability, gender identity, religion, race, color, caste, marital/parental status, veteran status, or any other special status. We stand against the discrimination of employees and individuals and are proud to be an equitable workplace that welcomes individuals from all walks of life if they fit the designated roles and responsibilities.<br><br>Life @ Acceldata<br><br> is all about working with some of the best minds in the industry and experiencing a culture that values an ‘out-of-the-box’ mindset. If you want to push boundaries, learn continuously, and grow to be the best version of yourself, Acceldata is the place to be!<br><br>We also believe in providing our employees with the right tools and resources to help them excel at their jobs. We offer:<br><ul><li>Flexible PTO Plan</li><li>Up to 100% employer-paid benefits for health, dental, and vision coverage</li><li>Discounts and offerings through major vendors through our PEO<br><br></li></ul>What should you know about joining Acceldata? <br><br>At Acceldata, each job and role serves a purpose toward our business goals. You’ll have opportunities to make an immediate impact on mission-critical projects as you work with highly capable and ambitious peer groups.  <br><br>Join Acceldata and help us achieve our data goals. Learn more about our solutions and products here: Acceldata Product Overview &amp; Demo

<strong>Overview</strong><p><br></p>Come elevate marketing sciences practices on the Data Science and Analytics team as a Senior Business Data Analyst. Our team is part of the larger Small Business and Self-Employed Group (SBSEG), focused on spearheading advanced data-driven solutions across marketing analytics practices. We are looking for a technical problem solver with a knack for delivering advanced scalable solutions. You will work alongside Data Scientists, Finance Analysts, Marketers, and Engineers to drive durable and data-driven forecasting solutions for the QuickBooks business.<p><br></p><strong>What You'll Bring</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>3+ years of demonstrable success combining advanced analysis and statistical modeling skills with exceptional business acumen. Experience with macroeconomics, causal inference modeling and forecasting is a plus. </li><li>Technical proficiency in SQL, Python, GitHub, and Databricks. Experience with Tableau and Plotly Dash is a plus. </li><li>Successful history of code design and documentation to scale projects beyond immediate working deliverables.</li><li>Strong bias for continued learning and meeting deadlines with a high degree of accuracy.</li><li>Ability to tell stories with data, educate effectively, and instill confidence, motivating stakeholders to act on recommendations.</li><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, Data Analytics, Finance, Advanced Analytics preferred or equivalent work experience.</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>How You Will Lead</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Effectively identify and apply analytics, causal inference, attribution methodologies and advanced modeling techniques to evaluate business performance and drive strategy across growth teams.</li><li>Identify the right solution and think out of the box to tackle open-ended, causal inference problems with or without known solutions to discover future opportunities.</li><li>Build and maintain time-series forecast models end-to-end, including data collection, code development, validation, model productionalization and documentation. </li><li>Collaborate with other analysts and key business stakeholders on budget scenario planning and optimizations to understand impact on key business metrics.</li><li>Build reusable tables and systems and recommend data standards to improve quality of data and speed of analysis and modeling.</li><li>Provide thought leadership to the team both strategically and technically.</li></ul>

<p><strong>About Second Harvest of Silicon Valley</strong></p><p>Founded in 1974, Second Harvest of Silicon Valley is one of the largest food banks in the nation and a trusted nonprofit leader in ending local hunger. The organization distributes nutritious groceries through a network of nearly 400 partners at drive-thru and walk-up sites across Santa Clara and San Mateo counties. Due to the prohibitively expensive cost of living in Silicon Valley, the economic downturn caused by the COVID-19 pandemic, and the rise in inflation, Second Harvest is now serving an average of 460,000 people every month. Second Harvest also connects people to federal nutrition programs and other food resources, and advocates for anti-hunger policies on the local, state and national levels. To learn more about how Second Harvest is responding to the incredible amount of need in Silicon Valley, visit shfb.org.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>About the Position</strong></p><p>Second Harvest is looking for a Data Analyst to join our Development department and support our fundraising efforts. The Data Analyst will collaborate with their colleagues in Development Operations &amp; Analytics as well as with our fundraisers, finance team, and Volunteer Engagement team to advance the department’s focus on being an effective, data-driven business operation.</p><p><br></p><p>The Data Analyst will help maximize fundraising effectiveness by conducting action-oriented analysis, explaining the narrative behind reports/findings, and making practical recommendations. The Data Analyst’s responsibilities will include: maintaining and expanding our use of dashboards for fundraising KPIs, enhancing our revenue forecasting, tracking industry trends and benchmarking our performance, supporting the finance department (including monthly reconciliation, annual audit, financial reporting), and fulfilling our reporting requirements for Feeding America. Once we have migrated our database to Salesforce, the Data Analyst will also conduct cross-organization analysis and support the Volunteer Engagement team with analytics tailored to their needs.</p><p><br></p><p>The Data Analyst will also contribute to the department’s transition to Salesforce and a new data lake by creating reports, documentation, and analysis that leverage these new tools and the new data that will become available to us. The Data Analyst will be a key player as we implement more advanced, predictive analytics.</p><p><br></p><p>In this role, you will be a valued member of a flexible, collaborative, supportive work environment that fosters creativity and collaboration. Everyone on the team is passionate about the mission of the organization and doing work that is personally meaningful.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>This job might be for you if:</strong></p><ul><li>You are passionate about ending hunger.</li><li>You have excellent attention to detail, an inquisitive mind, and you enjoy analyzing data to find answers to business questions.</li><li>You can identify fundraising and business opportunities and based on data trends.<strong> </strong></li><li>You enjoy collaborating with teammates and colleagues from other departments to design and create custom analysis.</li><li>You enjoy learning about and helping to implement new technologies.</li><li>You are interested in predictive analytics.</li><li>You can steward sensitive information and data with the utmost integrity and confidentiality.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Developing, implementing and maintaining dashboards, custom ad-hoc analysis, and reports in Salesforce, Power BI or Tableau, and Excel in collaboration with stakeholders.</li><li>Training staff on how to use and interpret data in dashboards and reports.</li><li>Drawing conclusions from the data and recommending appropriate course of action.</li><li>Documenting workflows and the results of business analysis.</li><li>Enhancing our forecast model to increase accuracy and updating our forecast process to use data from Salesforce.</li><li>Provide fundraising analytics as needed to finance for monthly reconciliations, annual audit, financial reporting including IRS Form 990 and other ad hoc queries.</li><li>Reporting on our fundraising results to Feeding America</li><li>Providing analytic support to our Volunteer Engagement team</li><li>Performing other duties as assigned to achieve Second Harvest of Silicon Valley’s goals and objectives.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>The ideal candidate will possess the following professional qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong analytical skills, a curious nature, demonstrated initiative, and the business acumen necessary to synthesize data and formulate conclusions/recommendations that inform practical business decisions.</li><li>Advanced skills with Excel are required. Experience with Salesforce, Power BI or Tableau, and SQL are highly desired.</li><li>Excellent organizational skills, detail-orientation, and a commitment to accuracy</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills and the ability to document processes.</li><li>Experience in a fundraising department or nonprofit organization is desired.</li><li>Experience working on and leading multidisciplinary teams.</li><li>Genuine interest in the mission and activities of Second Harvest of Silicon Valley</li><li>Bachelor’s degree in Data Analytics, Business Management, Economics, related field, or equivalent work experience. An understanding of finance through coursework or work experience is a plus.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Reports To</strong></p><p><strong> </strong>Data Analytics Manager</p><p><br></p><p><strong> Location</strong></p><p>Second Harvest of Silicon Valley, Cypress Distribution Center, 4001 North First Street, San Jose, CA 95134</p><p>This is a hybrid position. Specifics of work location will depend on department need</p><p>An employee’s regular remote work site should be within driving distance of one of Second Harvest’s locations and must be within the state of California.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Hours</strong></p><p>Full- Time. Exempt</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Compensation </strong></p><p><strong> </strong>$62,400- $77,030 is the wage range for this position. The salary wage offer will be commensurate with skills and experience. Outstanding and generous health benefits program, 4-5 weeks of Flexible Time Off (vacation and sick), ten paid holidays, and retirement plan.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>SH Covid-19 Vaccine Policy</strong></p><p><strong> </strong>Second Harvest Food Bank places great importance on the safety of its employees and customers. Therefore, in line with the CDC and state and local recommendations, Second Harvest requires as a condition of employment that employees have received full and effective COVID vaccines prior to commencing employment. In accordance with applicable law, Second Harvest will consider good faith requests for reasonable accommodation based on medical disability or sincerely held religious belief.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>EOE</strong></p><p>Second Harvest is committed to being an equal opportunity employer which values diversity. 55</strong> hour per client contract and candidate skills, experience and work location.<p><br></p><strong><u>Job Description</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>The RA/QA Data Analyst will be a member of the RA/QA data analytics team and use technical expertise and a solid understanding of business processes and needs to turn data into useful information. </li><li>In this role, the analyst will work closely with various business teams to understand, collect, clarify, and translate business data requirements into reports and analytics as required. </li><li>The analyst will be heavily involved with the use, distribution, and successful delivery of reports on a periodic basis. </li><li>The ideal candidate would have medical device post market experience and have the ability to explore and integrate different data sources using tools such as SQL and Tableau. </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Responsibilities</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Partner with various Quality Management System (QMS) business teams to support data needs </li><li>Translate non-technical data requirements into metrics, reports, and visualization dashboards </li><li>Partner with business teams to define and document business requirements for new metrics and reports </li><li>Ability to execute deep dives into available data sets to provide insight on product quality performance </li><li>Develop user documentation and a variety of visual representation of data analysis and ensures consistency and accuracy of data and analysis provided </li><li>Support business system integrations for data needs and report outputs </li><li>Perform ongoing monitoring and refinement of reports and analytical solutions to ensure a good user experience in support reports and dashboards </li><li>Partner with architecture and solution delivery teams to enable reports that have long-term value </li><li>Perform functional, regression, usability test, etc. as applicable for both new and existing datasets, reports and dashboards. Document and summarize test results and findings as required </li></ul><p><br></p><strong><u>Skill/Job Requirements</u></strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Education: Bachelor's or higher degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer and Information Science or equivalent blend of work and certification experience required </li><li>Minimum 5 years of data analytics experience, with 3+ years hands on using Tableau required </li><li>Minimum 3+ years of experience with Microsoft SQL or equivalent required </li><li>Programming skills and experience, especially for data exploration and presentation to management and other users of data required </li><li>Highly organized, self-starter and highly motivated with strong prioritization skills managing multiple projects required </li><li>Creative problem solver that is able to look at an issue from a variety of angles required </li><li>Ability to work in fast-paced teams with a great work ethic and an enthusiasm for problem solving and data analysis required </li><li>Working experience in medical device, pharmaceutical, regulatory or other related industries highly preferred </li><li>Experience and capability using visualization software such as Tableau, Power BI, and familiarity with SAP, CRM or other ERP system preferred </li><li>Knowledge of the business of medical device development and manufacture preferred </li><li>Excellent writing skills and documentation skills that enable analyses to be reliably reproduced using the same data years later preferred </li></ul><p><br></p>Amick Brown is an Information Technology consulting company specializing in ERP, Data Analytics, Information Security, Application Development, Networking, and Cloud Computing. The company was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in San Ramon, California.<p><br></p>Regular full-time employees are eligible for the following Amick Brown provided benefits:<p><br></p><ul><li>Health </li><li>Vision </li><li>Dental </li><li>401k with company match </li><li>Paid time off </li><li>Sick Leave </li><li>Short-Term Disability </li><li>Life Insurance </li><li>Wellness &amp; Discount Programs</li></ul>

job_title: Investigations Data Analyst, Influence Operations - USDS
desc: <strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong> About TikTok<br>TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.<br><br>Why Join Us<br>Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. <br>Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day. <br>To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always. <br>At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve. <br>Join us.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone entity of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security &amp; Privacy, Engineering, User &amp; Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>We are seeking an experienced Threat Data Analyst to join the Trust and Safety organization within USDS.  You will use your investigative and adversarial mindset to help us identify, detect, and mitigate Influence Operation (IO) networks operating on TikTok. You will work within a team of cross-functional subject matter experts to data mine threat actor abuse tactics, develop predictive models, and conduct comprehensive proactive and reactive investigations using analytical skills, subject-matter expertise, and regional experience. The Threat Data Analyst will have the responsibility to perform social network analysis at scale to discover, identify, and mitigate the most harmful threats targeting the platform. You will closely collaborate with engineers and behavioral scientists to resolve complex threats that reach across topic or feature areas and will require network analysis and the creation of detection pipelines. You will develop actionable recommendations, and continually iterate solutions to scale your impact. The work of the Investigations and Insights team is critical to TikTok user safety, and the Threat Data Analyst will have the opportunity to identify and mitigate the most harmful threats targeting the platform and our users. In order to enhance collaboration and cross-functional partnerships, among other things, at this time, our organization follows a hybrid work schedule that requires employees to work in the office 3 days a week, or as directed by their manager/department. We regularly review our hybrid work model, and the specific requirements may change at any time.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>- Identify deceptive behavior of threat actors, collect and analyze signals through data analysis, and work with engineers to improve detection models and develop data driven mitigation strategies. Develop and test predictive models of feature abuse.<br>- Use all available internal and external data sources to produce actionable intelligence on high-harm threat actors, their networks, and threat organizations in the topic area of Influence Operations.<br>- Data mine threat actor behaviors and tactics.<br>- Apply structured analytic techniques, data science, and intelligence tradecraft to perform social network analysis of large attribute, ideational, and relational data sets to identify threat actor networks, critical nodes, and kill-chains.<br>- Work cross-functionally with product managers, program managers, security, operations, policy, and communications teams to address gaps in current threat response processes such as detection and mitigation.<br>- Collaborate with a team of global experts that respond to known threat actors and proactively build and tailor queries to discover and identify potential threats. <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> - Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, Economics, Business, other relevant fields, or equivalent experience.<br>- 3 years of experience conducting data-driven social network analysis for social media organizations, law enforcement, and/or intelligence community agencies.<br>- Experience should include discovering and correlating high-harm threat actors, networks, and organizations across global markets by performing quantitative and qualitative analysis of large data sets including attribute, ideational, and relational data.<br>- Intermediate understanding of descriptive statistics.<br>- Proficient in SQL or other relational database language.<br>- Able to create advanced data visualizations.<br><br>Preferred Qualifications<br>- Experience researching or analyzing global Influence Operations (IO) in order to identify, detect, and develop mitigation strategies against IO networks.  <br>- Independently troubleshoot technical issues or bugs<br>- Rapidly shift priorities based on evolving challenges to the platform <br>- Identify anomalous behavior and determine ways for further exploring new research leads<br>- Communicate complex concepts to broader stakeholders without shared expertise  <br>- 2 years of experience leading projects and managing stakeholder relationships.<br>- Project management skills to ensure impactful output, achieve stakeholder alignment, and manage competing priorities.<br>- Critical thinking skills with the ability to apply theorems or analytical techniques to discover insights that are not readily apparent<br><br>TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.<br><br>Accommodation Statement<br>TikTok is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation, please reach out to us at usds.accommodations@tiktokusds.com <br><br><strong>Job Information:<br><br></strong>【For Pay Transparency】Compensation Description (annually) <p>The base salary range for this position in the selected city is $106400 - $177777 annually.<span></span></p><p>Compensation may vary outside of this range depending on a number of factors, including a candidate’s qualifications, skills, competencies and experience, and location. Base pay is one part of the Total Package that is provided to compensate and recognize employees for their work, and this role may be eligible for additional discretionary bonuses/incentives, and restricted stock units.<span></span></p><p>Our company benefits are designed to convey company culture and values, to create an efficient and inspiring work environment, and to support our employees to give their best in both work and life. We offer the following benefits to eligible employees: <span></span></p><p>We cover 100% premium coverage for employee medical insurance, approximately 75% premium coverage for dependents and offer a Health Savings Account(HSA) with a company match. As well as Dental, Vision, Short/Long term Disability, Basic Life, Voluntary Life and AD&amp;D insurance plans. In addition to Flexible Spending Account(FSA) Options like Health Care, Limited Purpose and Dependent Care. <span></span></p><p>Our time off and leave plans are: 10 paid holidays per year plus 17 days of Paid Personal Time Off (PPTO) (prorated upon hire and increased by tenure) and 10 paid sick days per year as well as 12 weeks of paid Parental leave and 8 weeks of paid Supplemental Disability. <span></span></p><p>We also provide generous benefits like mental and emotional health benefits through our EAP and Lyra. A 401K company match, gym and cellphone service reimbursements. The Company reserves the right to modify or change these benefits programs at any time, with or without notice.<span></span></p>

<p>Are you ready to join a pioneering genomic-driven organization, who are transforming the landscape of personalized medicine and drug discovery on a global scale?</p><p><br></p><p>Quotacom are proudly partnered with a leading research and clinical diagnostics company, who are seeking a talented Lead Insights Analyst to drive their mission of improving global health through decoding genetic information.</p><p><br></p><p>The company are at the forefront of innovation, leveraging their deep understanding of diverse genomic and clinical data, combined with cutting edge technology, to reshape how leading pharmaceutical companies approach personalized medicine and drug discovery. Their aim to provide personalized healthcare that is affordable, inclusive, and equitable to all<em>. </em></p><p><br></p><p>They have received over $200+ million USD in funding to date and awarded the “Transformational Business Awards” &amp; “Biotechnology Start-Up of the Year” by the Financial Times, solidifying their position as leaders in Next Generation Sequencing and precision medicine.</p><p><br></p><p>As they enter the next phase of their growth to secure unicorn status, they are seeking a Lead Insights Analyst to provide crucial commercial and market insights that will not only guide market strategy plans, but also improve sales effectiveness and boost customer outreach.</p><p><br></p><p>You will be joining during an exciting period of rapid growth and at a pivotal point of maturation, as the business works to democratize personalized medicine and cement their place as a global leader within the field of genomics.</p><p><br></p><p>The ideal candidate will have:</p><ul><li>3+ years of experience in management consulting, investment banking, or corporate development.</li><li>Bachelor's or equivalent degree in Finance, Economics, Accounting, or related fields.</li><li>Track record of working with senior management teams and driving growth through strategic planning.</li><li>Exceptional Microsoft Office skills, especially in presentations and financial analysis.</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills.</li><li>Organization and time-management skills to handle multiple workstreams.</li><li>Ability to travel across the US and Internationally when needed.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>For full details and a discreet conversation on this opportunity, contact Katie on katie@quotacom.com</p><p><br></p><p><em>At Quotacom, we take the security and privacy of your personal data seriously; any data we hold will be in accordance with data protection legislation. Full details of our privacy notice can be found at https://quotacom.com/privacy-policy/</em></p>

desc: <strong>Hybrid: Fairfield, CA – 1 day onsite, must be under 60 mins commute<br><br></strong><strong>Need Valid LinkedIn<br><br></strong><strong>Need photo ID for USC and visa copy for GC holders(front + back) [ no info must be hidden/blacked out in the IDs]<br><br></strong><strong>Possible CTH role<br><br></strong><strong>Required Skills<br><br></strong><ul><li> SQL</li><li> Data mining w/ excel</li><li> Clinical or quality improvement or informatics or population health or healthcare data analyst</li><li> Clinical research data analysis<br><br></li></ul>Duties/Day to Day Overview<br><br><ul><li> The Senior Healthcare Data Analyst I contributes to the overall success of the organization by developing analytic solutions that support activities related to health services utilization management, care coordination, quality improvement and population health.</li><li> Through analyzing patient claims, member enrollment, and other data, the Senior Healthcare Data Analyst participates in identifying progress, performance and opportunities for improvement on programs, quality of care, patient experience, and other metrics.</li><li> Works collaboratively with business partners, other analysts, and IT to gather and integrate data from disparate sources.</li><li> Responds to ad hoc data requests from business units and leadership</li><li> Assists in design and development of data collection strategies, aggregation, analysis, and reporting to ensure data integrity and enhance information value.</li><li> Participates in design and interpretation of data analyses; provides recommendations for improvement of data quality and reporting.</li><li> Helps build, manage, and/or enhance predictive models</li><li> Assesses reporting and automation requirements and develops appropriate solutions.</li><li> Maintains in-depth knowledge of health plan operations, including claims processing, utilization management, quality improvement activities and pay for performance programs.</li><li> Critically analyzes data, draws conclusions and effectively articulates results.</li><li> Presents data and conclusions to non-technical audience; uses data visualizations and summaries to highlight key findings.</li><li> Creates and maintains thorough and consistent documentation of programs used to create reports.</li><li> Manages and prioritizes workload while meeting deliverables and expectations. - Works autonomously and collaboratively with report requestors, providing guidance to define report requirements and validate results.</li><li> Works collaboratively across departments to understand and meet the organization’s analytic needs<br><br></li></ul>Top Requirements<br><br>(Must haves)<br><br><ul><li> This position requires a thorough understanding of healthcare data and workflows, combined with an extensive experience working with large data sets, conducting data analysis, including standard statistical software (SAS), and creating reports using Tableau.</li><li> Bachelor’s degree with concentration in health informatics, health administration, public health, computing, epidemiology, statistics or related field, Master’s degree preferred.</li><li> Minimum four (4) years of experience in data analysis and reporting. </li><li> Knowledge of major health plan operations: healthcare claims processing, membership, provider, and benefits; or equivalent combination of education and experience. </li><li> Excellent knowledge of data collection, analysis, statistics and data presentation with experience in data mining techniques and procedures. </li><li> Experience using statistical packages for analyzing large data sets, SAS and/or SQL a plus.</li><li> Experience working with administrative data, ideally health care data (Medicaid data a plus). Understanding of health data formats including claims, lab and pharmacy. Knowledge of clinical coding systems (e.g., ICD9, ICD10, CPT).</li><li> Proficiency in inferential and predictive statistical analysis. <strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong> TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. <br>Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day. <br>To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always. <br>At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve. <br>Join us.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone entity of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security &amp; Privacy, Engineering, User &amp; Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>In order to enhance collaboration and cross-functional partnerships, among other things, at this time, our organization follows a hybrid work schedule that requires employees to work in the office 2 days a week, or as directed by their manager/department. We regularly review our hybrid work model, and the specific requirements may change at any time.<br><br>About the Role<br>The primary role of a Data Analyst is to conduct deep analysis into user behavior, product features and content ecosystem to generate business insights that could be applied to actionable improving initiatives. You will work closely with cross-function teams, such as DS\PM\RD\MLE, to improve user experience and fulfill growth of TikTok in all different regions.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>- Keep track of key metrics and investigate metrics movement to identify root causes.<br>- Drive insightful understanding of TikTok user and creator ecosystem.<br>- Design and analyze experiments to verify product hypothesis and direction.<br>- Audit quality of launch experiment results and guarantee correct measurement of product or technical changes' impact. <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> Qualifications<br>• Bachelor or Master degree in statistics, econometrics, quantitative sociology or a related scientific major, with 2+ years of related work experience;<br>• Expertise in SQL<br>• Strong analytical and causal reasoning mindset, and rigidity on statistical correctness;<br>• Strong communication and teamwork skills.<br>• Passion about social products and curiosity to deep dive.<br><br>TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.<br><br>TikTok is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws.
