JOB POSTING<br><br>Student Health Services is excited about a new position, Project Data Analyst. If you love data and project management and you are interested in working at a local university in the redwoods look no further. As the Project Data Analyst you will provide key support on behalf of the Associate Vice Chancellor of Student Health Services (SHS). Under the direction of the Operations and Financial Managers, you will provide support for critical projects such as unit-wide incident reporting, and policy and procedure management within the UC reporting and proprietary systems. As Project Data Analyst you will also be responsible for in-depth data and financial analysis and fund management.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong>As the largest employer in the county, rated as one of the most beautiful campuses, located on the coast overlooking Monterey Bay. UC Santa Cruz employs over 3,100 people in staff positions alone. UC Santa Cruz staff have access to comprehensive benefits packages. Here is a sample of those benefits:<br><br><ul><li> Medical, Dental &amp; Vision Care Insurance Plans</li><li> UC Retirement Plans</li><li> Group Term Life Insurance</li><li> Legal Insurance</li><li> Pet Insurance</li><li> 14 Paid Holidays plus accrued vacation and sick leave</li><li> Reduced fees for alternative methods of transportation</li><li> Discount at UCSC recreation facilities<br><br></li></ul>For information on the comprehensive benefits package offered by the university visit: https://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/compensation-and-benefits/index.html.<br><br>The selected candidate may have the option to work a hybrid remote schedule. If a hybrid remote schedule is approved, the selected candidate must be able to successfully work from a home/remote office and fulfill the requirements of the UCSC telecommuting agreement.<br><br>Thank you for your interest in UC Santa Cruz.<br><br><strong>NOTIFICATIONS<br><br></strong>The University of California has implemented a Vaccination Policy covering all employees. Employees, including new hires, are required to comply with any applicable policies relating to the University of California's COVID-19 vaccine program.<br><br><strong>How To Apply<br><br></strong>For full consideration, all applications must be submitted directly through the UC Santa Cruz jobs portal at jobs.ucsc.edu . Applicants should include a resume and cover letter, and apply by the initial review date listed below.<br><br>The Search Firm, Another Source, is assisting UC Santa Cruz in this search. Interested parties seeking more information before applying are encouraged to reach out to Another Source by emailing taylor@anothersource.com . Qualified applicants will be contacted directly by Another Source both during and after the IRD period to discuss the position and schedule interviews.<br><br>For guidance related to the application process or if you are experiencing difficulties when applying, please review the Applicant Resources on our Talent Acquisition website.<br><br><ul><li> How to Apply </li><li> Troubleshooting </li><li> Tips for Applicants </li><li> FAQ’s <br><br></li></ul><strong>INITIAL REVIEW DATE (IRD)<br><br></strong>Application materials submitted by 11:59 pm on the IRD will be routed to the hiring unit for consideration. Materials submitted after the IRD will ONLY be forwarded at the request of the hiring unit. To ensure your application is routed for consideration, submit your materials before 11:59 p.m. on the IRD. Talent Acquisition cannot accept application materials outside of the jobs portal, and is unable to update submitted applications on an applicant's behalf, or forward communications to the hiring units. For more information about the IRD and the applicant review process, view this link .<br><br>The IRD for this job is: <strong> 10-02-2023<br><br></strong><strong>About Uc Santa Cruz<br><br></strong>UC Santa Cruz is a public university like no other in California, combining the experience of a small, liberal arts college with the depth and rigor of a major research university. It's known as an unconventional place where innovation and experimentation is part of the campus's DNA. That playful, bold spirit still thrives today, all on a campus renowned as among the most beautiful in the world.<br><br><strong>Department Overview<br><br></strong>UC Santa Cruz (UCSC) Student Health Services (SHS) is a full-service medical facility offering clinical, educational, and psychological support to UCSC students. SHS is deeply committed to ensuring affordable, well-integrated, multidisciplinary healthcare that effectively supports the university's diverse campus communities through equitable access and culturally competent, high-quality programs and services.<br><br>The Primary Care Program includes primary care and same-day care, with the support of on-site radiology, a COLA-accredited high-complexity clinical laboratory, and the campus pharmacy. Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS) supports UCSC students to maintain or improve their general well-being by providing a broad range of counseling, psychiatric services, consultation, and outreach services and programs. Other departments include Student Health Outreach and Promotion (SHOP), home of the Condom Co-op; CARE (Campus Advocacy, Resources, and Education) the advocacy and prevention education office that supports survivors of sexual assault, stalking, and dating/domestic violence; and Student Insurance Programs.<br><br>SHS employs approximately 130 staff including physicians, psychiatrists, case managers, lab scientists, pharmacists, nurses, radiologists, and many other clinical and administrative staff. Student Health Services welcomes staff with interest and experience in working with students with a wide range of ethnic, cultural, and gender identities.<br><br>More information can be found at: https://healthcenter.ucsc.edu<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>The Project Data Analyst provides key support on behalf of the Associate Vice Chancellor of Student Health Services (SHS). Under the direction of the Operations and Financial Managers, this position provides support for critical projects such as unit-wide incident reporting and policy and procedure management within UC reporting and proprietary systems. The position will also be responsible for in-depth data and financial analysis and fund management.<br><br>The Project Data Analyst is expected to apply theory and put into practice an in-depth understanding of concepts related to the analysis of data and systems pertaining to complex projects, policies, initiatives, processes, and/or functions, requiring facilitation and collaboration with representation within SHS, across the division and the campus, and expanding to UC Office of the President in relation to project management. The incumbent is also responsible for the implementation, staff training, and ongoing management of key systems required by the UC Office of the President and AAAHC accrediting body compliance.<br><br>The Project Data Analyst oversees the UC-wide Risk Services incident reporting system designed to record, manage and resolve incidents related to medical and mental health clinical care, facilities, health information management, information technology, privacy, and security, among others. They also oversee the proprietary document management system which holds all SHS policies, procedures, and related reference materials and monitors required employee compliance, and coordinate the document management system integration with the Accreditation Association for Ambulatory Health Care, Inc. (AAAHC) and compliance with AAAHC standards in preparation for periodic accreditation reviews.<br><br><strong>APPOINTMENT INFORMATION<br><br></strong><strong>Budgeted Salary:</strong> <strong> $95,000 - $125,000/annually. </strong>Salary commensurate with skills, qualifications and experience.<br><br>Under California law, the University of California, Santa Cruz is required to post a reasonable estimate of the compensation for this role. The salary shown above is the budgeted amount the University reasonably expects to pay and the salary extended should not exceed this posted amount.<br><br><strong>Benefits Level Eligibility:</strong> Full benefits<br><br><strong>Schedule Information<br><br></strong><ul><li> Full-time, Fixed </li><li> Percentage of Time: 100%, 40 Hours per Week </li><li> Days of the Week: Mon-Fri </li><li> Shift Includes: Day <br><br></li></ul><strong>Employee Classification:</strong> Career appointment<br><br><strong>Job End Date:</strong> None<br><br><strong>Work Location:</strong> UC Santa Cruz Main Campus, with the possibility of working a hybrid remote schedule<br><br><strong>Union Representation:</strong> Non-Represented<br><br><strong>Job Code Classification:</strong> 007399 (PROJECT POLICY ANL 4)<br><br><strong>Travel:</strong> Never or Rarely<br><br><strong>Job Duties<br><br></strong><strong>25% - Policy and Procedure System Administrator<br><br></strong>Student Health Services (SHS) utilizes, PowerDMS, a document management system that holds all SHS policies, procedures, and related reference materials, has the capacity to track employee compliance with policy review as well as other trainings, and has an integration with our accrediting body, the Accreditation Association for Ambulatory Health Care, Inc. (AAAHC) which facilitates and documents compliance with AAAHC standards in preparation for period accreditation reviews.<br><br><ul><li> Facilitates creation and editing of policies and procedures including uploading supporting attachments. Facilitates creation and implementation of various staff trainings that can be delivered and documented via PowerDMS </li><li> Creates workflows for document review and ensures timely completion of annual reviews and approvals of policies. </li><li> Assumes administrator responsibilities within the PowerDMS and serves as an expert user of the system. After completing PowerDMS training, actively participates in the PowerDMS community forums to support our implementation and ensure best practices are being followed. </li><li> Maintains user accounts and ensures timely addition and removal of new and terminating staff to remain within license limits. </li><li> Participates in various clinical and administrative meetings and workgroups where policies are presented or created and support the SHS management team. </li><li> Trains all staff on the use of the system and trains managers who are responsible for reviewing and sign-off off policies on an annual basis. This includes periodic training for all staff as well as onboarding of new staff. </li><li> Participates in AAAHC accreditation meetings and creates and manages the assessment feature where SHW policies and procedures are mapped to the current AAAHC standards in preparation for periodic site visits and re-accreditation. <br><br></li></ul><strong>20% - Data Management and Analysis<br><br></strong><ul><li> Contributes to the implementation of business and administrative initiatives and special projects. </li><li> Performs analytical studies on a wide variety of policies, programs, and issues which are complex in nature. </li><li> Engages in the research process and implementation of special projects under the direction / in collaboration with the AVC SH&amp;W, Administrative, and Financial Managers. </li><li> Creates projected financial scenarios in response to changes in university, division, and unit goals and objectives and reorganizations such as long-term facility, information technology, clinical and staffing needs. </li><li> Compiles statistics. Prepares trend analyses and creates predictive modeling in support of the needs of leadership including the analyses of administrative, financial, and organizational data. </li><li> Builds reports to provide timely and accurate data to support organizational activities. </li><li> Disseminates data to staff through the use of Tableau graphs, tables, PowerPoint presentations, and other visuals. <br><br></li></ul><strong>20% - Incident Reporting / Risk Management<br><br></strong>The RLDatix incident reporting system is a UC-wide system used by Risk Services to record, manage and resolve incidents that represent a risk to the organization. For Student Health and Wellness, this includes incidents related to medical and mental health clinical care, facilities, health information management, information technology, privacy, and security, among others.<br><br><ul><li> Manages all aspects of the RLDatix system including tracking incoming incident and patient feedback reports, reviewing all incidents in a timely manner, and tasks to appropriate managers or supervisors for review, investigation, documentation, and resolution, ensuring tasks are finalized in a timely manner. </li><li> Functions as a report writer within the system with sufficient proficiency to create and produce reports of incidents as needed for management including reports by type of incident, outcomes, severity, open tasks, and closed incidents. Responsible for preparing reports for Quality Management and Governing Body committees. </li><li> Develops and/or maintains policies related to incident reporting and risk management. </li><li> Maintains user accounts within the system including the creation of new accounts and termination of accounts via notification to UC system administrator. </li><li> Trains all staff on the use of the system and related policies, and supports users as they submit, investigate, document, and resolve incidents. This includes periodic training for all staff as well as onboarding of new staff. <br><br></li></ul><strong>20% - Fund Management and Analysis<br><br></strong><ul><li> Ensures fund use is in accordance with University policy. Monitors activity and audits work to ensure compliance with campus and system-wide controls, guidelines, policies, and deadlines. Determines, designs, and maintains tracking, reporting, and auditing systems, as needed. </li><li> Develops and prepares fiscal analyses and documentation for budget submittals and requests; Collects, compiles, and analyzes salary and incumbent data to produce cost estimates for short and long-term staffing budget projections. </li><li> Manages various fund sources and expenditures and prepares transfers of expense in campus systems; reconciles funding suspense reports and payroll distribution reports. <br><br></li></ul><strong>15% - Data Systems Administration<br><br></strong><ul><li> Serves as an expert user with data systems. </li><li> Utilizes and develops expertise in specialized systems, including but not limited to Tableau, PNC, ProPharm, Qualtrics, Survey Monkey, and Artemis Analytics. </li><li> Utilizes and develops expertise in campus systems, including but not limited to UCPATH, Financial Manager’s Workbench (FMW), and Infoview to provide reports and analyses related to historic, current, and future resource allocation and utilization. </li><li> Develops tools and reports for future utilization; trains staff to fully utilize systems as needed. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Bachelor's degree in related area and / or equivalent experience / training. </li><li> Strong skills in analyzing, researching and synthesizing large amounts of data for preparing sound and relevant reports. </li><li> Thorough knowledge of data management and documentation methods. </li><li> Demonstrated knowledge of data analysis, research and reporting. </li><li> Proven ability to apply external regulatory guidelines and internal accounting and administrative policies knowledge and skills to assess and monitor compliance and effectiveness of processes. </li><li> Strong communication and interpersonal skills to communicate effectively with all levels of staff. </li><li> Ability to use discretion and maintain confidentiality. </li><li> Demonstrated proficiency in using and managing administrative systems, applications and databases. </li><li> Ability to multi-task with demanding timeframes. </li><li> Strong policy analysis techniques. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Experience and knowledge working in a complex clinical environment. </li><li> Experience with Tableau or other data management systems. <br><br></li></ul><strong>SPECIAL CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT<br><br></strong><ul><li> Selected candidate will be required to pass a pre-employment criminal history background check. </li><li> Will be required to comply with current Student Health Center employee health safety requirements for health care workers as defined by state and federal regulatory agencies. </li><li> The selected candidate may have the option to work a hybrid remote schedule. If a hybrid remote schedule is approved, the selected candidate must be able to successfully work from a home/remote office and fulfill the requirements of the UCSC telecommuting agreement. </li><li> Ability to work long periods of time at a computer with or without accommodation. </li><li> Selected candidate will be required to take a TB test within 60 days of hire. </li><li> Selected candidate will be required to complete training within established time frames as directed including UC compliance training. </li><li> Per the Child Abuse and Neglect Reporting Act (CANRA), this position has been identified as a Mandated Reporter. The selected candidate will be required to report known or suspected child abuse or neglect as defined by CANRA and will be required to sign a Statement Acknowledging Requirement to Report Child Abuse prior to commencing employment. CANRA Penal Codes, and related definitions, requirements, and responsibilities may be obtained here . <br><br></li></ul><strong>SAFETY STATEMENT<br><br></strong>All UCSC employees must understand and follow job safety procedures, attend required health and safety training, proactively promote safety at work, and promptly report actual and potential accidents and injuries.<br><br><strong>EEO/AA<br><br></strong>The University of California is an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, age, or protected veteran status. UC Santa Cruz is committed to excellence through diversity and strives to establish a climate that welcomes, celebrates, and promotes respect for the contributions of all students and employees.

We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone department of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security &amp; Privacy, Engineering, User &amp; Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>About the team<br>We are a team of passionate Data Analysts, Data Scientists, and Operations who safeguard TikTok's US user data and join forces with cross-functional teams to derive actionable insights from US user data to maximize monetization results while still giving users a pleasant experience in our app. <br><br>We are looking for data analysts to join the efforts driving monetization, <br>- Apply expertise in data analysis and visualization to see beyond the numbers and understand how our users interact with our ads products.<br>- Deliver data support for both short term and long term business development plans from strategic scope and execution aspects with in-depths analysis.<br>- Work closely with key cross functional teams such as product managers, data science, and engineers to solve business problems.<br>- Build/maintain reports, dashboards, and metrics to monitor the performance of business products.<br>- This is an individual contributor role, but will be expected to manage projects. <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> - Bachelor's degree with a background in Math, Economics, Computer Science, Statistics, or other quantitative fields;<br>- 5 years experience of Data Analytics.<br>- Expert experience pulling large and complex data using SQL and writing data pipelines. <br>- Experience with a data visualization tool (e.g. Tableau);<br><br>Prefer to Have<br>- Experience doing quantitative analysis;<br>- Development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl, etc.); At Netflix, our mission is to entertain the world. With 200+ million paid members in over 190 countries on millions of devices, enjoying TV series, documentaries, and feature films across a wide variety of genres and languages, Netflix is reinventing entertainment from end to end. We are revolutionizing how shows and movies are produced, pushing technological boundaries to efficiently deliver streaming video at a massive scale over the internet, and continuously improving the end-to-end user experience with Netflix across their member journey.<br><br>The Device pod within the Streaming Data Engineering team partners with multiple engineering teams, producing high-quality and large-scale datasets, a source of truth for how Netflix services operate on the vast landscape of devices that support Netflix. This team helps to create datasets used to certify and retire devices, categorize them, and identify changes in this constantly changing environment.<br><br>This role is focused on supporting Netflix’s core data assets, delivering high-quality business datasets and metrics, and building systems to process batch and real-time data at a large scale. Additionally, a candidate should have a rich understanding of large distributed systems, modern big data technologies, and software development techniques. Since data engineers are responsible for their pipelines at Netflix, this role requires engineers to take ownership of the operational excellence in their domain. In addition, the ideal candidate will have excellent data intuition and share our passion for continuously improving how we handle streaming data at Netflix.<br><br>Who are you?<br><br><br><ul><li>You strive to write elegant code and are comfortable with independently picking up new technologies.</li><li>You have mastery over at least one major programming language (e.g., Java, Scala, Python) and are comfortable working with SQL.</li><li>You enjoy helping teams push the boundaries of analytical insights, creating new product features using data, and powering machine-learning models.</li><li>You have a strong background in at least one of the following: distributed data processing or software engineering of data services.</li><li>You are familiar with big data technologies like Spark and Flink and comfortable working with web-scale datasets.</li><li>You are passionate about the end-to-end software development lifecycle, focusing on automation, testing, CI/CD, and documentation.</li><li>At Netflix, you own your code, services, and pipelines. You have practical, solid DevOps and Operation fundamentals, and you enjoy total ownership of your domain.</li><li>You have a solid understanding of the device lifecycle. You have an eye for detail, good data intuition, and a passion for data quality.</li><li>You relate to and embody many of the aspects of the Netflix Culture</li><li>You love working independently while also collaborating and giving/receiving candid feedback.</li><li>You are comfortable working in a rapidly changing environment with ambiguous requirements. You are nimble and take intelligent risks.<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>What You Will Do<br><br><br></strong><ul><li>Help Netflix support and evolve the device data model by improving data excellence and quality, supporting analytics, developing and maintaining metrics, and partnering with engineering to deliver the next generation of Netflix experiences.</li><li>Engineer efficient, adaptable, and scalable data pipelines to process structured and unstructured data </li><li>Partner with numerous engineering teams, analytics engineers, and data scientists to enhance playback-related datasets. Maintain and rethink existing pipelines to improve scalability and maintainability.<br><br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Here Are a Few More Things To Know<br><br><br></strong><ul><li>Our culture is unique, and we live by our values, so it's worth learning more about Netflix at jobs.netflix.com/culture. You will need to be nimble and take smart risks.<br><br><br></li></ul>At Netflix, we carefully consider a wide range of compensation factors to determine your personal top of market. This market range is based on total compensation (vs. only base salary), which is in line with our compensation philosophy. Netflix is a unique culture and environment. <strong>About Probably Genetic<br><br></strong>Probably Genetic is changing the lives of patients living with severe, complex diseases. Our data platform is used by drug developers and patient advocacy groups to develop and launch treatments for these patients. Our technology discovers undiagnosed patients online, analyzes their disease state using machine learning and at-home testing, and enables compliant communication with patients. In doing so, we help patients access diagnoses, clinical trials, and treatments as early as possible.<br><br>We are a tight-knit group of hard-working, ambitious problem solvers united by a mission greater than ourselves.<br><br>We do well by doing right by patients. Our annually recurring revenue is growing &gt;6x year over year, we’re profitable, and our roadmap is packed with innovations in bioinformatics, machine learning, and drug development. We are building an all-star team to help us bring our vision to life, and we want you to be a part of it.<br><br>Probably Genetic has raised multiple rounds of funding from Silicon Valley’s best investors, including Threshold, Khosla, and Y Combinator, giving us the ability to pay competitive salaries, offer great benefits, and provide meaningful equity. We’re dedicated to ensuring your journey with us is unforgettable, with incredible team retreats to places like Barbados, the Alps, Mexico, Costa Rica, and Portugal, just to name a few.<br><br><strong>About The Role<br><br></strong>We are looking for a Data Engineer to build data pipelines and visualizations for key business metrics, machine learning (ML) models, and growth metrics to enable our data-driven organization.<br><br>What you will do<br><br>In this role, you will have the unique opportunity to use data to provide life-changing services, including genetic tests, to patients living with severe, complex diseases. This involves building data infrastructure to assess patient acquisition channel quality, ML training pipelines, and dashboards for business metrics driving all company decisions. You will own pipelines end-to-end while building beautiful visualizations and dashboards. You will play a pivotal role in enabling Probably Genetic to use our data to grow the business.<br><br>You will drive the Probably Genetic data infrastructure by:<br><br><ul><li>Collaborating with stakeholders in Business Development, Growth, Product, ML and Finance to design data visualizations and pipelines</li><li>Developing ETL pipelines from a PostreSQL database using Python Django and AWS services such as S3, Glue, and Athena</li><li>Integrating with external data sources such as Meta and Google Ad platforms, product analytics platforms, and financial platforms to extract valuable data and insights</li><li>Developing visualizations in a business intelligence (BI) tool of your choice to create reports and dashboards<br><br></li></ul>You will collaborate internally to achieve data and company goals by:<br><br><ul><li>Collaborating directly with the CEO and executive team on investor updates using data from BI reports and dashboards</li><li>Identifying missing data points which should be collected and working with the engineering team to collect all valuable data</li><li>Writing documentation to onboard team members to BI tooling and ensuring that datasets are available for ad-hoc analysis<br><br></li></ul>Who you are<br><br>What will help you succeed in this role:<br><br><ul><li>5+ years of relevant experience in data engineering</li><li>Experience using Python and SQL for ETL pipelines and data analysis</li><li>Experience in data reporting and dashboarding using variety of BI tools</li><li>Track-record of solving extremely difficult, ambiguous problems<br><br></li></ul>Some things that are not required, but you will learn on the job:<br><br><ul><li>Experience in contributing to a Python Django backend</li><li>Expertise with healthcare data, bioinformatics, ML infrastructure, or growth marketing<br><br></li></ul>As with all new hires at Probably Genetic, you will also need to be:<br><br><ul><li>A good person. We work with some of the most marginalized populations on the planet and empathy is key</li><li>Patient-focused and motivated to have a lasting, positive impact on humanity</li><li>Comfortable in a fast-paced, often ambiguous environment with rapid change</li><li>Action-oriented and excited to build a company from the ground up<br><br></li></ul>The salary range for this role is $127,000-$195,000 annually. Actual compensation offered will depend on several factors including but not limited to: work experience, education, skill level, and/or other business and organizational needs.<br><br><strong>What we offer at Probably Genetic:<br><br></strong><ul><li>An engaging and supportive team</li><li>30 days of vacation a year</li><li>Hybrid, flexible work</li><li>A “work from anywhere” policy, up to 4 weeks a year</li><li>Competitive equity grants</li><li>All-expenses paid quarterly team retreats</li><li>Benefits including medical and vision<br><br></li></ul><strong>This is a hybrid role that will require working on-site 3 days a week in San Francisco. Local candidates only. Relocation is not offered for this role.<br><br></strong><em>Probably Genetic is committed to fostering a welcoming and inclusive work environment for people of all genders, sexuality, ethnicity, socioeconomic background and life experiences. We urge candidates of all backgrounds to apply. If you require specific accommodations as you interview or consider working with us, please let us know.<br><br></em>Compensation Range: $127K - $195K

desc: <strong>Overview<br><br></strong>Intuit’s People Analytics, Research, and Technology (PART) team is looking for a Principal People Insights Partners to provide business-facing people analytics to senior leadership. This role will lead enterprise people analytics projects and actively seek to influence C-Suite leaders through data-driven insights and strategy. We are looking for a professional who is passionate, innovative, thoughtful and eager to make a big impact on both our people strategy and the business.<br><br>You will partner closely with senior HR and business leaders to deliver on Intuit’s vision of accelerating great people decisions through data. You will partner closely with colleagues across all areas of the Intuit People organization including talent development, talent acquisition, compensation, workforce strategy and more. In addition, you will work closely with HR business partners and business leaders in leveraging data to help inform our company-wide people strategies and achieve our mission of ‘maximizing the potential of our employees’ in order to accelerate Intuit's business growth.<br><br><strong>What You'll Bring<br><br></strong><ul><li>Ability to generate people insights that go beyond the surface of the data, in order to help stakeholders understand the underlying "why" and what to do about it</li><li>Ability to take complex analyses and insights and present them in a way that is digestible and relevant to your stakeholders</li><li>Expertise in analyzing and interpreting people-related data (i.e. advanced degree or equivalent experience/expertise in Psychology, Sociology, Industrial/Organizational Psychology, Economics or other people-focused field)</li><li>Two or more years of experience working in People Analytics, Talent Management, Organizational Development and/or Consulting to organizations</li><li>Strong understanding of the HR landscape (e.g., functions and processes) and existing challenges and best practices</li><li>Experience presenting to senior executives or stakeholders</li><li>Basic proficiency in statistics (i.e. ability to explain and answer questions about data analyses, results, and conduct tests of statistical significance)</li><li>Fluent in Excel and at least one scripting language (i.e. R, Python) with the ability to automate repetitive, manual work</li><li>Ability to influence and build strong relationships with stakeholders at all levels, while managing expectations appropriately</li><li>Success in managing project timelines and task assignments to ensure successful completion of the project within scope and on schedule</li><li>Effective communicator - ability to articulate clear messages to team members, stakeholders, and vendors</li><li>Possess an orientation for results and excellence, demonstrating conceptual and analytical thinking, initiative, and flexibility<br><br></li></ul><strong>How You Will Lead<br><br></strong><ul><li>Deeply understand Intuit’s business and people strategies and how they can be strategically shaped through people analytics</li><li>Collaborate closely with HR leaders and business leaders on enterprise people analytics projects, both recurring and ad-hoc; design and execute these projects in such a way that delivers tangible value to the business</li><li>Drive monthly analysis and insights reporting to the C-Suite regarding Intuit’s overall progress on key people metrics and talent initiatives</li><li>Drive bi-annual analysis, insights and strategic recommendations to the C-Suite regarding business-specific progress on talent strategy</li><li>Act as a subject matter expert to HR and business leaders on high-priority projects </li><li>Learn from and collaborate with other Insights Partners and mentor junior analysts on the team</li><li>Provide end-to-end partnership on leveraging people analytics to accelerate business growth, from diagnosis to recommendations and gauging the impact of any changes made</li><li>Collaborate with the various People &amp; Places teams to develop and maintain robust benchmarks on key people metrics</li><li>Continuously stay on top of emerging people analytics trends and bring in outside-in thinking and industry best practices to enhance the impact of your work</li><li>Role model the mindsets of pragmatic optimism, continuous experimentation and learning and growth</li></ul>

<p>Venable LLP’s Technology &amp; Innovation Group seeks a Privacy Data Analyst to join the Venable Blue team in the Washington, D.C., New York, Los Angeles, or San Francisco office. The Privacy Data Analyst, works on and supports all aspects of client-based projects related to privacy program management, privacy operations, and regulatory response. This is a non-attorney position.</p><p><br></p><p>This role will help bring efficiency to how clients respond to regulatory compliance requests, including data gathering, automation of regulatory responses, and measuring operational effectiveness of privacy safeguards. This will include gap analysis and actionable recommendations for improvements in quality and accuracy.</p><p><br></p><p>The Privacy Data Analyst will work on and support the delivery of various workstreams such as Safeguard Maintenance, Safeguard Development, Program Management, and Audit Support.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Key responsibilities include working with clients to:</strong></p><ul><li>Formulate responses to privacy compliance requests within SLA, perform data quality reviews, and conduct operational effectiveness testing against privacy safeguards.</li><li>Develop and communicate best practices for regulatory response.</li><li>Develop automation for compliance responses to increase efficiency and to provide consistency and quality in responses.</li><li>Articulate data and technology gaps and their compliance impact to a variety of technical and non-technical stakeholders, including product and engineering teams, risk and compliance partners, assessors and regulators.</li><li>Recommend process improvements and strategic initiatives as related to privacy compliance response.</li><li>Coordinate and drive client privacy response activities for both inbound and outbound relationships.</li><li>Support business relationships with internal and external auditors and regulators.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>B.A. or B.S. degree; Master’s degree (or equivalent) preferred</li><li>3 years of minimum work experience in high profile settings, such as presenting to leadership and driving cross-functional teams</li><li>3 years of minimum experience in a quantitative role related to data, reporting, and analytical problem solving</li><li>3 years of minimum experience writing complex SQL queries to drive analysis and insights</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience coding in Python, R, PHP and/or similar programming language</li><li>Experience with developing security/privacy reporting and recommendations that are meaningful, defensible and actionable for a variety of audiences</li><li>Experience developing and submitting audit and compliance reports to governing bodies, legal entities, and/or external authorities</li><li>Experienced in processes for assessing and designing internal controls for large scale organizations</li><li>Experience performing risk assessments or safeguard/control operational effectiveness testing</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Venable offers full-service solutions to everything from routine to novel privacy and cybersecurity challenges. Our team brings to bear significant experience and industry knowledge to help clients satisfy data privacy and security laws and maximize their business potential. Fully immersed in all aspects of data privacy, cybersecurity, and information governance, Venable is unique among privacy and cybersecurity practices.</p><p><br></p><p>We participate in legislative advocacy, rulemakings, and development of new legal standards. Our team advises organizations with regard to industry best practices and drafting codes of conduct and standards, helping them stay compliant with federal, state, international, and self-regulatory requirements.</p><p><br></p><p>We strengthen the integrity of our clients’ data, ecommerce security, and customer or user records; develop internal data collection and use practices; and ensure the creation of sound privacy policies and procedures.</p><p><br></p><p>Venable Blue helps organizations and individuals manage and mitigate risk in the online space. Whether it’s an issue of data access, account takeover, cyber harassment, child safety, or a government or regulatory investigation, we build, operationalize, and deploy integrated programs and systems designed with people and products in mind.</p><p><br></p><p>For additional information about the Technology &amp; Innovation Group, Venable Blue team see: www.venableblue.com</p><p><br></p><p>Venable LLP is an <em>American Lawyer</em> Global 100 law firm headquartered in Washington, D.C., with offices in California, Delaware, Florida, Illinois, Maryland, New York, and Virginia. Additional information can be found at Venable.com.</p><p><br></p><p><em>The salary range for Privacy Data Analyst positions is $85,000 - $130,000, depending upon relevant experience, education, other related considerations, and needs of the organization</em></p><p><br></p><p><em>We comply with the Los Angeles Fair Chance Initiative for Hiring and the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance. position is a minimum of $119,000 and a maximum of $161,000. <br><br><br></li></ul>About Us:<br><br>Natron Energy (natron.energy) is the future of energy storage. Situated in Stanford’s highly dynamic research environment the Curtis Laboratory (http://med.stanford.edu/curtislab.html), led by Christina Curtis, PhD, is seeking a bioinformatician/Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Cancer Computational and Systems Biology group. The Curtis Laboratory is administratively situated within the Stanford Cancer Institute and is integrated within Stanford University and the School of Medicine’s Departments of Medicine (Oncology) and Genetics. The SCI is part of a Comprehensive National Cancer Institute Cancer Center for cross-disciplinary research in cancer biology involving researchers from oncology, radiobiology, computer science, genetics, statistics, and basic/translational clinical research. Our research couples state-of-the-art computational and experimental techniques to define novel therapeutic targets and biomarkers and to characterize tumor evolution.<br><br>The successful candidate will be part of an interdisciplinary research team developing novel technological and methodological approaches to improve the diagnosis, treatment and earlier detection of cancer. He/she will analyze and interpret large sequencing datasets by applying and developing bioinformatics and statistical methods for whole genome/exome sequencing, RNA-seq, ATAC-seq, single cell and spatial datasets. The successful candidate will interact closely with other computational and experimental biologists and clinicians to test, validate, and refine hypotheses. This is a fantastic opportunity for a motivated bioinformatician or computational genomicist to join a dynamic team with significant opportunities for scholarship.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br></strong><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets.</li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data.</li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions.</li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation.</li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> - Other duties may also be assigned<br><br></li></ul><strong>Desired Qualifications<br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Bioinformatics, Computer Science or a related field with one year (min) of relevant experience </li><li>Strong background in bioinformatics and biostatistics, including analysis of high-throughput sequencing data</li><li>Experience working within a UNIX/Linux environment</li><li>Fluency in programming languages such as Perl, Python, Java, R, C, Matlab; MySQL</li><li>Excellent communication and team skills and fluency in both spoken and written English</li><li>Familiarity with machine learning, information theory and signal processing.</li><li>Experience with algorithm development</li><li>Familiarity with basic molecular biology</li><li>Background in cancer biology<br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; We started Bloom Institute of Technology because we believe that the “traditional” model of higher education is broken. Every year, people as young as 17 years old take on tens of thousands of dollars in student debt and pray that the education they’re investing in will land them on a job on the other side.<br><br><br><br>Unfortunately, traditional colleges and universities have no incentive to ensure their graduates get hired – they get paid regardless.<br><br><br><br>At BloomTech, we believe there is a better way to approach education.<br><br>Instead of asking our students to bet on us, we bet on them first. This paradigm-shifting model allows us to align the incentives of the school with the incentives of our students – and we all win when our graduates succeed.<br><br><br><br>We’re in this together.<br><br>If that sounds exciting to you, let’s talk. Our success depends on building teams who can challenge each other's assumptions with fresh perspectives. To that end, we don’t just accept differences – we celebrate them. BloomTech welcomes a diverse pool of applicants, including those from historically marginalized groups and non-traditional backgrounds who can appreciate the diverse student communities that we serve and are looking to grow into. This includes women, people with disabilities, people of color, formerly incarcerated people, individuals who are lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer and/or gender nonconforming, first and second generation immigrants, veterans, and people from different socioeconomic backgrounds.<br><br><strong>What You'll Do<br><br></strong><ul><li>Available shift: Part-Time, including evenings and weekends AM/PM shift (The working hours for this role are 29 hours a week including weekend availability)</li><li>Assist with Academic Unblocking: Offer technical support for learners in Data Science through various communication channels such as phone, SMS, Slack, and Zoom</li><li>Proactive Academic Support: Provide daily proactive academic assistance to learners, ensuring they receive the guidance they need to excel in their course</li><li>Progress Documentation: Document and report on learner progress, touchpoints, and achievements, maintaining accurate records to assess their development effectively and recommend interventions whenever necessary</li><li>Learner Support: Offer support to learners through Live Chat and Support Tickets using Salesforce, addressing their queries and concerns promptly and meeting all SLAs</li><li>One-on-One Instruction: Review the academic progress of learners and deliver personalized feedback and guidance in one-on-one meetings, helping them overcome challenges and improve their performance</li><li>Cross-Functional Collaboration: Collaborate regularly with other teams dedicated to learner success, fostering a collaborative environment to enhance the overall learner experience. Use your firsthand experience with learners to provide ongoing, actionable, and documented feedback to relevant teams for implementation</li><li>Knowledge Base Maintenance: Write, edit, and maintain knowledge base articles to create a comprehensive resource for learners and support staff</li><li>Additional Responsibilities: Fulfill any other duties as requested, contributing to the overall success of the program<br><br></li></ul><strong>What You'll Need<br><br></strong><ul><li>1-3 years of experience in the tech industry in a Data Science or Data Analyst role</li><li>Ability to explain complex technical concepts to a novice; strong empathy for learners</li><li>Process-oriented with exceptional attention to detail</li><li>Excellent written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills in English </li><li>Extremely comfortable and compelling in public speaking situations</li><li>Strong programming skills, and experience with Data Science best practices </li><li>Experience with Python and/or SQL</li><li>Takes the initiative and proactively solves problems</li><li>Self-starting with the ability to effectively work autonomously with little oversight</li><li>Ability to work with a diverse group of individuals</li><li>Strong analytical skills</li><li>Ability to multitask and manage multiple projects simultaneously<br><br></li></ul><strong>Nice To Have<br><br></strong><ul><li>Additional proficiency in Full Stuck Web and/or Backend is a plus!<br><br></li></ul>$25 - $30 an hour<br><br><em>Please note the posted salary range is based on U.S. geographic zones. job_title: Lead Data Analyst, Influence Operations - USDS
desc: <strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong> About TikTok<br>TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo. <br><br>Why Join Us<br>Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible. <br>Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day. <br>To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always. <br>At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve. <br>Join us.<br><br>About USDS<br>At TikTok, we're committed to a process of continuous innovation and improvement in our user experience and safety controls. We're proud to be able to serve a global community of more than a billion people who use TikTok to creatively express themselves and be entertained, and we're dedicated to giving them a platform that builds opportunity and fosters connection. We also take our responsibility to safeguard our community seriously, both in how we address potentially harmful content and how we protect against unauthorized access to user data.<br><br>U.S. Data Security (“USDS”) is a standalone entity of TikTok in the U.S. This new security-first division was created to bring heightened focus and governance to our data protection policies and content assurance protocols to keep U.S. users safe. Our focus is on providing oversight and protection of the TikTok platform and user data in the U.S., so millions of Americans can continue turning to TikTok to learn something new, earn a living, express themselves creatively, or be entertained. The teams within USDS that deliver on this commitment daily span Trust &amp; Safety, Security &amp; Privacy, Engineering, User &amp; Product Ops, Corporate Functions and more.<br><br>We are seeking an experienced lead Threat Data Analyst to join the Trust and Safety organization within USDS.  You will use your investigative and adversarial mindset to help us identify, detect, and mitigate Influence Operation (IO) networks operating on TikTok. You will lead a team of data scientists and data analysts to data mine threat actor abuse tactics, develop predictive models, and conduct comprehensive proactive and reactive investigations using analytical skills, subject-matter expertise, and regional experience. The lead Threat Data Analyst will have the responsibility to perform social network analysis at scale to discover, identify, and mitigate the most harmful threats targeting the platform. You will closely collaborate with engineers and behavioral scientists to resolve complex threats that reach across topic or feature areas and will require network analysis and the creation of detection pipelines. You will develop actionable recommendations, and continually iterate solutions to scale your impact. The work of the Investigations and Insights team is critical to TikTok user safety, and the lead Threat Data Analyst will have the opportunity to identify and mitigate the most harmful threats targeting the platform and our users. In order to enhance collaboration and cross-functional partnerships, among other things, at this time, our organization follows a hybrid work schedule that requires employees to work in the office 3 days a week, or as directed by their manager/department. We regularly review our hybrid work model, and the specific requirements may change at any time.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>- Identify deceptive behavior of threat actors, collect and analyze signals through data analysis, and work with engineers to improve detection models and develop data driven mitigation strategies. <br>- Use all available internal and external data sources to produce actionable intelligence on high-harm threat actors, their networks, and threat organizations in the topic area of Influence Operations.<br>- Build and execute team roadmap.<br>- Apply structured analytic techniques, data science, and intelligence tradecraft to perform social network analysis of large attribute, ideational, and relational data sets to identify threat actor networks, critical nodes, and kill-chains.<br>- Work cross-functionally with product managers, program managers, security, operations, policy, and communications teams to address gaps in current threat response processes such as detection and mitigation.<br>- Collaborate with a team of global experts that respond to known threat actors and proactively build and tailor queries to discover and identify potential threats. <br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong> - Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, Economics, Business, other relevant fields, or equivalent experience.<br>- Experience conducting social network analysis for social media organizations, law enforcement, and/or intelligence community agencies.<br>- 2 years of people management experience.<br>- Experience should include discovering and correlating high-harm threat actors, networks, and organizations across global markets by performing quantitative and qualitative analysis of large data sets including attribute, ideational, and relational data.<br>- Intermediate understanding of descriptive statistics<br>- Proficient in SQL or other relational database language and beginner in another object oriented programming language.<br>- Able to create meaningful data visualizations<br><br>Preferred Qualifications<br>- Experience researching or analyzing global Influence Operations (IO) in order to identify, detect, and develop mitigation strategies against IO networks.  <br>- Rapidly shift priorities based on evolving challenges to the platform <br>- Identify anomalous behavior and determine ways for further exploring new research leads<br>- Communicate coherently and crisply to incident response teams and senior leadership <br>- Communicate complex concepts to broader stakeholders without shared expertise  <br>- Critical thinking skills with the ability to apply theorems or analytical techniques to discover insights that are not readily apparent<br><br>TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.<br><br>Accommodation Statement<br>TikTok is committed to providing reasonable accommodations in our recruitment processes for candidates with disabilities, pregnancy, sincerely held religious beliefs or other reasons protected by applicable laws. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation, please reach out to us at usds.accommodations@tiktokusds.com <br><br><strong>Job Information:<br><br></strong>【For Pay Transparency】Compensation Description (annually) <p>The base salary range for this position in the selected city is $130133 - $232222 annually.<span></span></p><p>Compensation may vary outside of this range depending on a number of factors, including a candidate’s qualifications, skills, competencies and experience, and location. Base pay is one part of the Total Package that is provided to compensate and recognize employees for their work, and this role may be eligible for additional discretionary bonuses/incentives, and restricted stock units.<span></span></p><p>Our company benefits are designed to convey company culture and values, to create an efficient and inspiring work environment, and to support our employees to give their best in both work and life. We offer the following benefits to eligible employees: <span></span></p><p>We cover 100% premium coverage for employee medical insurance, approximately 75% premium coverage for dependents and offer a Health Savings Account(HSA) with a company match. As well as Dental, Vision, Short/Long term Disability, Basic Life, Voluntary Life and AD&amp;D insurance plans. In addition to Flexible Spending Account(FSA) Options like Health Care, Limited Purpose and Dependent Care. <span></span></p><p>Our time off and leave plans are: 10 paid holidays per year plus 17 days of Paid Personal Time Off (PPTO) (prorated upon hire and increased by tenure) and 10 paid sick days per year as well as 12 weeks of paid Parental leave and 8 weeks of paid Supplemental Disability. <span></span></p><p>We also provide generous benefits like mental and emotional health benefits through our EAP and Lyra. A 401K company match, gym and cellphone service reimbursements. The Company reserves the right to modify or change these benefits programs at any time, with or without notice.<span></span></p>
