CRM</li><li>Expert level understanding of Salesforce objects and relationships, as well as reporting</li><li>Expert in SQL and SOQL coding languages</li><li>Advanced in PostgreSQL, Python and R</li><li>Apex coding experience a plus</li><li>Demonstrated experience taking business requirements and turning them in to actionable dashboards</li><li>Demonstrated ability to accurately synthesize and present data in a digestible format.</li><li>Certifications are a plus.</li><li>Located in EST time zone.</li><li>Work samples or portfolio is must have while submitting the profile with detailed summary<br><br></li></ul><strong>Must Have Skills Set<br><br></strong><ul><li>Must have Tableau CRM- 3 years, Salesforce, Objects, tableau Online 5-7 years.</li><li>Experience SQL and SOQL</li><li>Practical exp, Dashboard,</li><li>5-7 + Exp in Marketing or Sales Operations</li><li>Advanced in PostgreSQL, Python and R</li></ul>

<strong>Description<br><br></strong><strong><em>Every day, we work together for what matters – bold, swift, and equitable climate action. <br><br></em></strong><strong>About The Role<br><br></strong>This is a fantastic career opportunity to join an innovative, passionate team that requires focus, persistence, and dynamism in the growing Climate sector! 3Degrees is hiring a Reporting Analyst, Environmental Markets to join our growing team and help organizations around the world achieve their renewable energy and decarbonization goals. In this role you will be a source for accurate and timely reporting from our Microsoft SQL Server database and other data sources. We are looking for a highly collaborative individual who can understand requirements from business leaders, have the skill to retrieve information, and be effective at presenting the data. You have a curious mind, a passion for accuracy and the ability to refine reporting processes with a focus on standardization and improved documentation.<br><br><em>This is a full-time position preferably located in the San Francisco, CA, Portland, ME, New York, NY or Portland, OR offices and will report to the Business Analyst, Environmental Markets. For highly qualified candidates a remote office with agreement to travel for training and collaboration will be considered. Remote workers agree that their home office provides a comfortable and productive environment that enables success in the role as a “remote” employee. <br><br></em><strong>What You’ll Do<br><br></strong>The Reporting Analyst, Environmental Markets will join the Environmental Markets (EM) business unit and will assist with a redesign and consolidation of the team’s reporting processes, tools, and reports. Using your Microsoft SQL and business intelligence experience you will take on existing portfolio management and general team reporting, ensuring that a high quality standard is maintained and that the business logic is sound. You will also be relied on for ad hoc analysis and operational support. Areas of work include:<br><br><ul><li>Manage channels of data sharing within EM</li><ul><li>Catalog a variety of KPIs, financial metrics, and reporting tools and create a single source of truth for key information</li><li>Merge similar tools into simplified master copies and distribute to stakeholders</li><li>Track the use cases and requirements of different teams within the company and ensure EM’s data offerings meet all needs and are accessible where needed</li><li>Write documentation and coordinate with technical development teams to address new data or reporting needs as the business grows</li><li>Maintain consistency in business logic and procedure despite a high volume of ad hoc requests</li><li>Guide members of other teams through EM’s data offerings, explaining terms and methodologies and helping to create a shared conceptual foundation</li></ul><li>Collect and report portfolio valuation metrics</li><ul><li>Support and improve portfolio valuation tools integral to the team, updating them when changes in methodology or server architecture occur</li><li>Ensure published financial totals are clearly supported by raw data and describe sources of any large changes</li><li>Renovate portfolio tools for Carbon and Transportation portfolios, bringing them up to the standards of existing portfolios</li></ul><li>Quantify and report other aspects of team performance</li><ul><li>Run monthly booking and commission reporting process, liaising with sales and consulting teams to ensure data accuracy</li><li>Conduct routine reporting on EM activity metrics and operational expenses</li><li>Work with Risk Management team to develop and/or maintain risk reports and tools</li></ul><li>Create infrastructure supporting expansion of team reporting in Tableau</li><ul><li>Migrate reporting from SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) into Tableau where applicable</li></ul><li>Take point on incoming ad hoc requests for information, from within and outside of EM</li><ul><li>Develop and release new reporting, modify existing reports to meet team needs</li><li>Keep company statistics directory updated with accurate performance metrics<br></li></ul></ul><strong>About You<br><br></strong>The Reporting Analyst will be able to translate business requirements into accurate reports and be able to explain the data in simple terms. You will join the Environmental Markets team which manages the environmental attribute commodity business at 3Degrees, including renewable energy credits (RECs), carbon offsets, and clean fuel standard (CFS) solutions.<br><br><ul><li>2-3 years of professional experience in data analysis, SQL reporting analyst, finance</li><li>Intermediate proficiency in Microsoft SQL, SSRS Report Builder, Advanced Excel VBA, and Tableau or other Business Intelligence software</li><li>Clean energy commodity industry experience preferred (REC’s, CFS &amp; Carbon)</li><li>Ability to work in a team based environment balancing competing demands toward mutual goals</li><li>Excellent presentation skills. Must be able to succinctly present information to other team members</li><li>Capability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and maintain composure under pressure</li><li>Intermediate proficiency in Microsoft SQL, SSRS Report Builder, Excel, and Tableau or other Business Intelligence software</li><li>Self-motivated, with a genuine desire to accelerate the growth of environmental markets in the US and abroad</li><li>BA/BS degree in a relevant discipline or equivalent combination of professional experience and education<br><br></li></ul><strong>How We Define Success<br><br></strong><strong>Within 30 days,<br><br></strong><ul><li>You will complete the first month of our onboarding program plus invested in your own research and have a basic understanding of 3Degrees’ company and commercial business structure, products, and services</li><li>Demonstrate a familiarity with the key weekly and monthly reporting conducted by the team. You understand the key server locations they rely on and are beginning to track the business requirements around each <br><br></li></ul><strong>Within 90 days, <br><br></strong><ul><li>You have a solid understanding of the suite of reporting currently produced within EM. You take ownership of a few key routine reports and processes within EM, especially the core monthly business processes </li><li>You are able to field ad-hoc questions against the data sources we manage and clearly explain the findings</li><li>You have created a source for documenting our reports and began to analyze each for consolidation and standardization<br><br></li></ul><strong>Within 6 months,<br><br></strong><ul><li>You have cataloged the team's routine reporting; merging and standardizing it where necessary </li><li>You will manage the suite of routine reports for distribution, updates, and integration</li><li>Provide and manage documentation for each report including detail on the SQL logic used</li><li>Assist with process updates to manage reporting requests to the team</li><li>You have become an independent information source for questions against these reports, explaining trends and events to both our internal team and business users<br><br></li></ul><strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits<br><br></strong><ul><li>Compensation: The starting base pay for this position is $82,000 to $104,000 in the US. The total compensation package for the successful candidate in this role may exceed the base pay as it includes other incentive pay. The base pay is dependent upon many factors such as location, transferable or job-related skills, work experience, relevant training, business needs, and market demands. The base salary range is subject to change and may be modified in the future</li><li>Benefits: this position is eligible for a benefits package that includes medical, dental, vision, 401k, flexible paid time off and more. Additional information regarding the benefits available for this position can be found at: https://jobs.jobvite.com/3degrees/jobs/jointheteam</li><li>Supplemental Pay: this position is eligible for discretionary bonus programs including the company’s profit sharing program and an annual team Bonus Pool</li><li>This compensation and benefits information is based on 3Degrees’ good faith estimate as of the date of publication and may be modified in the future<br><br></li></ul><strong>OUR COMMITMENT TO DIVERSITY, INCLUSION AND EQUITY<br><br></strong>3Degrees is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to creating an inclusive environment where different perspectives contribute to better solutions. 3Degrees welcomes people regardless of race, color, religion, national origin, gender, gender identity or gender expression, age, sex, pregnancy, marital status, ancestry, disability, military or veteran status, sexual orientation, genetic information, or any other category protected by law.<br><br>

job_title: Data Analyst (9774-Senior Community Development Specialist I)
company_name: City and County of San Francisco
desc: <strong>Company Description<br><br></strong><strong>Important Information - In order to be considered for this position you must submit a response to four (4) supplemental questions with your online application.<br><br></strong><strong>Mayor’s Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD)<br><br></strong>MOHCD’s mission is to address social, economic, and racial inequities through the creation of affordable housing opportunities and the funding of essential services that are foundational for strong communities. We are industry leaders in the implementation of policies for the creation, rehabilitation and preservation of affordable housing. In our hiring practices, we strive to build teams that reflect the diversity of our City and the populations we serve, and we urge qualified candidates of all races, ethnicity, sexual orientation, and gender identity to apply.<br><br><strong>Job Description<br><br></strong>Under the general direction of the Director of Data, Evaluation and Compliance, the Data Analyst at the Mayor’s Office of Housing and Community Development plans, organizes, leads, and conducts complex, sensitive, and detailed analytical work in support of departmental strategic planning efforts, policy development, decision-making, reporting and communications. The Data Analyst will also manage the migration of MOHCD data from disparate spreadsheets and databases to a Salesforce system. A strong candidate would have experience in project management and in performing analyses using coding and analysis software such as R, Python and Stata, mapping software such as ArcGIS, and data visualization software such as PowerBI. This position will work in a highly collaborative environment and assist with the department’s efforts to move toward better outcomes and racial equity with its programs and services and to maximize the impact of program resources.<br><br><ul><li>Conducts research and analytical work on special projects or highly visible public issues that have significant impact on the functions and operations of the department’s affordable housing and community development programs and projects;</li><li>In collaboration with Director of Database Development and Migration, manages the migration of department data from spreadsheets and databases to a Salesforce system, including coordination of multiple teams to develop department-wide schema and resolve data conflicts; collaboration with other City staff to integrate database development with the housing application portal; management of external project consultants; and report to internal leadership team;</li><li>Collaborates and confers with senior management staff and other subject matter experts to clarify needs, issues and parameters, and to discuss, evaluate and make policy recommendations on affordable housing and community development programs and projects;</li><li>Responds to internal and external informational and data requests, including those of a highly sensitive nature;</li><li>Compiles and analyzes the department’s program data for the purposes of tracking progress towards goals and of improving services, and for mandated reporting purposes;</li><li>Prepares clear, comprehensive reports and presentations;</li><li>Presents reports, finding and recommendations to internal and external stakeholders, including formal presentations to groups; may represent the department to the Mayor's Office, Board of Supervisors, Controller's Office, other city officials, outside agencies or the general the public;</li><li>Provides technical assistance and training to internal staff on data structure and data systems, including Salesforce onboarding, hosting bi-weekly Data/Salesforce Office Hours, and, assisting with the creation of reports to extract data;</li><li>Develops and implements processes, procedures and systems to clean, manage, store and present a large volume of sensitive and complex data, including creating and maintaining automated scripts;</li><li>As part of the Data, Evaluation and Compliance team, coordinates data management processes and systems across departmental divisions to improve reporting and communication of the department’s impact and to evaluate and improve the department’s programs and services; and, supports internal staff to collect, review, analyze and report data. </li><li>Performs related duties and responsibilities as assigned. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Important And Essential Knowledge, Skills And Abilities<br><br></strong>Knowledge of: the principles, procedures and standards related to the following: government and/or non-profit management and operations; project management; relational database structure; coding and analysis software; statistical, geospatial and other analytical methods; applicable local, state, and federal laws and regulations affecting departmental operations; the development and implementation of complex systems and procedures; program evaluation frameworks; policy analysis; and affordable housing and community development programs that serve low-income communities.<br><br>Ability to: collect, synthesize, and analyze a wide variety of information; conduct difficult analytical studies involving complex administrative and financial systems and procedures; work with authority to identify and define problems, determine methodology, evaluate data, make recommendations with appropriate justification and develop/implement a plan of action; manage projects effectively; effectively prioritize and organize multiple assignments and projects; exercise sound judgment; coordinate work/projects with other programs and departments; establish and maintain effective working relationships with departmental representatives, senior management, representatives of other departments/agencies, officials, contractors and the general public; negotiate effectively; speak clearly and concisely to communicate work-related information in a manner that is understandable to the intended audience; listen and effectively elicit information; prepare clear, accurate, effective, well-organized and understandable written documents and management reports; use a computer to research, access, extract and process data and information; use Windows-based software programs, including Word, Excel and PowerPoint; use data management systems such as Salesforce and/or other web-based grants or contract management systems; use coding and analysis software such as Python, R and Stata; use geospatial analysis software such as ArcGIS; use data visualization software such as PowerBI; create and maintain records; prepare correspondence, reports and other documentation, including statistical data.<br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Possession of a graduate degree (Master's degree or higher) from an accredited college or university and three (3) years of full-time equivalent experience performing professional level analytical work as described in Note A: OR</li><li> Possession of a graduate degree (Master's degree or higher) from an accredited college or university with major college coursework as described in Note B and two (2) years full-time equivalent experience performing professional level analytical work as described in Note A; OR</li><li> Possession of a baccalaureate degree from an accredited college or university and four (4) years full-time equivalent experience performing professional level analytical work as described in Note A; OR</li><li> Possession of a baccalaureate degree from an accredited college or university with major college coursework as described in Note B and three (3) years full-time equivalent performing professional level analytical work as described in Note A<br><br></li></ul>SUBSTITUTION: Applicants may substitute up to 2 years of the required education with additional qualifying experience in budget analysis, financial analysis and reporting, legislative/policy analysis, or contract/grant administration. One year (2000 hours) of additional qualifying experience will be considered equivalent to 30 semester units/45 quarter units.<br><br>Additional Information<br><br><strong>Important Information:<br><br></strong><strong>You may upload your supplemental questions response as an attachment with your online application in Smart Recruiters.<br><br></strong><strong>Supplemental Questions (1-4):<br><br></strong><ul><li>Describe your experience working in the affordable housing and/or community development field and with providing services for low and moderate-income community</li><li>Describe your experience with managing the migration of data from one data system to another, including your experience using a Salesforce system or other data management systems that you have used. Describe your experience working with multiple teams within the same organization or different organizations with different yet similar business processes and purposes, to develop a common database or data structure for all parties. </li><li>Describe your experience with compiling, analyzing and presenting program data and/or secondary data such as Census data. Please include your experience with geospatial software such as ArcGIS data visualization software such as PowerBI. </li><li>Describe a complex data analysis project that you led, especially one in which you used coding and analysis software, like R, Python, or Stata. In the description, please include a brief description of the research question(s), your approach to answering the question(s), and the steps that you took for the analysis project. Please also describe challenges that you encountered and steps that you took to overcome these obstacles. <br><br></li></ul>___________________________________<br><br><strong>Specific information regarding this recruitment process are listed below:<br><br></strong>Classification - 9774 - Senior Community Development Specialist I<br><br>Status - Permanent Exempt<br><br>Application Opening: Tuesday, November 14, 2023<br><br>Filing Deadline - Friday, December 8, 2023 - 11:59 pm<br><br>Salary - $106,730 - $129,688<br><br><strong>How To Apply<br><br></strong>Applications for City and County of San Francisco jobs are only accepted through an online process. Visit https://careers.smartrecruiters.com/CityAndCountyOfSanFrancisco1/ and begin the application process.<br><br><ul><li> Select the “I’m Interested” button and follow instructions on the screen 7 Applicants may be contacted by email about this recruitment and, therefore, it is their responsibility to ensure that their registered email address is accurate and kept up-to-date. Also, applicants must ensure that email from CCSF is not blocked on their computer by a spam filter. To prevent blocking, applicants should set up their email to accept CCSF mail from the following addresses (@sfgov.org, @sfdpw.org, @sfport.com, @flysfo.com, @sfwater.org, @sfdph.org, @asianart.org, @sfmta.com, @sfpl.org, @dcyf.org, @first5sf.org, @famsf.org, @ccsf.edu, @smartalerts.info, and @smartrecruiters.com). <br><br></li></ul>Applicants will receive a confirmation email that their online application has been received in response to every announcement for which they file. Applicants should retain this confirmation email for their records. Failure to receive this email means that the online application was not submitted or received.<br><br><strong>Additional Information Regarding Employment with the City and County of San Francisco:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Information About The Hiring Process</li><li>Conviction History</li><li>Employee Benefits Overview </li><li>Equal Employment Opportunity </li><li>Disaster Service Worker</li><li>ADA Accommodation</li><li>Veterans Preference</li><li>Right to Work</li><li>Copies of Application Documents</li><li>Diversity Statement<br><br></li></ul><strong>Exam Analyst Information: </strong>If you have any questions regarding this recruitment or application process, please contact the exam analyst at <strong>Karen Henderson - karen.henderson@sfgov.org.<br><br></strong>All City and County of San Francisco employees are designated Disaster Service Workers through state and local law (California Government Code Section 3100-3109). Employment with the City requires the affirmation of a loyalty oath to this effect. Employees are required to complete all Disaster Service Worker-related training as assigned, and to return to work as ordered in the event of an emergency.<br><br>All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.<br><br>The City and County of San Francisco encourages women, minorities and persons with disabilities to apply. Applicants will be considered regardless of their sex, race, age, religion, color, national origin, ancestry, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition (associated with cancer, a history of cancer, or genetic characteristics), HIV/AIDS status, genetic information, marital status, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, military and veteran status, or other protected category under the law.

As a highly collaborative organization, our data engineers work cross-functionally with software engineering, data science, and product management to optimize growth, strategy, and experience for our 3 billion plus users, as well as our internal employee community. In this role, you will see a direct correlation between your work, company growth, and user satisfaction. Beyond this, you will work with some of the brightest minds in the industry, and you'll have a unique opportunity to solve some of the most interesting data challenges with efficiency and integrity, at a scale few companies can match.<br><br>Data Engineer, Product Analytics Responsibilities:<br><br><ul><li>Conceptualize and own the data architecture for multiple large-scale projects, while evaluating design and operational cost-benefit tradeoffs within systems.</li><li>Create and contribute to frameworks that improve the efficacy of logging data, while working with data infrastructure to triage issues and resolve.</li><li>Collaborate with engineers, product managers, and data scientists to understand data needs, representing key data insights visually in a meaningful way.</li><li>Define and manage SLA for all data sets in allocated areas of ownership.</li><li>Determine and implement the security model based on privacy requirements, confirm safeguards are followed, address data quality issues, and evolve governance processes within allocated areas of ownership.</li><li>Design, build, and launch collections of sophisticated data models and visualizations that support multiple use cases across different products or domains.</li><li>Solve our most challenging data integration problems, utilizing optimal ETL patterns, frameworks, query techniques, sourcing from structured and unstructured data sources.</li><li>Assist in owning existing processes running in production, optimizing complex code through advanced algorithmic concepts.</li><li>Optimize pipelines, dashboards, frameworks, and systems to facilitate easier development of data artifacts.</li><li>Influence product and cross-functional teams to identify data opportunities to drive impact.</li><li>Mentor team members by giving/receiving actionable feedback.<br><br></li></ul>Minimum Qualifications:<br><br><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, relevant technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>5+ years experience in the data warehouse space.</li><li>5+ years experience in custom ETL design, implementation and maintenance.</li><li>5+ years experience with object-oriented programming languages.</li><li>7+ years experience with schema design and dimensional data modeling.</li><li>7+ years experience in writing SQL statements.</li><li>Experience analyzing data to identify gaps and inconsistencies.</li><li>Experience managing and communicating data warehouse plans to internal clients.<br><br></li></ul>Preferred Qualifications:<br><br><ul><li>Master's or Ph.D degree in a STEM field</li><li>Experience with one or more of the following: data processing automation, data quality, data warehousing, data governance, business intelligence, data visualization, data privacy</li><li>Experience working with terabyte to petabyte scale data</li><li>Experience influencing product decisions with data.<br><br></li></ul>About Meta:<br><br>Meta builds technologies that help people connect, find communities, and grow businesses. When Facebook launched in 2004, it changed the way people connect. Apps like Messenger, Instagram and WhatsApp further empowered billions around the world. Now, Meta is moving beyond 2D screens toward immersive experiences like augmented and virtual reality to help build the next evolution in social technology. People who choose to build their careers by building with us at Meta help shape a future that will take us beyond what digital connection makes possible today—beyond the constraints of screens, the limits of distance, and even the rules of physics.<br><br>Meta is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, transgender status, sexual stereotypes, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Meta participates in the E-Verify program in certain locations, as required by law. Please note that Meta may leverage artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies in connection with applications for employment.<br><br>Meta is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities in our recruiting process. If you need any assistance or accommodations due to a disability, please let us know at accommodations-ext@fb.com.

<p><strong>Title: </strong>Power BI Developer/Analyst </p><p><strong>Location: </strong>Bay rea CA (Onsite Mon-Fri)</p><p><strong>Job type:</strong> Fulltime/W2-hourly</p><p> </p><p><strong>Summary:</strong></p><ul><li>We are seeking a skilled and motivated Power BI Developer/Analyst to join the Critical River team. </li><li>The ideal candidate will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining interactive dashboards and reports using Microsoft Power BI. </li><li>You will collaborate with business stakeholders to gather requirements, analyse data, and translate business needs into effective visualizations. </li></ul><p> </p><p><strong>Responsibilities </strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with business users to understand their data requirements and visualization needs. </li><li>Design and develop interactive and visually appealing dashboards, reports, and data visualizations using Power BI. </li><li>Extract and transform data from various sources to create accurate and efficient data models. </li><li>Perform data analysis to identify trends, patterns, and insights that drive business decision-making. </li><li>Create new and Optimize existing Power BI reports and dashboards for performance and accuracy. </li><li>Stay up-to-date with industry best practices and new features in Power BI to ensure customer visualizations are Cutting-edge and effective. </li><li>Assist in training team members and end-users on Power BI usage and best practices. </li></ul><p> </p><p><strong>Qualifications </strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience in designing and developing interactive dashboards and reports using Microsoft Power BI. </li><li>Strong proficiency in data modeling, DAX (Data Analysis Expressions), and Power Query. </li><li>Proficiency in SQL queries, SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) </li><li>In-depth understanding of database management systems, online analytical processing (OLAP) and ETL (Extract, transform, load) framework. </li><li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to translate business requirements into effective visualizations. </li><li>Knowledge of data visualization best practices and principles. </li><li>Strong communication skills to collaborate with both technical and non-technical stakeholders. </li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment. </li><li>Strong Knowledge of SQL queries, SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) </li></ul><p> </p><p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with other BI tools like Tableau, QlikView, or Looker. </li><li>Knowledge of scripting languages like Python or R for data analysis. </li><li>Microsoft Power BI certification</li></ul>

company_name: Mercedes-Benz Research & Development North America, Inc.
desc: Embedded in a worldwide network Mercedes-Benz Research &amp; Development North America continuously strives to remain at the forefront of successful automotive research and development. MBRDNA is headquartered in Silicon Valley, California, with key areas of Autonomous Driving, Advanced Interaction Design, Digital User Experience, Machine Learning, Customer Research, and Open Innovation. In Farmington Hills, Michigan, the focus is on Powertrain and eDrive technology as well as in Long Beach, where the teams test durability of the latest driver assistant and telematic systems. The Digital Hub in Seattle focusses on developing a cloud architecture and building out the cloud platform for the next generation of connected car services. The Testing and Regulatory Affairs Division in Ann Arbor and the Advanced Vehicle Design in Carlsbad complete the competence center.<br><br>With the number of connected Mercedes-Benz vehicles on the road increasing daily, the amount of data being generated, and its significance is also increasing rapidly. The Mercedes-Benz Data and AI team is seeking a passionate and versatile Data Engineer Intern to join our Machine Learning Team for the Fall of 2023 / Spring 2024 to support with the collection, storage, processing, and analysis of large amounts of vehicle data. You will work with our Mercedes-Benz Research &amp; Development North America (MBRDNA) team based in Silicon Valley. The team focuses on gathering valuable insights from our Mercedes-Benz vehicles and support the development for data products that will shape the future of Mercedes-Benz vehicles with the goal of enhancing our customer’s experience.<br><br>In this position, you will work independently and collaboratively with our Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers to support the vehicle data processing, data product development, evaluation of data insights and gathering information from our Mercedes-Benz cars from around the world. Our ideal candidate is available full-time, from January through Summer 2024.<br><br><strong><strong>Job Responsibilities:<br><br></strong></strong><ul><li>Build and optimize the data pipelines that <strong>About Us<br><br></strong>The Stanford University Graduate School of Education (GSE) is a top-ranked school of education, known for its prestigious faculty, rigorous graduate degree programs, and its impact on the quality of education across the world. The GSE is committed to developing leaders in education research, practice and policy. Our community includes over 60 faculty, 400 students, 200 staff, 14,000 alumni and countless people from the local and global communities we work with and impact. The work environment is dynamic, deadline-driven, fast-paced, and energetic.<br><br><strong>Position Summary<br><br></strong>The Educational Opportunity Project (EOP) at Stanford University is working toward a future where all children have access to equitable educational opportunities. We are measuring educational opportunity in every community in America and have built the most comprehensive national database of academic performance in the U.S., based on over 500 million test scores. We hope that researchers will use the data to generate evidence about what policies and contexts are most effective at increasing educational opportunity, and that such evidence will inform educational policy and practices.<br><br>We seek an equity-minded, quantitative specialist to join our team as an <strong>Educational Opportunity Project Data Analyst</strong>. This person will be a core member of our research team and contribute to the development of the Stanford Education Data Archive (SEDA), including: cleaning, optimizing, and updating existing SEDA code, datasets, and documentation for future public releases on our website; cleaning, organizing, and harmonizing data from large longitudinal education datasets, including EDFacts, the Common Core of Data, Civil Rights Data Collection, among others; and supporting the development of research publications and reports for partners in the field (i.e., school districts and state departments of education). The ideal candidate can commit to the position for at least 2 years and brings strong Stata programming and communication skills along with a passion for using data to inform policies and practices that increase educational opportunity.<br><br>This is an exciting and dynamic time for the EOP as we create an innovative path to impacting the educational opportunity gap. It is also an exciting time for the Stanford Graduate School of Education where many new research programs are beginning, and faculty searches are underway for the very best in their fields. The EOP Data Analyst will play a key role in expanding our project’s capacity to achieve our mission. This position will be supervised by Dr. Erin Fahle, Executive Director of the EOP, and Dr. Sean Reardon, Faculty Director of the EOP. The analyst will also collaborate closely with other faculty, students, and research staff affiliated with the EOP.<br><br><strong>Your Primary Responsibilities Will Include<br><br></strong>As a data analyst, you will develop, implement, and maintain strong data management systems critical to the success of the EOP. This includes writing Stata code to clean and construct complex datasets, drafting technical documentation, and performing statistical analyses aligned with the EOP team’s research plan. Situated in Stanford’s highly dynamic research environment the Curtis Laboratory (http://med.stanford.edu/curtislab.html), led by Christina Curtis, PhD, is seeking a bioinformatician/Research Data Analyst 3 to join the Cancer Computational and Systems Biology group. The Curtis Laboratory is administratively situated within the Stanford Cancer Institute and is integrated within Stanford University and the School of Medicine’s Departments of Medicine (Oncology) and Genetics. The SCI is part of a Comprehensive National Cancer Institute Cancer Center for cross-disciplinary research in cancer biology involving researchers from oncology, radiobiology, computer science, genetics, statistics, and basic/translational clinical research. Our research couples state-of-the-art computational and experimental techniques to define novel therapeutic targets and biomarkers and to characterize tumor evolution.<br><br>The successful candidate will be part of an interdisciplinary research team developing novel technological and methodological approaches to improve the diagnosis, treatment and earlier detection of cancer. He/she will analyze and interpret large sequencing datasets by applying and developing bioinformatics and statistical methods whole genome/exome sequencing, RNA-seq, ATAC-seq, single cell, and circulating tumor DNA (ctDNA) data. The successful candidate will interact closely with other computational and experimental biologists and clinicians to test, validate, and refine hypotheses. This is a fantastic opportunity for a motivated bioinformatician, computational genomicist to join a dynamic team with significant opportunities for scholarship and leadership.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br></strong><ul><li>Lead and own organization-wide data initiatives (e.g. models, frameworks, platforms, dashboards).</li><li>Supervise, coach and mentor a high-performing team of analysts.</li><li>Identify, leverage and partner with external firms.</li><li>Prioritize and extract data from a variety of sources such as notes, survey results, medical reports, and laboratory data, and maintain its accuracy and completeness.</li><li>Determine additional data collection and reporting requirements. Design and customize reports based upon data in the database. Oversee and monitor regulatory compliance for utilization of the data.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and eliminate root cause for data problems or justify solutions to be implemented by others.</li><li>Create complex charts and databases, perform statistical analyses, and develop graphs and tables for publication and presentation.</li><li>Test prototype software and participate in approval and release process for new software.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Work with lab members to analyze biomedical data and address scientific problems with bioinformatics techniques</li><li>Design, develop, and operate computational pipelines for the analysis of sequencing data.</li><li>Install, maintain, evaluate third party software packages.</li><li>Manage and archive large data sets from next-generation sequencing experiments.</li><li>Maintain detailed records of all analyses.</li><li>Present results and progress updates at lab meetings and make presentations to experimental and scientific collaborators.</li><li>Attend seminars, lectures, and training courses to learn new bioinformatic skills and remain up to date with the cancer genomics field.</li><li> - Other duties may also be assigned<br><br></li></ul><strong>Desired Qualifications<br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Bioinformatics, Computer Science or a related field with two years of relevant experience </li><li>PhD in bioinformatics-related field</li><li>Strong background in bioinformatics and biostatistics, including analysis of high-throughput sequencing data</li><li>Experience working within a UNIX/Linux environment</li><li>Fluency in programming languages such as Perl, Python, Java, R, C, Matlab; MySQL</li><li>Excellent communication and team skills and fluency in both spoken and written English</li><li>Familiarity with machine learning, information theory and signal processing.</li><li>Experience with algorithm development</li><li>Familiarity with basic molecular biology</li><li>Background in cancer biology</li><li>Expertise in bioinformatics, computational genomics, evolutionary biology, accompanied by a relevant publication record. </li><li>Proficiency with high performance computing and multiple programming languages (C, Python, R).</li><li>Experience with high-throughput genome sequence data (WES, WGS, RNA-seq, ATAC-seq)</li><li>A background in evolutionary biology and familiarity with phylogenetics techniques.</li><li>Experience with high-performance computing, database management.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (required)<br><br></strong>Bachelor's degree and five years or more of relevant experience or combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.<br><br><strong>Knowledge, Skills And Abilities (required)<br></strong><ul><li>Ability to direct the work of others, for jobs requiring supervision.</li><li>Relevant subject matter knowledge.</li><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.</li><li>Excellent writing and analytical skills.</li><li>Ability to prioritize workload.<br><br></li></ul><strong>PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*:<br></strong><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.</li><li>Occasionally use a telephone.</li><li>Rarely writing by hand.</li><li> - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Working Conditions<br><br></strong>Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting.<br><br><strong>Work Standards<br></strong><ul><li>Interpersonal Skills: Demonstrates the ability to work well with Stanford colleagues and clients and with external organizations.</li><li>Promote Culture of Safety: Demonstrates commitment to personal responsibility and value for safety; communicates safety concerns; uses and promotes safe behaviors based on training and lessons learned.</li><li>Subject to and expected to comply with all applicable University policies and procedures, including but not limited to the personnel policies and other policies found in the University's Administrative Guide, http://adminguide.stanford.edu.<br><br></li></ul><strong>This hybrid or remote role is open to candidates anywhere in the United States. Stanford University has five Regional Pay Structures. The compensation for this position will be based on the location of the successful candidate. The expected pay range for this position is $88,000 to $159,000 per annum. Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. The pay offered to a selected candidate will be determined based on factors such as (but not limited to) the scope and responsibilities of the position, the qualifications of the selected candidate, departmental budget availability, internal equity, geographic location, and external market pay for comparable jobs.</strong>

<ul><li>Overdose Prevention Data Analyst<br><br></li></ul>As an AmeriCorps VISTA member you will build the capacity of the California Overdose Prevention Network (COPN; www.copn.org) by supporting the leadership team of a local overdose prevention coalition. You will help lead a local response to the overdose crisis by implementing intervention strategies known to reduce addiction and overdose deaths. This includes safe prescribing, ensuring access to treatment, and harm reduction. Through service with a local coalition, you will address inequities surrounding vulnerable populations, including but not limited to black and indigenous people of color (BIPOC), people of varying socio-economic status, and people of all genders. You will contribute to the goals of the coalition you serve through activities that will be based on local needs including strengthening coalition partnerships and networks; improving materials that support coalition intervention activities; conducting outreach; organizing and/or delivering naloxone trainings; managing coalition websites and social media platforms; assessing opportunities to enhance equitable services and programs; and creating a coalition database and/or data dashboard. This opportunity will provide key skills in logistics, organization, coordination, and interpersonal communication. Members are also part of a statewide member learning community through The Center for Health Leadership and Impact at the Public Health Institute (PHI), the largest AmeriCorps VISTA sponsorship in the Western Region. This community includes ongoing support from VISTA Leads and a monthly series of professional development opportunities, workshops, networking events, and trainings. Learn more about our VISTA network on our website, https://healthleadership.org/pathways/americorps ***NOTE: We have openings for VISTA positions throughout California year-round. If you would like to be considered for an opportunity to serve later in the year, you may also apply to this listing.<br><br>Further help on this page can be found by <strong> clicking here </strong> .<br><br><strong>Member Duties :</strong> The AmeriCorps VISTA member would serve as support to the coalition leadership, building the capacity needed to ensure that Coalition activities continue to curb the epidemic. A few examples of specific activities that VISTA members might do are: Work with community leaders and advocates to pilot new programs; Work with community members to identify opportunities in prevention, and bring in resources from other aligned efforts to engage the community in prevention efforts; Help coalitions with safer prescribing efforts by disseminating guidelines, fliers, and posters; Implement and enhance data collection process; and Implement outreach events like a drug take-back day and work with the community and pharmacies to translate these efforts into permanent structures.<br><br><strong>Program Benefits :</strong> Housing , Training , Living Allowance , Childcare assistance if eligible , Choice of Education Award or End of Service Stipend , Health Coverage* , Relocation Allowance .<br><br><ul><li>For details about AmeriCorps VISTA healthcare benefits, please visit http://www.vistacampus.gov/healthcare<br><br></li></ul><strong>Terms<br><br></strong>Permits working at another job during off hours , Car recommended .<br><br><strong>Service Areas<br><br></strong>Community and Economic Development , Public Safety , Health , Community Outreach .<br><br><strong>Skills<br><br></strong>Communications , Non-Profit Management , Conflict Resolution , Social Services , Community Organization , General Skills , Computers/Technology , Writing/Editing , Public Health , Leadership , Fund raising/Grant Writing , Team Work .<br><br>Refine Search<br><br><strong>Summary<br><br></strong><strong>Program Type:<br><br></strong>AmeriCorps VISTA<br><br><strong>Program<br><br></strong><ul><li>Overdose Prevention Data Analyst<br><br></li></ul><strong>Program Start/End Date<br><br></strong>03/11/2024 - IT EDW Operations<br><br>Full Time<br><br>74891BR<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>The Research Data Analyst involves gathering, analyzing, and interpreting a wide variety of research data. Designs and conducts research including selecting data samples, developing research instruments, analyzing collected information according to established statistical methods, and developing recommendations based on research findings. Prepares reports, charts, tables, and other visual aids to interpret and communicate data and results.<br><br>The Research Data Analyst will be responsible for managing and analyzing data from studies addressing how well the health care system works when it does not perform optimally, and what factors determine whether care is high quality, efficient, and focused on the needs of the patient. Because the information available about health care is evolving, we also are using big data and machine learning techniques to understand the benefits of and failures of, the health system. The goal of our research is to identify policies and practices that clinical organizations, payers, and the government could adopt that would make healthcare outcomes better and healthcare costs lower for individual patients and society as a whole.<br><br>The Research Data Analyst's responsibilities will include managing, designing, and improving datasets; extracting and cleaning datasets; designing, conducting, and interpreting basic and advanced statistical analysis; preparation of summary reports, charts, tables, and figures; and contributions to publications and presentations of this data. In addition, the job will include performance (with guidance from the lead investigators and from statisticians) of complicated statistical analysis—including mixed modeling, linear regression, latent class analysis, ROC analysis, model calibration, and unbiased hierarchical clustering in addition to more common statistics such as Fisher’s exact test, Students T-test, and Kaplan Meier plots—and of machine learning. The individual will present the data to the Principal Investigator (PI) and make additional analyses or adjustments after review of the results. The Research Analyst will generate tabulated tables summarizing the results so that they are suitable for publication.<br><br><strong>To see the salary range for this position (we recommend that you make a note of the job code and use that to look up):</strong> TCS Non-Academic Titles Search (ucop.edu)<br><br>Please note: The compensation ranges listed online for roles not covered by a bargaining unit agreement are very wide, however a job offer will typically fall in the range of 80% - 120% of the established mid-point. An offer will take into consideration the experience of the final candidate AND the current salary level of individuals working at UCSF in a similar role.<br><br>For roles covered by a bargaining unit agreement, there will be specific rules about where a new hire would be placed on the range.<br><br>To learn more about the benefits of working at UCSF, including total compensation, please visit: https://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/compensation-and-benefits/index.html<br><br><strong>Department Description<br><br></strong>The University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) Department of Information Technology Academic Research Services (ARS) is chartered to provide data services and infrastructure which support clinical researchers computing and analytic needs. The Clinical Data Research Consultants group’s services include the administration of Data Use Agreements for the reuse of CMS and Medicaid data, customized data extractions from UCSF health systems, a federated data steward program to support compliance and set best practice standards for analysts who access health system data outside of central IT.<br><br><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in biological science, computational / programming, or related area and/or equivalent experience/training.</li><li>Proficiency in any of the following; Stata, SQL, SAS, R, Python</li><li>2+ years of experience with data manipulation and data quality control</li><li>Proficiency and programming experience in SAS, Python, R, or SQL</li><li>Understanding of relational databases, web interfaces, and operating systems.</li><li>Thorough knowledge of modern biology and applicable fields of research.</li><li>Communication skills to work with both technical and non-technical personnel in multiple fields of expertise and at various levels in the organization.</li><li>Ability to communicate technical information in a clear and concise manner.</li><li>Ability to interface with management on a regular basis.</li><li>Self-motivated, working independently or as part of a team, able to learn quickly, meet deadlines, and Clarity Certification</li><li>Ability to interface with management on a regular basis.</li><li>Research skills at a level to evaluate alternate solutions and develop recommendations</li><li>Advanced degree in quantitively discipline and/or equivalent experience/training</li><li>Experience working with large (&gt;50Gb) datasets</li><li>Experience working with medical/health services data (e.g, SEER/EPIC/claims data)</li><li>Thorough knowledge of web, application, and data security concepts and methods.</li><li>Thorough knowledge of bioinformatics methods, application programming, web development, and data structures.</li><li>Thorough knowledge of bioinformatics programming design, modification, and implementation.</li><li>Strong project management skills.</li><li>Thorough knowledge of modern biology and applicable field of research.</li><li>2 + years of experience in statistical analysis and modeling</li><li>Experience in a research environment<br><br></li></ul><strong>About UCSF<br><br></strong>The University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) is a leading university dedicated to promoting health worldwide through advanced biomedical research, graduate-level education in the life sciences and health professions, and excellence in patient care. It is the only campus in the 10-campus UC system dedicated exclusively to the health sciences. We bring together the world’s leading experts in nearly every area of health. We are home to five Nobel laureates who have advanced the understanding of cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, aging and stem cells.<br><br><strong>Pride Values<br><br></strong>UCSF is a diverse community made of people with many skills and talents. desc: <strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>This individual contributor is primarily responsible for assisting senior employees in supporting data-informed decisions, assisting with data and information gathering for targeted variables in an established systematic fashion, and supporting data preparation for analytic efforts.<br><br>This position assists with the execution of creative data analytic approaches leading to actionable outcomes, assists with the development, implementation, and automation of business and reporting solutions, and assists with data analysis interpretation.<br><br><strong>Essential Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li>Pursues self-development and effective relationships with others by sharing resources, information, and knowledge with coworkers and customers; listening, responding to, and seeking performance feedback; acknowledging strengths and weaknesses; assessing and responding to the needs of others; and adapting to and learning from change, difficulties, and feedback. </li><li>Completes work assignments by applying up-to-date knowledge in subject area to meet deadlines; following procedures and policies and applying data, and resources to support projects or initiatives; collaborating with others, often cross-functionally, to solve business problems; supporting the completion of priorities, deadlines, and expectations; communicating progress and information; identifying and recommending ways to address improvement opportunities when possible; and escalating issues or risks as appropriate. </li><li>Assists with data analysis interpretation by organizing and editing reports and presentations telling a compelling story to stakeholders to enable and influence decision making. </li><li>Supports data-informed decisions under the guidance of more senior employees by working with clients to identify and clarify key business needs; assisting in the development of outcomes and process measures; translating business requirements; informing data/information needs and data collection methods; measuring the impact of business decisions on clients, customers, and/or members; working with clients and staff to identify opportunities and methods to improve efficiencies with analysis; supporting end-users; and documenting processes and deliverables. </li><li>Assists with data and information gathering for targeted variables in an established systematic fashion by cleaning and organizing data; querying, merging, and extracting data across sources; completing routine data refresh and update; and providing user support and documentation. </li><li>Supports data preparation for analytic efforts under the guidance of more senior employees by cleaning data to ensure quality and accuracy based on provided guidelines; and consolidating data. </li><li>Assists with the execution of creative data analytic approaches leading to actionable outcomes by organizing metrics to be analyzed and calculating algorithms and conducting basic analyses under the guidance of more senior employees, including descriptive statistics. </li><li>Assists with the development, implementation, and automation of business and reporting solutions by creating summary statistics; organizing data reports, visualizations, and/or interactive Business Intelligence (BI) reports; identifying opportunities to improve exiting reporting solutions; and preparing documentation as appropriate. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Minimum Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelors degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Social/Physical/Life Science, Business, or related field OR Minimum two (2) years experience in data analytics or a directly related field. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Additional Requirements<br><br></strong><ul><li>Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs): Data Extraction; Data Mining; Data Visualization Tools; Statistical Programming Language; Relational Database Management; Project Management; Written Communication</li></ul>

job_title: Principal Data Analyst, Data Platform - Remote
desc: We are a dynamic, data-driven healthcare company on a mission to transform healthcare delivery for seniors. Partnering with health systems, health plans, and provider groups, we prioritize preventive, convenient, and coordinated care that leads to improved clinical outcomes. Backed by top private equity firms, our growth is rapid, and we are looking for exceptional individuals to join our Data Services and Business Intelligence (BI) team.<br><br><strong>Position Overview<br><br></strong>As a Principal Data Analyst in our Data Platform team, you will play a pivotal role in translating business requirements into technical specifications, conducting competitive market and product analysis, shaping data and AI product features, managing multiple projects, and extracting actionable insights from data using a range of analytic tools.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong>Perform in-depth data analysis, data model design, and data mapping activities, utilizing tools such as spreadsheets, Visio, and specialized BI tools.<br><br>Collaborate with the development team to create a Risk Adjustment Factor (RAF) calculation engine for predicting Risk scores and identifying optimization opportunities.<br><br>Work closely with Data Engineering and the business team to devise strategies for identifying Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) gaps and develop a coding application for the coding team.<br><br>Expertise in improving Encounter Data Processing System (EDPS) submission accuracy to achieve CMS compliance goals.<br><br>Implement data modeling based on healthcare data and care gaps, proposing solutions to optimize HEDIS rates by closing gaps in a timely manner.<br><br>Handle healthcare data, including patient-level data, claims data, and provider data.<br><br>Map data from various complex sources into an Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) using proprietary mapping tools.<br><br>Analyze and validate data to ensure compliance with data modeling, terminology, and code-set standards for harmonizing healthcare data.<br><br>Collaborate with technical resources to perform root cause analysis and resolve data quality issues.<br><br>Proficiency in HEDIS tools to generate rates and submit to the National Committee for Quality Assurance (NCQA) and other mandated submissions.<br><br>Serve as the liaison between the business and the Data Engineering Team.<br><br>Collaborate closely with Data Engineering &amp; BI leadership to define goals and objectives.<br><br>Interact with different business units to translate their data needs into specific requirements.<br><br>Actively participate in project meetings, provide input to project plans, and offer regular status updates.<br><br>Foster a positive and cohesive work environment.<br><br><strong>Required Skills And Experience<br><br></strong>5+ years of experience in Healthcare Data platforms and technologies with a solid understanding of Healthcare industry standards and requirements.<br><br>5+ years of database experience with MS SQL Server.<br><br>5+ years of experience in the healthcare industry with a strong grasp of data terminology.<br><br>Proficient in HIPAA protocols and guidelines.<br><br>Extensive hands-on experience with SQL Server, Azure Data Factory, APIs, and other cloud-based data services.<br><br>Strong expertise in Power BI, SSRS, or other Paginated Reporting tools to demonstrate advanced analytical and reporting skills.<br><br>Solid understanding of Healthcare Payer and clinical data.<br><br>Knowledge of programming languages such as Python, R, or SAS.<br><br>Strong Data Modeling experience.<br><br>Experience with Big Data processing technologies within a cloud ecosystem.<br><br>Education/Licensure: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or a related field (e.g., Electronics, IT). Foreign degree equivalencies are accepted.<br><br><strong>Work Environment<br><br></strong>This role offers the flexibility of remote work.<br><br>We are excited to welcome driven and talented individuals to our team who share our passion for improving healthcare outcomes and delivering exceptional care experiences.<br><br>Employment Type: Full-Time

job_title: Research Data Analyst - Addiction Care Team
desc: MED-ZSFG-HOSP<br><br>Full Time<br><br>74575BR<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>Involves gathering, analyzing, and interpreting a wide variety of Addiction Care Team research data. Duties may include but will not be limited to supporting the oversight and coordinating the tasks of single or multiple clinical research studies, (e.g., Zuckerberg San Francisco General Hospital) depending on their size and complexity. The research data analyst (RDA) will help to conduct qualitative interviews; create the codebook; training research staff to conduct qualitative research; and assist with data analysis, including preparing reports, charts, tables, and other visual aids to interpret and communicate data and results. They may oversee socio-demographic data and interview process; track and report on study results; create, and update databases; assist the PI with oversight of other research staff; participate in the review and writing of protocols to ensure Institutional Review Board approval within University compliance; help assure compliance with all relevant regulatory agencies; oversee study data integrity; implement and maintain periodic quality control procedures; interface with departments to obtain UCSF approval prior to study initiation; maintain all regulatory documents; report study progress to investigators; and participate in any internal and external audits or reviews of study protocols.<br><br><strong>To see the salary range for this position (we recommend that you make a note of the job code and use that to look up):</strong> TCS Non-Academic Titles Search (ucop.edu)<br><br>Please note: The compensation ranges listed online for roles not covered by a bargaining unit agreement are very wide, however a job offer will typically fall in the range of 80% - 120% of the established mid-point. An offer will take into consideration the experience of the final candidate AND the current salary level of individuals working at UCSF in a similar role.<br><br>For roles covered by a bargaining unit agreement, there will be specific rules about where a new hire would be placed on the range.<br><br>To learn more about the benefits of working at UCSF, including total compensation, please visit: https://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/compensation-and-benefits/index.html<br><br><strong>Department Description<br><br></strong>The Division of Hospital Medicine (DHM) is the largest division in the Department of Medicine (DOM) in terms of faculty size and is a national leader in clinical care, education, research, and quality improvement. Clinically, the division runs 10 clinical services and provides care for nearly half of the patients in the adult hospital on any given day. The Division of Hospital Medicine is the national leader in the field of Hospital Medicine, and supports a diverse research program spanning a broad range of clinical questions and methodologies.<br><br><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in related area and three-plus (3+) years of related work experience; / or equivalent experience / training</li><li>Skills in project management</li><li>Research skills at a level to evaluate alternate solutions and develop recommendations</li><li>Thorough knowledge of research function</li><li>Thorough skills associated with statistical analysis and systems programming</li><li>Thorough skills in analysis and consultation</li><li>Skills to communicate complex information in a clear and concise manner both verbally and in writing<br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong>NA<br><br><strong>About UCSF<br><br></strong>The University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) is a leading university dedicated to promoting health worldwide through advanced biomedical research, graduate-level education in the life sciences and health professions, and excellence in patient care. It is the only campus in the 10-campus UC system dedicated exclusively to the health sciences. We bring together the world’s leading experts in nearly every area of health. We are home to five Nobel laureates who have advanced the understanding of cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, aging and stem cells.<br><br><strong>Pride Values<br><br></strong>UCSF is a diverse community made of people with many skills and talents. We seek candidates whose work experience or community service has prepared them to contribute to our commitment to professionalism, respect, integrity, diversity and excellence – also known as our PRIDE values.<br><br>In addition to our PRIDE values, UCSF is committed to equity – both in how we deliver care as well as our workforce. We are committed to building a broadly diverse community, nurturing a culture that is welcoming and supportive, and engaging diverse ideas for the provision of culturally competent education, discovery, and patient care. Additional information about UCSF is available at diversity.ucsf.edu<br><br>Join us to find a rewarding career contributing to improving healthcare worldwide.<br><br><strong>Equal Employment Opportunity<br><br></strong>The University of California San Francisco is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, protected veteran or disabled status, or genetic information.<br><br><strong>Organization<br><br></strong>Campus<br><br><strong>Job Code and Payroll Title<br><br></strong>006257 RSCH DATA ANL 3<br><br><strong>Job Category<br><br></strong>Professional (Non-Clinical), Research and Scientific<br><br><strong>Bargaining Unit<br><br></strong>99 - Policy-Covered (No Bargaining Unit)<br><br><strong>Employee Class<br><br></strong>Contract<br><br><strong>Percentage<br><br></strong>100%<br><br><strong>Appointment End Date<br><br></strong>31-Dec-2024<br><br><strong>Location<br><br></strong>Flexible (combination of onsite and remote work), Zuckerberg San Francisco General (ZSFG)<br><br><strong>Shift<br><br></strong>Days<br><br><strong>Shift Length<br><br></strong>8 Hours<br><br><strong>Additional Shift Details<br><br></strong>Monday-Friday, 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM

job_title: Operations and Insights Analyst, Product Support
desc: Figma is growing our team of passionate people on a mission to make design accessible to all. Born on the Web, Figma helps entire product teams brainstorm, design and build better products — from start to finish. Whether it’s consolidating tools, simplifying workflows, or collaborating across teams and time zones, Figma makes the design process faster, more efficient, and fun while keeping everyone on the same page. From great products to long-lasting companies, we believe that nothing great is made alone—come make with us!<br><br>As a member of our Product Support Operations and Strategy team, the Operations and Insights Analyst will help us to use data to refine our Product Support experience. You will build dashboards and optimize reporting to ensure our leadership team has a clear pulse on the business, helping the team realize opportunities, build upon our strengths, and optimize our operations. As a problem solver, you will dig into data to find root causes, identify trends, uncover blind spots, and help to answer questions about the customer and employee experience. You will present data to the team in a manner that is effective, tangible, and tells a clear story.<br><br>What you’ll do at Figma:<br><br><ul><li>Delivering impactful analysis to help improve overall team performance, customer experience, and identify trends and opportunities for process improvements</li><li>Building team performance dashboards and comprehensive scorecards to provide transparent reporting and insight into the health of our business to enable our team to quickly capture customer, product, and team performance insights</li><li>Building and maintaining workforce planning models to forecast staffing needs, monitor performance metrics, and identifying/enforcing these opportunities for improvement</li><li>Present and communicate data-backed recommendations to leadership and our internal partners to drive Product Support initiatives and help facilitate the decision-making process</li><li>Monitoring and Evaluating the impact of process changes and initiatives, providing ongoing feedback and suggesting refinements</li><li>Collaborating with our data science and engineering teams to build, document, and manage our Product Support data structure<br><br></li></ul>We'd love to hear from you if you have:<br><br><ul><li>Experience supporting a technical SaaS company in a senior analyst capacity</li><li>Familiarity with SQL and querying databases using tools like Tableau, Mode, Looker, or Zendesk Explore (we use Mode and Explore)</li><li>Solid understanding of statistical analysis and data modeling techniques</li><li>A passion for using data and analytics to answer questions and support decisions</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including the ability to present technical findings to non-technical stakeholders in a clear and concise manner</li><li>Deep technical capability and understanding of product support strategies</li><li>Excellent decision quality and creative problem solving skills<br><br></li></ul>At Figma, one of our values is Grow as you go. We believe in hiring smart, curious people who are excited to learn and develop their skills. If you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with the points outlined in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyways. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.<br><br>Read more about our team<br><br><ul><li>Investing in Figma: The Decade of Design</li><li>How work is changing at Figma</li><li>Figma's next product is a multiplayer whiteboard called FigJam</li><li>Software Design Startup Figma Is Now Worth $10 Billion<br><br></li></ul><strong>Pay Transparency Disclosure<br><br></strong>If based in Figma’s San Francisco or New York hub offices, this role has the annual base salary range stated below.<br><br>Job level and actual compensation will be decided based on factors including, but not limited to, individual qualifications objectively assessed during the interview process (including skills and prior relevant experience, potential impact, and scope of role), market demands, and specific work location. The listed range is a guideline, and the range for this role may be modified. For roles that are available to be filled remotely, the pay range is localized according to employee work location by a factor of between 80% and 100% of range. Please discuss your specific work location with your recruiter for more information.<br><br>Figma offers equity to employees, as well a competitive package of additional benefits, including health, dental &amp; vision, retirement with company contribution, parental leave &amp; reproductive or family planning support, mental health &amp; wellness benefits, generous PTO, company recharge days, a learning &amp; development stipend, a work from home stipend, and cell phone reimbursement. Figma also offers sales incentive pay for most sales roles. Figma’s compensation and benefits are subject to change and may be modified in the future. You may view our Pay Transparency Policy by clicking on the corresponding link.<br><br>Annual Base Salary Range (SF/NY Hub):<br><br>$99,000—$210,000 USD<br><br>At Figma we celebrate and support our differences. We know employing a team rich in diverse thoughts, experiences, and opinions allows our employees, our product and our community to flourish. Figma is an equal opportunity workplace - we are dedicated to equal employment opportunities regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity/expression, veteran status<strong>, </strong>or any other characteristic protected by law. If you require accommodation, please reach out to accommodations-ext@figma.com.<br><br>By applying for this job, the candidate acknowledges and agrees that any personal data contained in their application or supporting materials will be processed in accordance with the applicable candidate section of Figma's Privacy Policy.

job_title: Data and Policy Analyst - Statistical Programmer
desc: At Acumen, LLC / The SPHERE Institute, Data and Policy Analysts provide analytical support for research and consulting projects for government and private clients, primarily in the area of health policy. This position is responsible for managing and analyzing data, researching and interpreting policy, and communicating findings to multiple audiences.<br><br>Data and Policy Analysts perform a wide array of functions as part of the research process. Those applicants interested in focusing on statistical programming help create and report descriptive statistic, conduct econometric and statistical analyses of data using statistical software such as SAS and STATA, interpret study specifications, research findings, and quantitative analyses for relevant audiences, develop research files from large confidential datasets, and perform other duties as assigned.<br><br>As we review your materials, we are looking for candidates who best exemplify the following qualifications:<br><br><strong>Qualifications Required:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative, public policy, or related field or equivalent relevant experience</li><li>Prior work experience is not necessary</li><li>Good quantitative analytical skills</li><li>Good oral and written communication skills</li><li>Good organizational skills and strong attention to detail</li><li>Familiar with one or more of the following technical competencies: statistics, programming, policy writing, research methods documentation, or project management</li><li>Able to demonstrate initiative, critical thinking, and problem-solving</li><li>Able to work in a team-oriented environment</li><li>Able to prioritize tasks and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Demonstrated aptitude and enthusiasm for learning<br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications Desired:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Demonstrates an interest in health and social policy</li><li>Master's degree in a quantitative, public policy, or related field or equivalent relevant experience<br><br></li></ul>$50,000 - $110,000 a year<br><br>Any application without a cover letter will not be considered. Transcripts and coding samples are not required, however highly preferred and may be requested. We are excited to review your application and look forward to seeing how you may best contribute to our work.<br><br>Please note, this position is available in our Burlingame, CA office.<br><br>The salary range for this position is $50,000- $110,000; consideration for higher compensation may be made for candidates with advanced qualifications.
