<strong>Company Description<br><br></strong>Xcel Agency is a leading digital marketing agency that specializes in helping global brands of all sizes increase their online visibility and reach their target audience. We help evolve and transform your data into best-in-class customer journeys that allow you to deepen customer relationships and drive revenue. With a robust team of experienced marketers, Xcel Agency offers a wide range of services to help businesses grow, including email marketing automation, social media marketing, search engine optimization, digital media services, and more. Our email marketing automation services help businesses create personalized and targeted campaigns that engage and convert customers, while its digital media services, including PPC advertising and social media advertising, drive targeted traffic to websites and generate leads and sales. With a focus on innovation, creativity, and results, Xcel Agency is the go-to partner for businesses looking to enhance their digital presence and drive growth.<br><br><strong>Job Description<br><br></strong>We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced data analyst to join our email marketing team. As an email marketing data analyst, you will be responsible for analyzing, interpreting, and making actionable insights from email campaign data to optimize email marketing strategy and drive business growth. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop and implement data-driven solutions to improve customer engagement, increase conversions, and enhance overall customer experience.<br><br><strong>What you’ll be doing:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Develop and maintain data models and algorithms to drive insights into email campaign performance and customer behavior. </li><li>Analyze email marketing data to identify patterns, trends, and opportunities to optimize email campaigns and increase customer engagement and conversions. </li><li>Develop and implement testing plans for email campaigns, including A/B testing, to optimize campaign performance and drive continuous improvement. </li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including marketing, product, and engineering, to develop and implement data-driven solutions to improve email campaign performance and customer experience. </li><li>Provide regular reports and dashboards to communicate campaign performance and insights to key stakeholders. </li><li>Stay up-to-date with industry trends and best practices in email marketing, data analysis, and machine learning techniques to drive innovation and continuous improvement. <br><br></li></ul>Qualifications<br><br><strong>What we’re looking for:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Agency experience preferred working with enterprise clients. </li><li>Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or a related field. Master's or Ph.D. preferred. </li><li>Minimum of 3 years of experience in data analysis and modeling, with a focus on email marketing. </li><li>Strong analytical skills and experience with data modeling, segmentation, and predictive analytics. </li><li>Proficient in data analysis tools such as SQL, R, or Python. </li><li>Experience with marketing automation tools such as Marketo, Eloqua, or Salesforce Marketing Cloud. </li><li>Experience with A/B testing, experimental design, and statistical analysis. </li><li>Excellent communication skills, with the ability to clearly communicate complex data insights to non-technical stakeholders. </li><li>Experience on the Eloqua platform. <br><br></li></ul>Additional Information<br><br>If you are a highly analytical and data-driven individual with a passion for email marketing and customer engagement, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity!<br><br>We are an equal opportunity employer and do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity, or any other legally protected status. We strive to create a workplace that reflects the communities we serve and welcome individuals from all backgrounds to apply.<br><br>This is a remote, contract position. Must reside in the United States.

As a highly collaborative organization, our data engineers work cross-functionally with software engineering, data science, and product management to optimize growth, strategy, and experience for our 3 billion plus users, as well as our internal employee community. In this role, you will see a direct correlation between your work, company growth, and user satisfaction. Beyond this, you will work with some of the brightest minds in the industry, and you'll have a unique opportunity to solve some of the most interesting data challenges with efficiency and integrity, at a scale few companies can match.<br><br>Data Engineer, Product Analytics Responsibilities:<br><br><ul><li>Conceptualize and own the data architecture for multiple large-scale projects, while to triage issues and resolve.</li><li>Collaborate with engineers, product managers, and data scientists to understand data needs, representing key data insights visually in a meaningful way.</li><li>Define and manage SLA for all data sets in allocated areas of ownership.</li><li>Determine and implement the security model based on privacy requirements, confirm safeguards are followed, address data quality issues, and evolve governance processes within allocated areas of ownership.</li><li>Design, build, and launch collections of sophisticated data models and visualizations that support multiple use cases across different products or domains.</li><li>Solve our most challenging data integration problems, utilizing optimal ETL patterns, frameworks, query techniques, sourcing from structured and unstructured data sources.</li><li>Assist in owning existing processes running in production, optimizing complex code through advanced algorithmic concepts.</li><li>Optimize pipelines, dashboards, frameworks, and systems to facilitate easier development of data artifacts.</li><li>Influence product and cross-functional teams to identify data opportunities to drive impact.</li><li>Mentor team members by giving/receiving actionable feedback.<br><br></li></ul>Minimum Qualifications:<br><br><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, relevant technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>5+ years experience in the data warehouse space.</li><li>5+ years experience in custom ETL design, implementation and maintenance.</li><li>5+ years experience with object-oriented programming languages.</li><li>7+ years experience with schema design and dimensional data modeling.</li><li>7+ years experience in writing SQL statements.</li><li>Experience analyzing data to identify gaps and inconsistencies.</li><li>Experience managing and communicating data warehouse plans to internal clients.<br><br></li></ul>Preferred Qualifications:<br><br><ul><li>Master's or Ph.D degree in a STEM field</li><li>Experience with one or more of the following: data processing automation, data job_title: Research Data Analyst 2 (2 Years Fixed Term)
desc: The Center for Population Health Sciences (PHS) at Stanford University School of Medicine is seeking a Research Data Analyst 2 (2-year fixed term) for data management, data analysis, and data science work focused on population health and health equity serving the American Family Cohort Consortium. The American Family Cohort (AFC) is a national EHR dataset comprised of over 7 million unique individuals from a variety of sources. These data have been used for research in health economics, health services and health equity. We seek an individual with an interest in population health and primary care, health equity, quality and continuity. The ideal applicant will have experience in AI, ML or NLP in EHR data or a strong interest in applying these methods to primary care.<br><br>The Research Data Analyst will specifically work on a project in collaboration between PHS the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). The main research includes monitoring COVID-19 hot spots and trends, and to obtain the analytic products and deliverables to inform the COVID-19 emergency public health response and working closely with physician collaborators on quality and continuity metrics in clinical care both before and during the pandemic. Although the project is for a fixed 2 years term, it is likely the position is extended indefinitely as other opportunities arise at PHS and the AFC research cohort expands.<br><br>This position will be primarily responsible for managing and analyzing AFC, a large, rich, national EHR dataset. The applicant should be comfortable with data management and cleaning and statistical analyses. The Research Data Analyst is expected to be exposed to working in the cloud environment and learning machine learning techniques. The role requires working independently with minimal supervision, as well as communicating results in code, orally, and in writing to internal and external researchers and stakeholders. This position will also be expected to curate and create new derivative datasets and perform data management procedures, including data security, as well as train and update other researchers and staff on these procedures. In addition, the position requires project management skills helping to move projects along for internal and external collaborators and assisting in the design and management of new projects. This position provides ample opportunity for first author publications.<br><br><strong>About Center For Population Health Sciences<br><br></strong>We enter the world with a set of genes that determine many factors of our health. From that moment forward, every aspect of our lives affects our health. There is unequivocal evidence that social, environmental, and behavioral factors are by far the strongest predictors of health and disease. Founded in 2015, the Stanford Center for Population Health Sciences' (PHS) mission is to improve population health by bringing together diverse disciplines and data to better understand and address the social and environmental determinants of health. This position will work with PHS’s most valuable datasets to advance the goal of reducing premature morbidity and mortality and disparities in health outcomes.<br><br><strong>Duties Include<br><br></strong><ul><li>Prioritize and extract data from a variety of source including a large, national, granular, high value health dataset held by PHS. These datasets include EHRs, claims, survey data, medical reports, and laboratory data. The position will be expected to perform quality checks and ensure data are accurate and complete.</li><li>Determine additional data collection and reporting requirements.</li><li>Design and customize reports based upon data in the database. Monitor regulatory compliance for utilization of the data.</li><li>Perform data quality checks to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and eliminate root cause for data problems or justify solutions to be implemented by others.</li><li>Create complex charts and databases, perform statistical analyses, and develop graphs and tables for publication and presentation.</li><li>Serve as a resource for non-routine inquiries such as requests for statistics or surveys.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li> - Other duties may also be assigned<br><br><br></li></ul>This role is open to candidates anywhere in the United States. Stanford University has five Regional Pay Structures . The compensation for this position will be based on the location of the successful candidate. The expected pay range for this position is $72,000 to $126,000 per annum.<br><br>Stanford University provides pay ranges representing its good faith estimate of what the university reasonably expects to pay for a position. The pay offered to a selected candidate will be determined based on factors such as (but not limited to) the scope and responsibilities of the position, the qualifications of the selected candidate, departmental budget availability, internal equity, geographic location, and external market pay for comparable jobs.<br><br><strong>Desired Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Minimum 2 years of experience with Python programming and its data analysis packages.</li><li>Expertise in SQL for data management and data analysis.</li><li>Expertise and experience conducting statistical analyses.</li><li>Experience using cloud environment such as Google Cloud or AWS is a plus.</li><li>Experience working with large datasets is a plus.</li><li>Academic or practical training in public health epidemiology, research methodology, database construction, and biostatistics is a plus.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Education &amp; Experience (required)<br><br></strong>Bachelor's degree and three years of relevant experience or combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.<br><br><strong>Knowledge, Skills And Abilities (required)<br><br></strong><ul><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.</li><li>Excellent writing and analytical skills.</li><li>Ability to prioritize workload.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Certifications &amp; Licenses<br><br></strong>None<br><br><strong>PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.</li><li>Occasionally use a telephone.</li><li>Rarely writing by hand.</li><li> - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.<br><br><br></li></ul><strong>Working Conditions<br><br></strong>Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting.<br><br><strong>Work Standards<br><br></strong><ul><li>Interpersonal Skills: Demonstrates the ability to work well with Stanford colleagues and clients and with external organizations.</li><li>Promote Culture of Safety: Demonstrates commitment to personal responsibility and value for safety; communicates safety concerns; uses and promotes safe behaviors based on training and lessons learned.</li><li>Subject to and expected to comply with all applicable University policies and procedures, including but not limited to the personnel policies and other policies found in the University's Administrative Guide, http://adminguide.stanford.edu. <br><br><br></li></ul>As an organization that receives federal funding, Stanford University has a COVID-19 vaccination requirement that will apply to all university employees, including those working remotely in the United States and applicable subcontractors. To learn more about COVID policies and guidelines for Stanford University Staff, please visit https://cardinalatwork.stanford.edu/working-stanford/covid-19/interim-policies/covid-19-surveillance-testing-policy<br><br>Additional Information<br><br><ul><li> Schedule: Full-time </li><li> Job Code: 4752 </li><li> Employee Status: Regular </li><li> Grade: I </li><li> Requisition ID: 96070 </li><li> Work Arrangement : Remote Eligible</li></ul>

<p><strong>About Second Harvest of Silicon Valley</strong></p><p>Founded in 1974, Second Harvest of Silicon Valley is one of the largest food banks in the nation and a trusted nonprofit leader in ending local hunger. The organization distributes nutritious groceries through a network of nearly 400 partners at drive-thru and walk-up sites across Santa Clara and San Mateo counties. Due to the prohibitively expensive cost of living in Silicon Valley, the economic downturn caused by the COVID-19 pandemic, and the rise in inflation, Second Harvest is now serving an average of about 500,000 people every month. Second Harvest also connects people to federal nutrition programs and other food resources, and advocates for anti-hunger policies on the local, state and national levels. To learn more about how Second Harvest is responding to the incredible amount of need in Silicon Valley, visit shfb.org.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>About the Position</strong></p><p>As the Senior Data Analyst, Leadership Gifts in the Development department, you will be a valued, strategic business partner to the Leadership Gifts team (who stewards individual, corporate and foundation donors who each give $10,000 or more per year). You will also support the fundraising efforts for our $150M multi-year Capital Campaign. You will work in close collaboration with the fundraisers and use your business acumen, technical skills, and knowledge of fundraising to maximize fundraising effectiveness. </p><p><br></p><p>The Senior Data Analyst will proactively conceive and design reports and analyses, explain the narrative behind the findings, and make practical recommendations. Your varied analyses will draw on and combine data from numerous sources including Salesforce, iWave, a new data lake, and third-party demographic data and will employ predictive analytic techniques where possible. You will manage the vendor relationship with iWave including the annual budget, and stay current with product releases, informing the team when new relevant features become available. You will prepare pledge forms in DocuSign, troubleshooting as necessary to ensure they are functioning properly.</p><p><br></p><p>The Senior Data Analyst will also play a key role in transitioning our analytics to Salesforce and an upcoming data lake. All existing reports and dashboards will need to be evaluated for relevance and rewritten to use Salesforce and/or the data lake as the data source. In addition, new dashboards and reports will need to be created that leverage the capabilities of Salesforce.</p><p>In this role, you will be a member of a flexible and supportive work environment that fosters creativity and collaboration. Everyone on the team is passionate about the mission of the organization and doing work that is personally meaningful.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>This job might be for you if:</strong></p><ul><li>You are passionate about ending hunger. </li><li>You have excellent attention to detail, an inquisitive mind, and you enjoy conducting customized analysis and building reports to find answers to business questions. </li><li>You are self-directed and can conceive of and translate business questions into actionable analytics.</li><li>You enjoy learning about and helping to implement new technologies.</li><li>You like collaborating with staff from other departments and with peers in the Analytics team.</li><li>You can help identify fundraising opportunities and improvements based on existing and emerging data trends.<strong> </strong></li><li>You can steward sensitive information with the utmost integrity and confidentiality.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Gathering requirements and conducting analysis to answer complex questions, developing plans &amp; requirements, and tracking key performance indicators to inform Leadership Gifts strategy.</li><li>Defining, developing, and maintaining dashboards, custom ad-hoc analysis, and tailored reports in Salesforce, Power BI, and Excel in collaboration with stakeholders.</li><li>Training staff on how to use and interpret data in dashboards and reports.</li><li>Presenting conclusions from the data and recommending appropriate course of action.</li><li>Documenting workflows and the results of business analysis.</li><li>Performing other duties as assigned to achieve Second Harvest of Silicon Valley’s goals and objectives.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>The ideal candidate will possess the following professional qualifications:</strong> </p><ul><li>Advanced skills with Microsoft Excel and database queries/reports are required. Experience with Salesforce, Power BI, iWave and SQL are highly desired.</li><li>Strong analytical skills, a curious nature, demonstrated initiative, and the business acumen necessary to synthesize data and formulate a narrative and/or recommendations that inform practical business decisions.</li><li>Ability to create visualizations, dashboards and tools that provide insights and guidance for practical business decisions.</li><li>Strong written, verbal and presentation skills.</li><li>Excellent organizational skills, detail-orientation, and a commitment to accuracy</li><li>Experience building relationships with a diverse group of internal constituents.</li><li>Bachelor’s degree or higher in Data Analytics, Business Management, Economics, Information Science, or related field preferred.</li><li>5 years of experience in data analysis role. Experience within a fundraising department or nonprofit organization strongly desired.</li><li><strong>Genuine interest in the mission and activities of a food bank</strong></li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Reports To</strong></p><p>Data Analytics Manager</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Location</strong></p><p>Second Harvest Food Bank, Cypress Center. 4001 North First Street, San Jose CA 95134</p><p>This is a hybrid position. Specifics of work location will depend on department need.</p><p>An employee’s regular remote work site should be within driving distance of one of Second Harvest’s locations and must be within the state of California.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Hours</strong></p><p>Full-Time Exempt. 40 hours/week, with some evening and weekend work as necessary. </p><p><br></p><p><strong>Compensation </strong></p><p>$78,309 – $92,128 is the wage range for this position. The salary wage offer will be commensurate with skills and experience. Outstanding and generous health benefits program, 4-5 weeks of Flexible Time Off (vacation and sick), eleven paid holidays, and retirement plan.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>SH Covid-19 Vaccine Policy</strong></p><p>Second Harvest Food Bank places great importance on the safety of its employees and customers. Therefore, in line with the CDC and state and local recommendations, Second Harvest requires as a condition of employment that employees have received full and effective COVID vaccines prior to commencing employment. In accordance with applicable law, Second Harvest will consider good faith requests for reasonable accommodation based on medical disability or sincerely held religious belief.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>EOE</strong></p><p>Second Harvest is committed to being an equal opportunity employer which values diversity. Under-represented groups are encouraged to apply for all positions. ­</p>

Department of Neurology - Memory and Aging Center<br><br>Full Time<br><br>75007BR<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>We are looking for a <strong>Data Analyst Manager </strong>for the Multitudes Project. The Multitudes Project is a California State founded project aiming to bridge Neuroscience and public schools with the intent to develop a battery for early detection and intervention for children with Dyslexia.<br><br>The Data Analyst Manager will be the core of the data organization throughout the Multitudes project. This includes collaborations with other institutions, universities, school districts and other stakeholders involved in data collection, analysis, and interpretation. This position will be central in coordinating the effort to create a strong data pipeline architecture for a wide variety of research data pertinent to the project.<br><br>The Data Analyst Manager will help design and conduct research including selecting data samples, developing research instruments, analyzing collected information according to established statistical methods, and developing recommendations based on research findings. The role will also imply supervision of the junior analyst(s) and collaboration with other stakeholders in preparing reports, charts, tables, and other visual aids to interpret and diffuse data and results.<br><br>The ideal candidate will be experienced professional who knows how to apply theory and put it into practice with in-depth understanding of the professional field; independently performs the full range of responsibilities within the function; possesses broad job knowledge; analyzes problems / issues of diverse scope and determines solutions. The Data Analyst Manager will need to have Project Management skills to keep stakeholders aligned, has the ability to envision a future data architecture to support Artificial Intelligence and predictive analytic models to create innovative approaches to precision science and research to guide progressive, science based, result driven personalized interventions.<br><br>The Data Analyst Manager will work with Multitudes faculty and data science team to manage, communicate, and analyze data pertaining to all aspects of a complex multi-institutional project. Uses skills as a seasoned, experienced research professional with a full understanding of in-depth statistical analyses and research software programming techniques. Demonstrates good judgment in selecting methods and techniques for answering specific queries in the service of research and development and will report to the COO.<br><br>The role also involves technical acumen for planning, designing, developing, implementing and administering data-based systems that acquire, prepare, store and provide access to data and metadata. Maintains and optimizes systems and migrates data and systems as needed. Ensures integrity and completeness of data and workflow, manages and / or develops data practices, databases and information systems as well as guidelines, dictionaries, registries and / or services. Interpretation of scientific research data artifacts as well as mediation across science and technology domains and long-term data care. As information architect and data steward, designs systems, data products and / or data production processes while focusing on data curation, data exchange, data security, data integrity and information environments. (Re)evaluates frameworks, strategies, standards and standards-making activities. Involve work with a project-level data repository, a center or an archive.<br><br>Additional responsibilities- conduct psychometric analyses using classical test theory, item response theory, equating to support product development Communicate technical psychometric concepts orally and in writing to all customer bases, including non-technical audiences. Work with cross-functional teams to problem-solve and find solutions for product development. With supervision, analyze, research, and propose solutions to current and future measurement problems, and communicate those solutions effectively.<br><br><ul><li>NOTE: This is an 1-year Contract role from the date of hire. <br><br></li></ul><strong>To see the salary range for this position (we recommend that you make a note of the job code and use that to look up):</strong> TCS Non-Academic Titles Search (ucop.edu)<br><br>Please note: The compensation ranges listed online for roles not covered by a bargaining unit agreement are very wide, however a job offer will typically fall in the range of 80% - 120% of the established mid-point. An offer will take into consideration the experience of the final candidate AND the current salary level of individuals working at UCSF in a similar role.<br><br>For roles covered by a bargaining unit agreement, there will be specific rules about where a new hire would be placed on the range.<br><br>To learn more about the benefits of working at UCSF, including total compensation, please visit: https://ucnet.universityofcalifornia.edu/compensation-and-benefits/index.html<br><br><strong>Department Description<br><br></strong>The UCSF Dyslexia Center is developing a new digital tool, Multitudes. Free for all California public schools, this platform aids in the early identification of Kindergarten and First Grade students who may face challenges learning to read. Early identification can lead to early intervention. With the right support, more California students can learn to read with greater ease, leading to more equitable educational and health outcomes. Multitudes is led by the part of the Dyslexia Center located in the ALBA Language Neurobiology lab. The ALBA Language Neurobiology laboratory in the UCSF Neurology Department’s Memory and Aging Center is directed by Dr. Maria Luisa Gorno Tempini. We study how language is organized into brain networks across the lifespan. Our group researches how language skills and brain regions are impacted by neurological conditions and how they reorganize in response. Our multidisciplinary team correlates behavioral research with multimodal neuroimaging techniques to understand the neural underpinning of higher cognitive functions such as speech, language, and memory. In particular, we research two syndromes: Primary Progressive Aphasia and Dyslexia. Dr. Gorno Tempini is also co-director of the UCSF Dyslexia Center and the UCSF|UC Berkeley Schwab Center for Dyslexia and Cognitive Diversity. These centers aim to eliminate the debilitating effects of developmental dyslexia while supporting the relative strengths of each individual. We develop best practice protocols to assess and diagnose children with dyslexia and other learning differences through a multimodal cognitive and neuroimaging program. We work closely with schools and educators to develop early interventions and educational strategies to help children with dyslexia thrive.<br><br>The Multitudes Project is part of the Memory and Aging Center (MAC) is the largest division within the Department of Neurology with a diverse workforce of over 260 employees. The Department of Neurology is a teaching, research and clinical care unit within the School of Medicine (SOM). The Department of Neurology is a large, multi-site department, with locations including Mission Bay, Parnassus, Mt. Zion, ZSFG, VAMC and the Gladstone Institutes, and is affiliated with the UCSF Weill Institute for Neurosciences. The department is constructed of 14 administrative divisions with 11 clinical specialties. The department has over 230 faculty and academic employees, 290 staff positions, and 170 trainees including: residents, clinical fellows and postdoctoral scholars.<br><br>The Department has an annual operating budget in excess of $120M and has been the #1 recipient of NIH funding across all U.S. Departments of Neurology for the past 6 consecutive years, in addition to being the #1 recipient of philanthropic dollars across all departments at UCSF.<br><br>Our department’s mission includes delivering the most exceptional clinical care to our patients, leading transformative cutting-edge research, and training the leaders of tomorrow in both neurology and neuroscience. Our department’s faculty, trainees, and staff work at a university and in a community that values and embraces diversity and strives to make an impact worldwide through our global and public health efforts.<br><br><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Bachelor's degree in related area and / or equivalent experience / training. </li><li> 5 years of experience in the related fields. </li><li> Proven modeling and information design skills. </li><li> Conduct psychometric analyses in support of a testing program </li><li> Understanding of concepts central to psychometrics: classical test theory, equating, and item response theory </li><li> Experience using open-source statistical analysis software (e.g. R) and version control (e.g. GitHub). </li><li> Advanced analytical and design skills, including the ability to abstract information requirements from real-world processes to understand information flows in computer systems. </li><li> Advanced knowledge of data management systems, practices and standards. </li><li> Ability to analyze and research applied measurement problems, and, to propose solutions to those problems </li><li> Ability to represent relevant information in abstract models. Critical thinking skills and attention to detail. </li><li> Ability to prepare complex data models unassisted. </li><li> Familiarity with highly complex logical data design and data mapping or data conversion. </li><li> Demonstrated ability to work with others from diverse backgrounds. Demonstrated effective communication and interpersonal skills. Demonstrated service orientation skills. </li><li> Demonstrated ability to communicate technical information to technical and non-technical personnel at various levels in the organization. </li><li> Self-motivated and works independently and as part of a team. Strong organizational skills. </li><li> Demonstrated advanced problem-solving skills. Able to learn effectively and meet deadlines. </li><li> Good presentation, organizational, problem-solving, communication and customer service skills with attention to details and deadlines. </li><li> Ability to work cooperatively with cross - functional teams. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Doctorate (or near completion) in educational measurement, psychometrics, industrial/organizational psychology, or a closely related field. </li><li> Ability to understand and model complex knowledge-intensive processes such as scholarly and research processes. </li><li> Experience in data integration and the specification of data services. </li><li> Good negotiation and influencing skills. </li><li> Familiarity with highly complex data quality and governance issues and requirements. </li><li> Thorough knowledge of relevant rules and regulations. <br><br></li></ul><strong>About UCSF<br><br></strong>The University of California, San Francisco (UCSF) is a leading university dedicated to promoting health worldwide through advanced biomedical research, graduate-level education in the life sciences and health professions, and excellence in patient care. It is the only campus in the 10-campus UC system dedicated exclusively to the health sciences. We bring together the world’s leading experts in nearly every area of health. We are home to five Nobel laureates who have advanced the understanding of cancer, neurodegenerative diseases, aging and stem cells.<br><br><strong>Pride Values<br><br></strong>UCSF is a diverse community made of people with many skills and talents. We seek candidates whose work experience or community service has prepared them to contribute to our commitment to professionalism, respect, integrity, diversity and excellence – also known as our PRIDE values.<br><br>In addition to our PRIDE values, UCSF is committed to equity – both in how we deliver care as well as our workforce. We are committed to building a broadly diverse community, nurturing a culture that is welcoming and supportive, and engaging diverse ideas for the provision of culturally competent education, discovery, and patient care. Additional information about UCSF is available at diversity.ucsf.edu<br><br>Join us to find a rewarding career contributing to improving healthcare worldwide.<br><br><strong>Equal Employment Opportunity<br><br></strong>The University of California San Francisco is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, protected veteran or disabled status, or genetic information.<br><br><strong>Organization<br><br></strong>Campus<br><br><strong>Job Code and Payroll Title<br><br></strong>000599 DATA SYS ANL 4<br><br><strong>Job Category<br><br></strong>Clinical Systems / IT Professionals, Professional and Managerial<br><br><strong>Bargaining Unit<br><br></strong>99 - Policy-Covered (No Bargaining Unit)<br><br><strong>Employee Class<br><br></strong>Contract<br><br><strong>Percentage<br><br></strong>100%<br><br><strong>Location<br><br></strong>China Basin (SF)<br><br><strong>Shift<br><br></strong>Days<br><br><strong>Shift Length<br><br></strong>8 Hours<br><br><strong>Additional Shift Details<br><br></strong>Monday - Friday; 9:00 AM - 6:00 PM

Situated in Stanford’s highly dynamic research environment the Curtis Laboratory ( http://med.stanford.edu/curtislab.html ), led by Christina Curtis, PhD, is seeking a bioinformatician/Research Data Analyst 1 to join the Cancer Computational and Systems Biology group. The Curtis Laboratory is administratively situated within the Stanford Cancer Institute and is integrated within Stanford University and the School of Medicine’s Departments of Medicine (Oncology) and Genetics. The SCI is part of a Comprehensive National Cancer Institute Cancer Center for cross-disciplinary research in cancer biology involving researchers from oncology, radiobiology, computer science, genetics, statistics, and basic/translational clinical research. Our research couples state-of-the-art computational and experimental techniques to define novel therapeutic targets and biomarkers and to characterize tumor evolution.<p><br></p>The successful candidate will be part of an interdisciplinary research team developing novel technological and methodological approaches to improve the diagnosis, treatment and earlier detection of cancer. He/she will analyze and interpret large sequencing datasets by applying and developing bioinformatics and statistical methods for whole genome/exome sequencing, RNA-seq, ATAC-seq, single cell and spatial datasets. The successful candidate will interact closely with other computational and experimental biologists and clinicians to test, validate, and refine hypotheses. This is a fantastic opportunity for a motivated bioinformatician or computational genomicist to join a dynamic team with significant opportunities for scholarship.<p><br></p><strong>Duties Include</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Collect, manage and clean datasets.</li><li>Employ new and existing tools to interpret, analyze, and visualize multivariate relationships in data.</li><li>Create databases and reports, develop algorithms and statistical models, and perform statistical analyses appropriate to data and reporting requirements.</li><li>Use system reports and analyses to identify potentially problematic data, make corrections, and determine root cause for data problems from input errors or inadequate field edits, and suggest possible solutions.</li><li>Develop reports, charts, graphs and tables for use by investigators and for publication and presentation.</li><li>Analyze data processes in documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with faculty and research staff on data collection and analysis methods.</li><li>Provide documentation based on audit and reporting criteria to investigators and research staff.</li><li>Communicate with government officials, grant agencies and industry representatives.</li><li> - Other duties may also be assigned</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Desired Qualifications</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Bioinformatics, Computer Science or a related field with one year (min) of relevant experience </li><li>Strong background in bioinformatics and biostatistics, including analysis of high-throughput sequencing data</li><li>Experience working within a UNIX/Linux environment</li><li>Fluency in programming languages such as Perl, Python, Java, R, C, Matlab; MySQL</li><li>Excellent communication and team skills and fluency in both spoken and written English</li><li>Familiarity with machine learning, information theory and signal processing.</li><li>Experience with algorithm development</li><li>Familiarity with basic molecular biology</li><li>Background in cancer biology</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Education &amp; Experience (required)</strong><p><br></p>Bachelor's degree or a combination of education and relevant experience. Experience in a quantitative discipline such as economics, finance, statistics or engineering.<p><br></p><strong>Knowledge, Skills And Abilities (required)</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Substantial experience with MS Office and analytical programs.</li><li>Strong writing and analytical skills.</li><li>Ability to prioritize workload.</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS*:</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Sitting in place at computer for long periods of time with extensive keyboarding/dexterity.</li><li>Occasionally use a telephone.</li><li>Rarely writing by hand.</li><li> - Consistent with its obligations under the law, the University will provide reasonable accommodation to any employee with a disability who requires accommodation to perform the essential functions of his or her job.</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Working Conditions</strong><p><br></p>Some work may be performed in a laboratory or field setting.<p><br></p><strong>Work Standards</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Interpersonal Skills: Demonstrates the ability to work well with Stanford colleagues and clients and with external organizations.</li><li>Promote Culture of Safety: Demonstrates commitment to personal responsibility and value for safety; communicates safety concerns; uses and promotes safe behaviors based on training and lessons learned.</li><li>Subject to and expected to comply with all applicable University policies and procedures, including but not limited to the personnel policies and other policies found in the University's Administrative Guide, http://adminguide.stanford.edu .</li></ul><p><br></p>As an organization that receives federal funding, Stanford University has a COVID-19 vaccination requirement that will apply to all university employees, including those working remotely in the United States and applicable subcontractors. To learn more about COVID policies and guidelines for Stanford University Staff, please visit https://cardinalatwork.stanford.edu/working-stanford/covid-19/interim-policies/covid-19-surveillance-testing-policy<p><br></p>Additional Information<p><br></p><ul><li> Schedule: Full-time </li><li> Job Code: 4751 </li><li> Employee Status: Regular </li><li> Grade: G </li><li> Requisition ID: 95360</li></ul>

The SCI is part of a Comprehensive National Cancer Institute Cancer Center for cross-disciplinary research in cancer biology involving researchers from oncology, radiobiology, computer science, genetics, statistics, and basic/translational clinical research. We are looking for candidates who do great work, and we hope they come from a number of different backgrounds and experiences. We aspire to build an increasingly diverse, equitable, and inclusive workplace. We encourage you to apply even if you do not believe you meet every qualification for the position but possess transferable skills and experience.<br><br><strong>Job Summary<br><br></strong>Under the direction and general supervision of the URIS Associate Director, Business Analysis &amp; Systems Support Services, the Information Systems Business Analyst is responsible for analyzing and documenting requirements for, and strategizing, overseeing, and reporting on specified day-to-day work and projects to implement, maintain, improve, and upgrade the information management technology and associated business processes and solutions that support UR in carrying out its mission.<br><br>The Data Management Business Analyst is primarily responsible for supporting technical systems, designing and documenting processes and procedures associated with the Information Management data processing services; this includes support of data entry, data quality, data integrations, online giving systems, and document imaging/management systems.<br><br><strong>APPOINTMENT INFORMATION<br><br></strong><strong>Budgeted Salary:</strong> $29.24 - $38.91/hour. Salary commensurate with skills, qualifications and experience.<br><br>Under California law, the University of California, Santa Cruz is required to post a reasonable estimate of the compensation for this role. The salary shown above is the budgeted amount the University reasonably expects to pay and the salary extended should not exceed this posted amount.<br><br><strong>Benefits Level Eligibility:</strong> Full benefits<br><br><strong>Schedule Information<br><br></strong><ul><li> Full-time, Fixed </li><li> Percentage of Time: 100%, 40 Hours per Week </li><li> Days of the Week: Mon-Fri </li><li> Shift Includes: Day <br><br></li></ul><strong>Employee Classification:</strong> Career appointment<br><br><strong>Job End Date:</strong> None<br><br><strong>Work Location:</strong> Remote<br><br><strong>Union Representation:</strong> Non-Represented<br><br><strong>Job Code Classification:</strong> 007582 (BUS SYS ANL 1)<br><br><strong>Travel:</strong> Never or Rarely<br><br><strong>Job Duties<br><br></strong>80% - Information Management Systems Analysis, Maintenance, and Technical Support<br><br><ul><li>Under the direction and general supervision of the Associate Director, Business Analysis &amp; Systems Support Services:</li><ul><li>Elicit and manage functional and user experience requirements for new systems being implemented:</li><ul><li>Specify and document business and process requirements.</li><li>Work with functional teams and vendors to understand applications/solutions from a functional perspective.</li><li>Document all data integration and data management requirements.</li><li>Document application configurations, and ensure all test planning is appropriate, adequately comprehensive, and well documented.</li><li>Manage testing and quality assurance process and ensure this is adequately completed prior to release to production of any component.</li><li>Map data for API, application-based, and manually enabled data integrations (e.g. campus and 3rd party systems) for existing and new needs/business processes.</li><li>Troubleshoot problems related to Data Management systems user experience, data entry, and data interfaces/integrations. Work with technical programming staff and other business and user analysts to devise and implement solutions. Oversee testing of solutions, and directly work with and guide end-users to integrate the solutions into their business processes and/or procedures.</li></ul><li>Define and lead development and implementation of solutions, tools, and processes within Information Management systems to support new and/or improved procedures for Data Management.</li><li>Analyze, specify design and testing; and oversee testing of systems, processes, and reports intended to solve issues and/or improve gift processing, data integrations, and data integrity. This Involves working closely with technical and end-user staff in UR, ITS, and sometimes other campus divisions to develop functional specifications and test cases for solutions.</li><li>Provide detailed functional specifications to technical programming staff for modifications or enhancements to existing systems that support Data Management. This includes defining specifications for changes in business processes and the supporting applications/systems and data reports.</li><li>Assist in assessing the impact of hardware, operating system, CRM, and integrated system upgrades and modifications on gift administration and data management/processing.</li><li>Investigate and report on any vendor-provided known issues that adversely impact gift administration and data management/processing.</li><li>Support the Associate Director, Business Analysis &amp; Systems Support Services and other business analysts in the review of modification requests from users that may affect the technology and business processes of the functional areas you support to determine feasibility, benefit, and effort required to plan and implement.</li><li>Work with Associate Director, Business Analysis &amp; Systems Support Services, other business analysts, and the technical programming staff to determine which modifications should be implemented and to prioritize the requirements backlog. Develop functional specifications for the modifications and work with technical programming staff to implement modifications.</li><li>Evaluate technical and reporting-related functionality changes of systems upgrades provided by the vendor (e.g. Salesforce, Affinaquest, ImageNow) as these upgrades might affect business processes. Develop specifications for any modifications that need to be made to the upgraded software and reporting in order to meet business needs. Work with technical programming and Information Management staff to plan, test, and implement the modifications.</li><li>As trained to do so, provide systems administration and technical support of Data Management user experience design, data entry, data quality, data integrations, data reporting, and other data management solutions which may be supported by URIS.<br></li></ul></ul>20% - Project Management Assignments<br><br><ul><li>Under the direction and general supervision of the Associate Director, Business Analysis &amp; Systems Support Services:</li><ul><li>Utilize industry and campus standard project management techniques and methods.</li><li>Manage multiple projects or programs simultaneously as assigned and prioritized.</li><li>Conduct project feasibility analysis to determine the cost and implementation timeframe for proposed projects.</li><li>Develop project charters and/or plans to define the objectives, deliverables, approach, risk, resources, estimated cost and timeline for small projects and assist the project lead in developing project charters and/or plans for larger projects.</li><li>Monitor and report project results against technical and business requirements specifications as a key member of a project implementation team.</li><li>Develop and maintain business requirements specifications and documentation during the lifecycle of the project.</li><li>Confer with project staff, subject matter experts, and software application vendors to develop business requirements specifications and provide advice and resolve issues throughout the assigned project life cycle.</li><li>Provide leadership to work teams assembled to plan and implement new or improved business processes. This will involve working with staff members from a wide variety of UR and sometimes campus offices, developing project schedules, identifying tasks, tracking progress, and providing overall project management for small projects (and assisting in all of these areas on larger projects). This will frequently involve coordinating training and developing user documentation.</li><li>Take part in technical team meetings with appropriate ITS and URIS staff to ensure projects and business requirements that need ITS services and support are on track and integrated into the systems release schedule. If assigned, and when necessary, lead the agenda of these meetings to ensure URIS/ITS projects and requirements are delivered within the agreed upon timeline.<br></li></ul></ul><strong>Required Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Excellent oral communication skills sufficient to articulate complex information in a way that is comprehensible to a diverse audience; and including demonstrated ability to communicate technical information to technical and non- technical personnel at various levels in the organization.</li><li>Ability to work in a collaborative and cooperative manner, and to be an effective and productive member of a team and to maintain and develop relationships across the organization.</li><li>Demonstrated creative problem solving ability and ability to pay close attention to detail with a high degree of accuracy and autonomy in all work. Demonstrated organization skills sufficient to establish work priorities to handle a heavy workload, maintain accurate records, and complete tasks within deadlines established by your supervisor or established guidelines in an environment with changing priorities.</li><li>Demonstrated ability to develop and revise business processes, procedures, help and support documentation and related training materials; and to effectively participate in and oversee associated systems planning, process analysis, implementation, and upgrade projects.</li><li>Demonstrated ability to read, learn, interpret, and apply policies, rules, and regulations governing data stewardship/governance to all work.</li><li>Previous proven business process analysis experience and experience analyzing business needs and creating high- level and detailed functional requirements and specifications, both system (application) and data-focused (reporting &amp; data integration) to meet those needs; the ability to develop such specifications from vague and often changing requirements.</li><li>Experience in defining requirements for data integration between systems, data migration to a new system, and the specification of data services that include features/functions to ensure data quality and enforce business process and data governance rules/policies.</li><li>Skilled in the use of spreadsheets, word processing, and databases and at least some experience in the use of business process modeling tools such as Visio or Lucidchart and project management tools such as Smartsheet, Asana, Atlassian JIRA, or Microsoft Project, or Asana.</li><li>Excellent written communication skills necessary to create clear, concise, and effective correspondence, procedures, and training materials.</li><li>Ability to learn, use, and support the Affinaquest CRM (built on Salesforce), Perceptive Content, reporting tools and query languages (e.g. SQL, SOQL) with proficiency.</li><li>Two years or more of business analysis experience. Req Demonstrated experience in designing and developing training curriculum and materials and conducting in-person and remote training, particularly for business process training topics.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Advanced knowledge of data management systems, practices and standards; and familiarity with highly complex logical data design and data mapping and/or data conversion.</li><li>Experience in a development/advancement services unit which directly supports systems and services utilizing Salesforce.</li><li>Technical project management experience.</li><li>Experience in a higher education fundraising organization, specifically in the areas of multi-channel marketing (email, social, text), volunteer management, alumni and friends group membership management, automated customer engagement solutions, marketing and communications, and/or government and community relations.</li><li>Salesforce Administrator certification.<br><br></li></ul><strong>SPECIAL CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT<br><br></strong><ul><li> Selected candidate will be required to pass a pre-employment criminal history background check. </li><li>Ability to work long periods of time at a computer with or without accommodation.</li><li>The selected candidate will be required to work a hybrid work schedule and must be able to work successfully from a home/remote office and fulfill the requirements of the UCSC telecommuting agreement.</li><li>This position requires the ability to report to campus to work in-person as operationally required, with reasonable notice as determined by your manager; travel expenses not covered.</li><li>Ability to work a variable schedule including evenings and weekends.</li><li>Ability to maintain appearance and conduct suitable for working in a professional setting.</li><li>The University of California has implemented a Vaccination Policy covering all employees. CANRA Penal Codes, and related definitions, requirements, and responsibilities may be obtained here . <br><br></li></ul><strong>SAFETY STATEMENT<br><br></strong>All UCSC employees must understand and follow job safety procedures, attend required health and safety training, proactively promote safety at work, and promptly report actual and potential accidents and injuries.<br><br><strong>EEO/AA<br><br></strong>The University of California is an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. job_title: Data Reporting and Analytics Consultant II, Programming
desc: In addition to the responsibilities listed below, this position is also responsible for programming in analytical programming languages (may include SAS, SQL, SPSS, R, Python, etc.), data management, quality control, and reporting for projects as appropriate; extracting, manipulating, and merging large databases to create analytical datasets; performing simple analytical tasks using SAS or other analytical tools; maintaining and troubleshooting software and programs; and implementing automated reporting and data loading schemes.<br><br><strong>Essential Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li>Pursues self-development and effective relationships with others by sharing resources, information, and knowledge with coworkers and customers; listening, responding to, and seeking performance feedback; acknowledging strengths and weaknesses; assessing and responding to the needs of others; and adapting to and learning from change, difficulties, and feedback. </li><li>Completes work assignments by applying up-to-date knowledge in subject area to meet deadlines; following procedures and policies and applying data, and resources to support projects or initiatives; collaborating with others, often cross-functionally, to solve business problems; supporting the completion of priorities, deadlines, and expectations; communicating progress and information; identifying and recommending ways to address improvement opportunities when possible; and escalating issues or risks as appropriate. </li><li>Assists with data analysis interpretation by organizing and editing reports and presentations telling a compelling story to stakeholders to enable and influence decision making. </li><li>Supports data-informed decisions under the guidance of more senior employees by working with clients to identify and clarify key business needs; assisting in the development of outcomes and process measures; translating business requirements; informing data/information needs and data collection methods; measuring the impact of business decisions on clients, customers, and/or members; working with clients and staff to identify opportunities and methods to improve efficiencies with analysis; supporting end-users; and documenting processes and deliverables. </li><li>Assists with data and information gathering for targeted variables in an established systematic fashion by cleaning and organizing data; querying, merging, and extracting data across sources; completing routine data refresh and update; and providing user support and documentation. </li><li>Supports data preparation for analytic efforts under the guidance of more senior employees by cleaning data to ensure quality and accuracy based on provided guidelines; and consolidating data. </li><li>Assists with the execution of creative data analytic approaches leading to actionable outcomes by organizing metrics to be analyzed and calculating algorithms and conducting basic analyses under the guidance of more senior employees, including descriptive statistics. </li><li>Assists with the development, implementation, and automation of business and reporting solutions by creating summary statistics; organizing data reports, visualizations, and/or interactive Business Intelligence (BI) reports; identifying opportunities to improve exiting reporting solutions; and preparing documentation as appropriate. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Minimum Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Minimum one (1) year experience programming with SAS, SQL, R or other similar analytical programming language. </li><li>Bachelors degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Social/Physical/Life Science, Business, or related field OR Minimum two (2) years experience in data analytics or a directly related field. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Additional Requirements<br><br></strong><ul><li>Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs): SAS Tools; SQL/SAS; Data Extraction; Data Mining; Data Visualization Tools; Statistical Programming Language; Relational Database Management; Project Management; Written Communication</li></ul>

Upgrade is a fintech company that provides affordable and responsible credit, mobile banking, and payment products to everyday consumers. We were the fastest growing company in the Americas last year according to the Financial Times and Upgrade Card was the fastest growing credit card in America two years in a row. We have delivered over $25 billion in affordable and responsible credit to our 2.7M customers. The company is backed by some of the most prominent technology investors and was recently valued at $6.3B.<br><br>We have built an energizing, collaborative and inclusive culture where team members help each other, learn and innovate to move the company and its customers in the right direction, and own the outcome of their efforts.<br><br>Upgrade has been named a “Best Place to Work in the Bay Area” three years in a row, “Top Companies to work for in Arizona” and one of the "Best Engineering Department" awarded annually by Comparably. We've also received recognition for being a best company for Diversity, Women, Culture, and Veterans.<br><br>We are looking for new team members who get excited about designing and delivering new and better products to join a team of 1600 talented and dedicated professionals. Come work with us if you like to tackle big problems and make a meaningful difference in people's lives.<br><br><strong>About the role:<br><br></strong>Upgrade is looking for a Senior Analyst to join our Credit &amp; Investor Analytics team in San Francisco. In this role, you will be working with our Credit Risk team, as well other cross-functional stakeholders on reviewing and maintaining Upgrade's credit policy, strategy and model use across our diverse suite of products.<br><br>This is a hybrid role, 2-3 times per week in our San Francisco, reporting to our Senior Director, Credit Risk.<br><br><strong>What You’ll Do</strong>:<br><br><br><ul><li> Work closely with Credit Risk team to review and enhance Upgrade's underwriting practice (strategy, credit policy, and model use) to deliver investor target yields. </li><li> Monitor credit profile and return/risk performance across products (Personal Loans, Card, Auto, Home Improvement, Travel BNPL) and communicate insights. </li><li> Back-test credit strategies using historical performance and review impact of credit expansion/tightening. </li><li> Develop loss forecasts to reflect credit policy and/or segmentation changes. </li><li> Support periodic reporting to executive management, Credit Risk Committee and Upgrade Investor Team. </li><li> Obtain subject matter expertise in internal and external data sources and ensure data integrity. </li><li> Collaborate with Investor team to support external investor communication on product, segment, and credit policy changes. <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>What We Look For</strong>:<br><br><br><ul><li> 2-5 years of experience in analytics, preferably consumer credit risk </li><li> Bachelor's/Master’s degree in Data Analytics, Mathematical Finance, Economics, or a related quantitative field </li><li> Strong programming skills in Python and/or R </li><li> Advanced experience in SQL </li><li> Experience with Tableau or other BI/data visualization tools </li><li> Detail oriented and strong analytical skill set </li><li> Proactive, driven, and ability to work in a fast-paced environment </li><li> Fintech lender experience preferred <br><br><br></li></ul><strong>What We Offer You: <br><br><br></strong><ul><li> <ul><li>Overdose Prevention Data Analyst<br><br></li></ul>As an AmeriCorps VISTA member you will build the capacity of the California Overdose Prevention Network (COPN; www.copn.org) by supporting the leadership team of a local overdose prevention coalition. You will help lead a local response to the overdose crisis by implementing intervention strategies known to reduce addiction and overdose deaths. This includes safe prescribing, ensuring access to treatment, and harm reduction. Through service with a local coalition, you will address inequities surrounding vulnerable populations, including but not limited to black and indigenous people of color (BIPOC), people of varying socio-economic status, and people of all genders. You will contribute to the goals of the coalition you serve through activities that will be based on local needs including strengthening coalition partnerships and networks; improving materials that support coalition intervention activities; conducting outreach; organizing and/or delivering naloxone trainings; managing coalition websites and social media platforms; assessing opportunities to enhance equitable services and programs; and creating a coalition database and/or data dashboard. This opportunity will provide key skills in logistics, organization, coordination, and interpersonal communication. Members are also part of a statewide member learning community through The Center for Health Leadership and Impact at the Public Health Institute (PHI), the largest AmeriCorps VISTA sponsorship in the Western Region. This community includes ongoing support from VISTA Leads and a monthly series of professional development opportunities, workshops, networking events, and trainings. Learn more about our VISTA network on our website, https://healthleadership.org/pathways/americorps ***NOTE: We have openings for VISTA positions throughout California year-round. <ul><li>Overdose Prevention Data Analyst<br><br></li></ul>As an AmeriCorps VISTA member you will build the capacity of the California Overdose Prevention Network (COPN; www.copn.org) by supporting the leadership team of a local overdose prevention coalition. This includes safe prescribing, ensuring access to treatment, and harm reduction. Through service with a local coalition, you will address inequities surrounding vulnerable populations, including but not limited to black and indigenous people of color (BIPOC), people of varying socio-economic status, and people of all genders. You will contribute to the goals of the coalition you serve through activities that will be based on local needs including strengthening coalition partnerships and networks; improving materials that support coalition intervention activities; conducting outreach; organizing and/or delivering naloxone trainings; managing coalition websites and social media platforms; assessing opportunities to enhance equitable services and programs; and creating a coalition database and/or data dashboard. This opportunity will provide key skills in logistics, organization, coordination, and interpersonal communication. Members are also part of a statewide member learning community through The Center for Health Leadership and Impact at the Public Health Institute (PHI), the largest AmeriCorps VISTA sponsorship in the Western Region. This community includes ongoing support from VISTA Leads and a monthly series of professional development opportunities, workshops, networking events, and trainings.
